#. class="division">
msgctxt "dn16:1.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 16"
msgstr "Long Discourses 16"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn16:2.1"
msgid "Mahāparinibbānasutta"
msgstr "The Great Discourse on the Buddha’s Extinguishment"

#. </h1></div><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.1"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.72"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:3.1"
msgid "<span class=\"evam\">Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​</span>"
msgstr "<span class=”evam”>So I have heard.</span>"

msgctxt "dn16:3.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak "
"Mountain."

msgctxt "dn16:3.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto vajjī "
"abhiyātukāmo hoti."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time King Ajātasattu Vedehiputta of Māgadha wanted to invade the "
"Vajjis."

msgctxt "dn16:3.4"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He declared:"

#. VAR: ucchecchāmi → ucchejjāmi (s1-3, km, pts1) | ucchijjāmi (mr)
#. VAR: anayabyasanaṃ āpādessāmī”ti → āpādessāmi vajjīti (bj) | āpādessāmi
#. vajjinti (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn16:3.5"
msgid ""
"“ahaṃ hime vajjī evaṃmahiddhike evaṃmahānubhāve ucchecchāmi vajjī, "
"vināsessāmi vajjī, anayabyasanaṃ āpādessāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“I will wipe out these Vajjis, so mighty and powerful! I will destroy them, "
"and lay ruin and devastation upon them!”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.2"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.73"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto vassakāraṃ brāhmaṇaṃ "
"magadhamahāmattaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"And then King Ajātasattu addressed Vassakāra the brahmin minister of Māgadha:"

msgctxt "dn16:4.2"
msgid "“ehi tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkama;"
msgstr "“Please, brahmin, go to the Buddha,"

msgctxt "dn16:4.3"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā mama vacanena bhagavato pāde sirasā vandāhi, appābādhaṃ "
"appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ puccha:"
msgstr ""
"and in my name bow with your head to his feet. Ask him if he is healthy and "
"well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably."

msgctxt "dn16:4.4"
msgid ""
"‘rājā, bhante, māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto bhagavato pāde sirasā vandati, "
"appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchatī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:4.5"
msgid "Evañca vadehi:"
msgstr "And then say: "

msgctxt "dn16:4.6"
msgid "‘rājā, bhante, māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto vajjī abhiyātukāmo."
msgstr ""
"‘Sir, King Ajātasattu Vedehiputta of Māgadha wants to invade the Vajjis."

msgctxt "dn16:4.7"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "dn16:4.8"
msgid ""
"“ahaṃ hime vajjī evaṃmahiddhike evaṃmahānubhāve ucchecchāmi vajjī, "
"vināsessāmi vajjī, anayabyasanaṃ āpādessāmī”’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I will wipe out these Vajjis, so mighty and powerful! I will destroy them, "
"and lay ruin and devastation upon them!’”"

msgctxt "dn16:4.9"
msgid "Yathā te bhagavā byākaroti, taṃ sādhukaṃ uggahetvā mama āroceyyāsi."
msgstr "Remember well how the Buddha answers and tell it to me."

msgctxt "dn16:4.10"
msgid "Na hi tathāgatā vitathaṃ bhaṇantī”ti."
msgstr "For Realized Ones say nothing that is not so.”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:5.1"
msgid "1. Vassakārabrāhmaṇa"
msgstr "The Brahmin Vassakāra"

# Reading yojapetva as per PTS.
#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.3"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:6.1"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho vassakāro brāhmaṇo magadhamahāmatto rañño māgadhassa "
"ajātasattussa vedehiputtassa paṭissutvā bhaddāni bhaddāni yānāni yojetvā "
"bhaddaṃ bhaddaṃ yānaṃ abhiruhitvā bhaddehi bhaddehi yānehi rājagahamhā "
"niyyāsi, yena gijjhakūṭo pabbato tena pāyāsi."
msgstr ""
"“Yes, sir,” Vassakāra replied. He had the finest carriages harnessed. Then "
"he mounted a fine carriage and, along with other fine carriages, set out "
"from Rājagaha for the Vulture’s Peak Mountain."

msgctxt "dn16:6.2"
msgid ""
"Yāvatikā yānassa bhūmi, yānena gantvā, yānā paccorohitvā pattikova yena "
"bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"He went by carriage as far as the terrain allowed, then descended and "
"approached the Buddha on foot,"

msgctxt "dn16:6.3"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr "and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "dn16:6.4"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side,"

msgctxt "dn16:6.5"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vassakāro brāhmaṇo magadhamahāmatto bhagavantaṃ "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn16:6.6"
msgid ""
"“rājā, bho gotama, māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto bhoto gotamassa pāde "
"sirasā vandati, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ "
"pucchati."
msgstr ""
"“Master Gotama, King Ajātasattu Vedehiputta of Māgadha bows with his head to "
"your feet. He asks if you are healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living "
"comfortably."

#. VAR: Rājā → evañca vadeti rājā (mr)
msgctxt "dn16:6.7"
msgid "Rājā, bho gotama, māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto vajjī abhiyātukāmo."
msgstr "Master Gotama, King Ajātasattu wants to invade the Vajjis."

msgctxt "dn16:6.8"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He has declared:"

msgctxt "dn16:6.9"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ hime vajjī evaṃmahiddhike evaṃmahānubhāve ucchecchāmi vajjī, "
"vināsessāmi vajjī, anayabyasanaṃ āpādessāmī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I will wipe out these Vajjis, so mighty and powerful! I will destroy them, "
"and lay ruin and devastation upon them!’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:7.1"
msgid "2. Rājaaparihāniyadhamma"
msgstr "Principles That Prevent Decline"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.4"></a>
#. VAR: bījayamāno → vījayamāno (bj) | vījiyamāno (s1-3) | vījamāno (pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:8.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā ānando bhagavato piṭṭhito ṭhito hoti "
"bhagavantaṃ bījayamāno."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Venerable Ānanda was standing behind the Buddha fanning him."

msgctxt "dn16:8.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to him:"

msgctxt "dn16:8.3"
msgid ""
"“kinti te, ānanda, sutaṃ, ‘vajjī abhiṇhaṃ sannipātā sannipātabahulā’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Ānanda, have you heard that the Vajjis meet frequently and have many "
"meetings?”"

msgctxt "dn16:8.4"
msgid "“Sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante:"
msgstr "“I have heard that, sir.”"

msgctxt "dn16:8.5"
msgid "‘vajjī abhiṇhaṃ sannipātā sannipātabahulā’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:8.6"
msgid ""
"“Yāvakīvañca, ānanda, vajjī abhiṇhaṃ sannipātā sannipātabahulā bhavissanti, "
"vuddhiyeva, ānanda, vajjīnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(1)</span>"
msgstr ""
"“As long as the Vajjis meet frequently and have many meetings, they can "
"expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.74"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:9.1"
msgid ""
"Kinti te, ānanda, sutaṃ, ‘vajjī samaggā sannipatanti, samaggā vuṭṭhahanti, "
"samaggā vajjikaraṇīyāni karontī’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Ānanda, have you heard that the Vajjis meet in harmony, leave in harmony, "
"and carry on their business in harmony?”"

msgctxt "dn16:9.2"
msgid "“Sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante:"
msgstr "“I have heard that, sir.”"

msgctxt "dn16:9.3"
msgid ""
"‘vajjī samaggā sannipatanti, samaggā vuṭṭhahanti, samaggā vajjikaraṇīyāni "
"karontī’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:9.4"
msgid ""
"“Yāvakīvañca, ānanda, vajjī samaggā sannipatissanti, samaggā vuṭṭhahissanti, "
"samaggā vajjikaraṇīyāni karissanti, vuddhiyeva, ānanda, vajjīnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, "
"no parihāni. <span class=\"brnum\">(2)</span>"
msgstr ""
"“As long as the Vajjis meet in harmony, leave in harmony, and carry on their "
"business in harmony, they can expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:10.1"
msgid ""
"Kinti te, ānanda, sutaṃ, ‘vajjī apaññattaṃ na paññapenti, paññattaṃ na "
"samucchindanti, yathāpaññatte porāṇe vajjidhamme samādāya vattantī’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Ānanda, have you heard that the Vajjis don’t make new decrees or abolish "
"existing decrees, but proceed having undertaken the traditional Vajjian "
"principles as they have been decreed?”"

msgctxt "dn16:10.2"
msgid "“Sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante:"
msgstr "“I have heard that, sir.”"

msgctxt "dn16:10.3"
msgid ""
"‘vajjī apaññattaṃ na paññapenti, paññattaṃ na samucchindanti, yathāpaññatte "
"porāṇe vajjidhamme samādāya vattantī’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:10.4"
msgid ""
"“Yāvakīvañca, ānanda, vajjī apaññattaṃ na paññapessanti, paññattaṃ na "
"samucchindissanti, yathāpaññatte porāṇe vajjidhamme samādāya vattissanti, "
"vuddhiyeva, ānanda, vajjīnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(3)</span>"
msgstr ""
"“As long as the Vajjis don’t make new decrees or abolish existing decrees, "
"but proceed having undertaken the traditional Vajjian principles as they "
"have been decreed, they can expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a>
#. VAR: garuṃ karonti → garukaronti (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:11.1"
msgid ""
"Kinti te, ānanda, sutaṃ, ‘vajjī ye te vajjīnaṃ vajjimahallakā, te sakkaronti "
"garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, tesañca sotabbaṃ maññantī’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Ānanda, have you heard that the Vajjis honor, respect, esteem, and venerate "
"Vajjian elders, and think them worth listening to?”"

msgctxt "dn16:11.2"
msgid "“Sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante:"
msgstr "“I have heard that, sir.”"

msgctxt "dn16:11.3"
msgid ""
"‘vajjī ye te vajjīnaṃ vajjimahallakā, te sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti "
"pūjenti, tesañca sotabbaṃ maññantī’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:11.4"
msgid ""
"“Yāvakīvañca, ānanda, vajjī ye te vajjīnaṃ vajjimahallakā, te sakkarissanti "
"garuṃ karissanti mānessanti pūjessanti, tesañca sotabbaṃ maññissanti, "
"vuddhiyeva, ānanda, vajjīnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(4)</span>"
msgstr ""
"“As long as the Vajjis honor, respect, esteem, and venerate Vajjian elders, "
"and think them worth listening to, they can expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:12.1"
msgid ""
"Kinti te, ānanda, sutaṃ, ‘vajjī yā tā kulitthiyo kulakumāriyo, tā na okkassa "
"pasayha vāsentī’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Ānanda, have you heard that the Vajjians don’t rape or abduct women or girls "
"from their families and force them to live with them?”"

msgctxt "dn16:12.2"
msgid "“Sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante:"
msgstr "“I have heard that, sir.”"

msgctxt "dn16:12.3"
msgid "‘vajjī yā tā kulitthiyo kulakumāriyo tā na okkassa pasayha vāsentī’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:12.4"
msgid ""
"“Yāvakīvañca, ānanda, vajjī yā tā kulitthiyo kulakumāriyo, tā na okkassa "
"pasayha vāsessanti, vuddhiyeva, ānanda, vajjīnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni. <"
"span class=\"brnum\">(5)</span>"
msgstr ""
"“As long as the Vajjians don’t rape or abduct women or girls from their "
"families and force them to live with them, they can expect growth, not "
"decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.75"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:13.1"
msgid ""
"Kinti te, ānanda, sutaṃ, ‘vajjī yāni tāni vajjīnaṃ vajjicetiyāni "
"abbhantarāni ceva bāhirāni ca, tāni sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti "
"pūjenti, tesañca dinnapubbaṃ katapubbaṃ dhammikaṃ baliṃ no parihāpentī’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Ānanda, have you heard that the Vajjis honor, respect, esteem, and venerate "
"the Vajjian shrines, whether inner or outer, not neglecting the proper "
"spirit-offerings that were given and made in the past?”"

msgctxt "dn16:13.2"
msgid "“Sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante:"
msgstr "“I have heard that, sir.”"

msgctxt "dn16:13.3"
msgid ""
"‘vajjī yāni tāni vajjīnaṃ vajjicetiyāni abbhantarāni ceva bāhirāni ca, tāni "
"sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti tesañca dinnapubbaṃ katapubbaṃ "
"dhammikaṃ baliṃ no parihāpentī’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:13.4"
msgid ""
"“Yāvakīvañca, ānanda, vajjī yāni tāni vajjīnaṃ vajjicetiyāni abbhantarāni "
"ceva bāhirāni ca, tāni sakkarissanti garuṃ karissanti mānessanti pūjessanti, "
"tesañca dinnapubbaṃ katapubbaṃ dhammikaṃ baliṃ no parihāpessanti, "
"vuddhiyeva, ānanda, vajjīnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(6)</span>"
msgstr ""
"“As long as the Vajjis honor, respect, esteem, and venerate the Vajjian "
"shrines, whether inner or outer, not neglecting the proper spirit-offerings "
"that were given and made in the past, they can expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:14.1"
msgid ""
"Kinti te, ānanda, sutaṃ, ‘vajjīnaṃ arahantesu dhammikā rakkhāvaraṇagutti "
"susaṃvihitā, kinti anāgatā ca arahanto vijitaṃ āgaccheyyuṃ, āgatā ca "
"arahanto vijite phāsu vihareyyun’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Ānanda, have you heard that the Vajjis arrange for proper protection, "
"shelter, and security for perfected ones, so that more perfected ones might "
"come to the realm and those already here may live in comfort?”"

msgctxt "dn16:14.2"
msgid ""
"“Sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante ‘vajjīnaṃ arahantesu dhammikā rakkhāvaraṇagutti "
"susaṃvihitā kinti anāgatā ca arahanto vijitaṃ āgaccheyyuṃ, āgatā ca arahanto "
"vijite phāsu vihareyyun’”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:14.3"
msgid ""
"“Yāvakīvañca, ānanda, vajjīnaṃ arahantesu dhammikā rakkhāvaraṇagutti "
"susaṃvihitā bhavissati, kinti anāgatā ca arahanto vijitaṃ āgaccheyyuṃ, āgatā "
"ca arahanto vijite phāsu vihareyyunti."
msgstr ""
"“As long as the Vajjis arrange for proper protection, shelter, and security "
"for perfected ones, so that more perfected ones might come to the realm and "
"those already here may live in comfort, they can expect growth, not decline.”"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:14.4"
msgid ""
"Vuddhiyeva, ānanda, vajjīnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihānī”ti. <span class=\""
"brnum\">(7)</span>"
msgstr " "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.5"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:15.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā vassakāraṃ brāhmaṇaṃ magadhamahāmattaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to Vassakāra:"

#. VAR: sārandade → sānandare (mr)
msgctxt "dn16:15.2"
msgid "“ekamidāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, samayaṃ vesāliyaṃ viharāmi sārandade cetiye."
msgstr ""
"“Brahmin, this one time I was staying near Vesālī at the Sarandada woodland "
"shrine."

msgctxt "dn16:15.3"
msgid "Tatrāhaṃ vajjīnaṃ ime satta aparihāniye dhamme desesiṃ."
msgstr "There I taught the Vajjis these seven principles that prevent decline."

msgctxt "dn16:15.4"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, brāhmaṇa, ime satta aparihāniyā dhammā vajjīsu ṭhassanti, imesu "
"ca sattasu aparihāniyesu dhammesu vajjī sandississanti, vuddhiyeva, "
"brāhmaṇa, vajjīnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihānī”ti."
msgstr ""
"As long as these seven principles that prevent decline last among the "
"Vajjians, and as long as the Vajjians are seen following them, they can "
"expect growth, not decline.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.76"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:16.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, vassakāro brāhmaṇo magadhamahāmatto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When the Buddha had spoken, Vassakāra said to him:"

#. VAR: vajjī → vajjīnaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "dn16:16.2"
msgid ""
"“ekamekenapi, bho gotama, aparihāniyena dhammena samannāgatānaṃ vajjīnaṃ "
"vuddhiyeva pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni."
msgstr ""
"“Master Gotama, if the Vajjis follow even a single one of these principles "
"they can expect growth, not decline."

msgctxt "dn16:16.3"
msgid "Ko pana vādo sattahi aparihāniyehi dhammehi."
msgstr "How much more so all seven!"

#. VAR: Akaraṇīyāva → akaraṇīyā ca (bj, s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "dn16:16.4"
msgid ""
"Akaraṇīyāva, bho gotama, vajjī raññā māgadhena ajātasattunā vedehiputtena "
"yadidaṃ yuddhassa, aññatra upalāpanāya aññatra mithubhedā."
msgstr ""
"King Ajātasattu cannot defeat the Vajjis in war, unless by diplomacy or by "
"sowing dissension."

msgctxt "dn16:16.5"
msgid ""
"Handa ca dāni mayaṃ, bho gotama, gacchāma, bahukiccā mayaṃ bahukaraṇīyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Well, now, Master Gotama, I must go. I have many duties, and much to do.”"

msgctxt "dn16:16.6"
msgid "“Yassadāni tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, kālaṃ maññasī”ti."
msgstr "“Please, brahmin, go when you’re ready.” "

msgctxt "dn16:16.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho vassakāro brāhmaṇo magadhamahāmatto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā "
"anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"Then Vassakāra the brahmin, having approved and agreed with what the Buddha "
"said, got up from his seat and left."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:17.1"
msgid "3. Bhikkhuaparihāniyadhamma"
msgstr "Principles That Prevent Decline Among the Mendicants"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.6"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:18.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā acirapakkante vassakāre brāhmaṇe magadhamahāmatte "
"āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Soon after he had left, the Buddha said to Ānanda:"

msgctxt "dn16:18.2"
msgid ""
"“gaccha tvaṃ, ānanda, yāvatikā bhikkhū rājagahaṃ upanissāya viharanti, te "
"sabbe upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ sannipātehī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Go, Ānanda, gather all the mendicants staying in the vicinity of Rājagaha "
"together in the assembly hall.”"

msgctxt "dn16:18.3"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paṭissutvā yāvatikā bhikkhū "
"rājagahaṃ upanissāya viharanti, te sabbe upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ sannipātetvā yena "
"bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"“Yes, sir,” relied Ānanda. He did what the Buddha asked. Then he went back,"

msgctxt "dn16:18.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr "bowed, stood to one side,"

msgctxt "dn16:18.5"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

msgctxt "dn16:18.6"
msgid ""
"“sannipatito, bhante, bhikkhusaṅgho, yassadāni, bhante, bhagavā kālaṃ "
"maññatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, the mendicant Sangha has assembled. Please, sir, go at your "
"convenience.” "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:19.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā uṭṭhāyāsanā yena upaṭṭhānasālā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then the Buddha went to the assembly hall,"

msgctxt "dn16:19.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "where he sat on the seat spread out"

msgctxt "dn16:19.3"
msgid "Nisajja kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "and addressed the mendicants: "

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:19.4"
msgid ""
"“satta vo, bhikkhave, aparihāniye dhamme desessāmi, taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ "
"manasikarotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, I will teach you these seven principles that prevent decline. "
"Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "dn16:19.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "dn16:19.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:20.1"
msgid ""
"“Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū abhiṇhaṃ sannipātā sannipātabahulā "
"bhavissanti, vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni. <"
"span class=\"brnum\">(1)</span>"
msgstr ""
"As long as the mendicants meet frequently and have many meetings, they can "
"expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.77"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:21.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū samaggā sannipatissanti, samaggā "
"vuṭṭhahissanti, samaggā saṅghakaraṇīyāni karissanti, vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, "
"bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni. <span class=\"brnum\">(2)</span>"
msgstr ""
"As long as the mendicants meet in harmony, leave in harmony, and carry on "
"their business in harmony, they can expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:22.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū apaññattaṃ na paññapessanti, paññattaṃ na "
"samucchindissanti, yathāpaññattesu sikkhāpadesu samādāya vattissanti, "
"vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni. <span class=\""
"brnum\">(3)</span>"
msgstr ""
"As long as the mendicants don’t make new decrees or abolish existing "
"decrees, but undertake and follow the ancient Vajjian principles as they "
"have been decreed, they can expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:23.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū ye te bhikkhū therā rattaññū cirapabbajitā "
"saṅghapitaro saṅghapariṇāyakā, te sakkarissanti garuṃ karissanti mānessanti "
"pūjessanti, tesañca sotabbaṃ maññissanti, vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ "
"pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni. <span class=\"brnum\">(4)</span>"
msgstr ""
"As long as the mendicants honor, respect, esteem, and venerate the senior "
"mendicants—of long standing, long gone forth, fathers and leaders of the "
"Saṅgha—and think them worth listening to, they can expect growth, not "
"decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:24.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū uppannāya taṇhāya ponobbhavikāya na vasaṃ "
"gacchissanti, vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni. <"
"span class=\"brnum\">(5)</span>"
msgstr ""
"As long as the mendicants don’t fall under the sway of arisen craving for "
"future lives, they can expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:25.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū āraññakesu senāsanesu sāpekkhā bhavissanti, "
"vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni. <span class=\""
"brnum\">(6)</span>"
msgstr ""
"As long as the mendicants take care to live in wilderness lodgings, they can "
"expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:26.1"
msgid "Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū paccattaññeva satiṃ upaṭṭhapessanti:"
msgstr "As long as the mendicants individually establish mindfulness, so that"

#. VAR: phāsu → phāsuṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:26.2"
msgid ""
"‘kinti anāgatā ca pesalā sabrahmacārī āgaccheyyuṃ, āgatā ca pesalā "
"sabrahmacārī phāsu vihareyyun’ti."
msgstr ""
"more good-hearted spiritual companions might come, and those that have "
"already come may live comfortably,"

msgctxt "dn16:26.3"
msgid ""
"Vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni. <span class=\""
"brnum\">(7)</span>"
msgstr "they can expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:27.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, ime satta aparihāniyā dhammā bhikkhūsu ṭhassanti, "
"imesu ca sattasu aparihāniyesu dhammesu bhikkhū sandississanti, vuddhiyeva, "
"bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni."
msgstr ""
"As long as these seven principles that prevent decline last among the "
"mendicants, and as long as the mendicants are seen following them, they can "
"expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.7"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:28.1"
msgid ""
"Aparepi vo, bhikkhave, satta aparihāniye dhamme desessāmi, taṃ suṇātha, "
"sādhukaṃ manasikarotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "I will teach you seven more principles that prevent decline. …"

msgctxt "dn16:28.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:28.3"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.78"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:29.1"
msgid ""
"“Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū na kammārāmā bhavissanti na kammaratā na "
"kammārāmatamanuyuttā, vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no "
"parihāni. <span class=\"brnum\">(1)</span>"
msgstr ""
"As long as the mendicants don’t relish work, loving it and liking to relish "
"it, they can expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:30.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū na bhassārāmā bhavissanti na bhassaratā na "
"bhassārāmatamanuyuttā, vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no "
"parihāni. <span class=\"brnum\">(2)</span>"
msgstr "As long as they don’t enjoy talk …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:31.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū na niddārāmā bhavissanti na niddāratā na "
"niddārāmatamanuyuttā, vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no "
"parihāni. <span class=\"brnum\">(3)</span>"
msgstr "sleep …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:32.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū na saṅgaṇikārāmā bhavissanti na "
"saṅgaṇikaratā na saṅgaṇikārāmatamanuyuttā, vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ "
"pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni. <span class=\"brnum\">(4)</span>"
msgstr "company …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:33.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū na pāpicchā bhavissanti na pāpikānaṃ "
"icchānaṃ vasaṃ gatā, vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no "
"parihāni. <span class=\"brnum\">(5)</span>"
msgstr ""
"they don’t have wicked desires, falling under the sway of wicked desires …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:34.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū na pāpamittā bhavissanti na pāpasahāyā na "
"pāpasampavaṅkā, vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni. <"
"span class=\"brnum\">(6)</span>"
msgstr "they don’t have bad friends, companions, and associates …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="30"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:35.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū na oramattakena visesādhigamena "
"antarāvosānaṃ āpajjissanti, vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no "
"parihāni. <span class=\"brnum\">(7)</span>"
msgstr ""
"they don’t stop half-way after achieving some insignificant distinction, "
"they can expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="31"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.8"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:36.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, ime satta aparihāniyā dhammā bhikkhūsu ṭhassanti, "
"imesu ca sattasu aparihāniyesu dhammesu bhikkhū sandississanti, vuddhiyeva, "
"bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni."
msgstr ""
"As long as these seven principles that prevent decline last among the "
"mendicants, and as long as the mendicants are seen following them, they can "
"expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="32"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.79"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:37.1"
msgid "Aparepi vo, bhikkhave, satta aparihāniye dhamme desessāmi …"
msgstr "I will teach you seven more principles that prevent decline. …"

msgctxt "dn16:37.2"
msgid "pe …."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:37.3"
msgid "Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū saddhā bhavissanti …"
msgstr "As long as the mendicants are faithful …"

msgctxt "dn16:37.4"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:37.5"
msgid "hirimanā bhavissanti …"
msgstr "conscientious …"

msgctxt "dn16:37.6"
msgid "ottappī bhavissanti …"
msgstr "prudent …"

msgctxt "dn16:37.7"
msgid "bahussutā bhavissanti …"
msgstr "learned …"

msgctxt "dn16:37.8"
msgid "āraddhavīriyā bhavissanti …"
msgstr "energetic …"

msgctxt "dn16:37.9"
msgid "upaṭṭhitassatī bhavissanti …"
msgstr "mindful …"

msgctxt "dn16:37.10"
msgid ""
"paññavanto bhavissanti, vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no "
"parihāni."
msgstr "wise, they can expect growth, not decline."

msgctxt "dn16:37.11"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, ime satta aparihāniyā dhammā bhikkhūsu ṭhassanti, "
"imesu ca sattasu aparihāniyesu dhammesu bhikkhū sandississanti, vuddhiyeva, "
"bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni."
msgstr ""
"As long as these seven principles that prevent decline last among the "
"mendicants, and as long as the mendicants are seen following them, they can "
"expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="33"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:38.1"
msgid ""
"Aparepi vo, bhikkhave, satta aparihāniye dhamme desessāmi, taṃ suṇātha, "
"sādhukaṃ manasikarotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "I will teach you seven more principles that prevent decline. …"

msgctxt "dn16:38.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:38.3"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="34"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.9"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:39.1"
msgid "“Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu satisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāvessanti …"
msgstr ""
"As long as the mendicants develop the awakening-factors of mindfulness …"

msgctxt "dn16:39.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:39.3"
msgid "dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāvessanti …"
msgstr "investigation of principles …"

msgctxt "dn16:39.4"
msgid "vīriyasambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāvessanti …"
msgstr "energy …"

msgctxt "dn16:39.5"
msgid "pītisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāvessanti …"
msgstr "rapture …"

msgctxt "dn16:39.6"
msgid "passaddhisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāvessanti …"
msgstr "tranquillity …"

msgctxt "dn16:39.7"
msgid "samādhisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāvessanti …"
msgstr "immersion … "

msgctxt "dn16:39.8"
msgid ""
"upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāvessanti, vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ "
"pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni."
msgstr "equanimity, they can expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="35"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.10"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:40.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, ime satta aparihāniyā dhammā bhikkhūsu ṭhassanti, "
"imesu ca sattasu aparihāniyesu dhammesu bhikkhū sandississanti, vuddhiyeva, "
"bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā no parihāni."
msgstr ""
"As long as these seven principles that prevent decline last among the "
"mendicants, and as long as the mendicants are seen following them, they can "
"expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="36"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:41.1"
msgid ""
"Aparepi vo, bhikkhave, satta aparihāniye dhamme desessāmi, taṃ suṇātha, "
"sādhukaṃ manasikarotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "I will teach you seven more principles that prevent decline. …"

msgctxt "dn16:41.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:41.3"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="37"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:42.1"
msgid "“Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū aniccasaññaṃ bhāvessanti …"
msgstr "As long as the mendicants develop the perceptions of impermanence …"

msgctxt "dn16:42.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:42.3"
msgid "anattasaññaṃ bhāvessanti …"
msgstr "not-self …"

msgctxt "dn16:42.4"
msgid "asubhasaññaṃ bhāvessanti …"
msgstr "ugliness …"

msgctxt "dn16:42.5"
msgid "ādīnavasaññaṃ bhāvessanti …"
msgstr "drawbacks …"

msgctxt "dn16:42.6"
msgid "pahānasaññaṃ bhāvessanti …"
msgstr "giving up …"

msgctxt "dn16:42.7"
msgid "virāgasaññaṃ bhāvessanti …"
msgstr "fading away …"

msgctxt "dn16:42.8"
msgid ""
"nirodhasaññaṃ bhāvessanti, vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no "
"parihāni."
msgstr "cessation, they can expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="38"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.80"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:43.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, ime satta aparihāniyā dhammā bhikkhūsu ṭhassanti, "
"imesu ca sattasu aparihāniyesu dhammesu bhikkhū sandississanti, vuddhiyeva, "
"bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni."
msgstr ""
"As long as these seven principles that guard against decline last among the "
"mendicants, and as long as the mendicants are seen following them, they can "
"expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="39"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.11"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:44.1"
msgid ""
"Cha vo, bhikkhave, aparihāniye dhamme desessāmi, taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ "
"manasikarotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "I will teach you six principles that guard against decline. …"

msgctxt "dn16:44.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:44.3"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="40"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:45.1"
msgid ""
"“Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū mettaṃ kāyakammaṃ paccupaṭṭhāpessanti "
"sabrahmacārīsu āvi ceva raho ca, vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ "
"pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni. <span class=\"brnum\">(1)</span>"
msgstr ""
"As long as the mendicants consistently treat their spiritual companions with "
"bodily kindness …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="41"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:46.1"
msgid "Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū mettaṃ vacīkammaṃ paccupaṭṭhāpessanti …"
msgstr "verbal kindness …"

msgctxt "dn16:46.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:46.3"
msgid ""
"mettaṃ manokammaṃ paccupaṭṭhāpessanti sabrahmacārīsu āvi ceva raho ca, "
"vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni."
msgstr ""
"and mental kindness both in public and in private, they can expect growth, "
"not decline."

msgctxt "dn16:46.4"
msgid "(2–3.)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="42"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:47.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū, ye te lābhā dhammikā dhammaladdhā antamaso "
"pattapariyāpannamattampi tathārūpehi lābhehi appaṭivibhattabhogī bhavissanti "
"sīlavantehi sabrahmacārīhi sādhāraṇabhogī, vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ "
"pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni. <span class=\"brnum\">(4)</span>"
msgstr ""
"As long as the mendicants share without reservation any material possessions "
"they have gained by legitimate means, even the food placed in the alms-bowl, "
"using them in common with their ethical spiritual companions, they can "
"expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="43"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:48.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū yāni tāni sīlāni akhaṇḍāni acchiddāni "
"asabalāni akammāsāni bhujissāni viññūpasatthāni aparāmaṭṭhāni "
"samādhisaṃvattanikāni tathārūpesu sīlesu sīlasāmaññagatā viharissanti "
"sabrahmacārīhi āvi ceva raho ca, vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ "
"pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni. <span class=\"brnum\">(5)</span>"
msgstr ""
"As long as the mendicants live according to the precepts shared with their "
"spiritual companions, both in public and in private—such precepts as are "
"uncorrupted, unflawed, unblemished, untainted, liberating, praised by "
"sensible people, not mistaken, and leading to immersion—they can expect "
"growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="44"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:49.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhū yāyaṃ diṭṭhi ariyā niyyānikā, niyyāti "
"takkarassa sammā dukkhakkhayāya, tathārūpāya diṭṭhiyā diṭṭhisāmaññagatā "
"viharissanti sabrahmacārīhi āvi ceva raho ca, vuddhiyeva, bhikkhave, "
"bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihāni. <span class=\"brnum\">(6)</span>"
msgstr ""
"As long as the mendicants live according to the view shared with their "
"spiritual companions, both in public and in private—the view that is noble "
"and emancipating, and leads one who practices it to the complete end of "
"suffering—they can expect growth, not decline."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="45"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.81"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:50.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, ime cha aparihāniyā dhammā bhikkhūsu ṭhassanti, "
"imesu ca chasu aparihāniyesu dhammesu bhikkhū sandississanti, vuddhiyeva, "
"bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā, no parihānī”ti."
msgstr ""
"As long as these six principles that guard against decline last among the "
"mendicants, and as long as the mendicants are seen following them, they can "
"expect growth, not decline.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn16:51.1"
msgid "()"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="46"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.12"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:52.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharanto gijjhakūṭe pabbate etadeva bahulaṃ "
"bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ karoti:"
msgstr ""
"And while staying there at the Vulture’s Peak the Buddha often gave this "
"Dhamma talk to the mendicants:"

msgctxt "dn16:52.2"
msgid "“iti sīlaṃ, iti samādhi, iti paññā."
msgstr "“Such is ethics, such is immersion, such is wisdom."

msgctxt "dn16:52.3"
msgid "Sīlaparibhāvito samādhi mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso."
msgstr "When immersion is imbued with ethics it’s very fruitful and beneficial."

msgctxt "dn16:52.4"
msgid "Samādhiparibhāvitā paññā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā."
msgstr "When wisdom is imbued with immersion it’s very fruitful and beneficial."

msgctxt "dn16:52.5"
msgid "Paññāparibhāvitaṃ cittaṃ sammadeva āsavehi vimuccati, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"When the mind is imbued with wisdom it is rightly freed from the "
"defilements, namely,"

msgctxt "dn16:52.6"
msgid "kāmāsavā, bhavāsavā, avijjāsavā”ti."
msgstr "the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="47"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.13"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:53.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā rājagahe yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ "
"āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha had stayed in Rājagaha as long as he wished, he addressed "
"Venerable Ānanda:"

msgctxt "dn16:53.2"
msgid "“āyāmānanda, yena ambalaṭṭhikā tenupasaṅkamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Ānanda, let’s go to Ambalaṭṭhikā.”"

msgctxt "dn16:53.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

msgctxt "dn16:53.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ yena ambalaṭṭhikā tadavasari."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants arrived at "
"Ambalaṭṭhikā,"

#. <a class="wp" id="wp1.14"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:53.5"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā ambalaṭṭhikāyaṃ viharati rājāgārake."
msgstr "where he stayed in the royal rest-house."

msgctxt "dn16:53.6"
msgid ""
"Tatrāpi sudaṃ bhagavā ambalaṭṭhikāyaṃ viharanto rājāgārake etadeva bahulaṃ "
"bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ karoti:"
msgstr ""
"And while staying there, too, he often gave this Dhamma talk to the "
"mendicants:"

msgctxt "dn16:53.7"
msgid "“iti sīlaṃ iti samādhi iti paññā."
msgstr "“Such is ethics, such is immersion, such is wisdom."

msgctxt "dn16:53.8"
msgid "Sīlaparibhāvito samādhi mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso."
msgstr "When immersion is imbued with ethics it’s very fruitful and beneficial."

msgctxt "dn16:53.9"
msgid "Samādhiparibhāvitā paññā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā."
msgstr "When wisdom is imbued with immersion it’s very fruitful and beneficial."

msgctxt "dn16:53.10"
msgid "Paññāparibhāvitaṃ cittaṃ sammadeva āsavehi vimuccati, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"When the mind is imbued with wisdom it is rightly freed from the "
"defilements, namely,"

msgctxt "dn16:53.11"
msgid "kāmāsavā, bhavāsavā, avijjāsavā”ti."
msgstr "the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="48"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.15"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:54.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā ambalaṭṭhikāyaṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ "
"āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha had stayed in Ambalaṭṭhikā as long as he wished, he "
"addressed Venerable Ānanda:"

msgctxt "dn16:54.2"
msgid "“āyāmānanda, yena nāḷandā tenupasaṅkamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Ānanda, let’s go to Nāḷandā.”"

msgctxt "dn16:54.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:54.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ yena nāḷandā tadavasari, "
"tatra sudaṃ bhagavā nāḷandāyaṃ viharati pāvārikambavane."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants arrived at "
"Ambalaṭṭhikā, where he stayed in Pāvārika’s mango grove. "

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:55.1"
msgid "4. Sāriputtasīhanāda"
msgstr "Sāriputta’s Lion’s Roar"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="49"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.16"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.82"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:56.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then Sāriputta went up to the Buddha,"

msgctxt "dn16:56.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed, sat down to one side, "

msgctxt "dn16:56.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

msgctxt "dn16:56.4"
msgid "“evaṃ pasanno ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavati;"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, I have such confidence in the Buddha that I believe there’s no other "
"ascetic or brahmin—whether past, future, or present—whose direct knowledge "
"is superior to the Buddha when it comes to awakening.”"

msgctxt "dn16:56.5"
msgid ""
"na cāhu na ca bhavissati na cetarahi vijjati añño samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā "
"bhagavatā bhiyyobhiññataro yadidaṃ sambodhiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"I believe there’s no other ascetic or brahmin—whether past, future, or "
"present—whose direct knowledge is superior to the Buddha when it comes to "
"awakening.”"

#. VAR: āsabhī vācā → āsabhivācā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn16:56.6"
msgid ""
"“Uḷārā kho te ayaṃ, sāriputta, āsabhī vācā bhāsitā, ekaṃso gahito, sīhanādo "
"nadito:"
msgstr ""
"“That’s a grand and dramatic statement, Sāriputta. You’ve roared a "
"definitive, categorical lion’s roar, saying:"

msgctxt "dn16:56.7"
msgid "‘evaṃpasanno ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavati;"
msgstr "‘I have such confidence in the Buddha that"

msgctxt "dn16:56.8"
msgid ""
"na cāhu na ca bhavissati na cetarahi vijjati añño samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā "
"bhagavatā bhiyyobhiññataro yadidaṃ sambodhiyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"I believe there’s no other ascetic or brahmin—whether past, future, or "
"present—whose direct knowledge is superior to the Buddha when it comes to "
"awakening.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="50"></a>
#. VAR: te → kiṃ nu (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "dn16:57.1"
msgid ""
"Kiṃ te, sāriputta, ye te ahesuṃ atītamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā, "
"sabbe te bhagavanto cetasā ceto paricca viditā:"
msgstr ""
"What about all the Perfected Ones, the fully awakened Buddhas who lived in "
"the past? Have you comprehended their minds to know that"

msgctxt "dn16:57.2"
msgid ""
"‘evaṃsīlā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, evaṃdhammā evaṃpaññā evaṃvihārī "
"evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipī’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"those Buddhas had such ethics, or such teachings, or such wisdom, or such "
"meditation, or such freedom?”"

msgctxt "dn16:57.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="51"></a>
#. VAR: pana te → kiṃ pana (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "dn16:58.1"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ pana te, sāriputta, ye te bhavissanti anāgatamaddhānaṃ arahanto "
"sammāsambuddhā, sabbe te bhagavanto cetasā ceto paricca viditā:"
msgstr ""
"“And what about all the Perfected Ones, the fully awakened Buddhas who will "
"live in the future? Have you comprehended their minds to know that"

msgctxt "dn16:58.2"
msgid ""
"‘evaṃsīlā te bhagavanto bhavissanti itipi, evaṃdhammā evaṃpaññā evaṃvihārī "
"evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto bhavissanti itipī’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"those Buddhas will have such ethics, or such teachings, or such wisdom, or "
"such meditation, or such freedom?”"

msgctxt "dn16:58.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="52"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:59.1"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ pana te, sāriputta, ahaṃ etarahi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho cetasā ceto "
"paricca vidito:"
msgstr ""
"“And what about me, the Perfected One, the fully awakened Buddha at present? "
"Have you comprehended my mind to know that"

msgctxt "dn16:59.2"
msgid ""
"‘evaṃsīlo bhagavā itipi, evaṃdhammo evaṃpañño evaṃvihārī evaṃvimutto bhagavā "
"itipī’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"I have such ethics, or such teachings, or such wisdom, or such meditation, "
"or such freedom?”"

msgctxt "dn16:59.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="53"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.83"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:60.1"
msgid ""
"“Ettha ca hi te, sāriputta, atītānāgatapaccuppannesu arahantesu "
"sammāsambuddhesu cetopariyañāṇaṃ natthi."
msgstr ""
"“Well then, Sāriputta, given that you don’t comprehend the minds of Buddhas "
"past, future, or present,"

msgctxt "dn16:60.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kiñcarahi te ayaṃ, sāriputta, uḷārā āsabhī vācā bhāsitā, ekaṃso gahito, "
"sīhanādo nadito:"
msgstr ""
"what exactly are you doing, making such an grand and dramatic statement, "
"roaring such a definitive, categorical lions roar?”"

msgctxt "dn16:60.3"
msgid "‘evaṃpasanno ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavati;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:60.4"
msgid ""
"na cāhu na ca bhavissati na cetarahi vijjati añño samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā "
"bhagavatā bhiyyobhiññataro yadidaṃ sambodhiyan’”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="54"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.17"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:61.1"
msgid ""
"“Na kho me, bhante, atītānāgatapaccuppannesu arahantesu sammāsambuddhesu "
"cetopariyañāṇaṃ atthi, api ca me dhammanvayo vidito."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, though I don’t comprehend the minds of Buddhas past, future, and "
"present, still I understand this by inference from the teaching."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:61.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, rañño paccantimaṃ nagaraṃ daḷhuddhāpaṃ "
"daḷhapākāratoraṇaṃ ekadvāraṃ, tatrassa dovāriko paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī "
"aññātānaṃ nivāretā ñātānaṃ pavesetā."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a king’s frontier citadel with fortified embankments, "
"ramparts, and arches, and a single gate. And it has a gatekeeper who is "
"astute, competent, and intelligent. He keeps strangers out and lets known "
"people in. "

msgctxt "dn16:61.3"
msgid ""
"So tassa nagarassa samantā anupariyāyapathaṃ anukkamamāno na passeyya "
"pākārasandhiṃ vā pākāravivaraṃ vā, antamaso biḷāranikkhamanamattampi."
msgstr ""
"As he walks around the patrol path, he doesn’t see a hole or cleft in the "
"wall, not even one big enough for a cat to slip out."

#. VAR: Tassa evamassa → na passeyya tassa evamassa (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn16:61.4"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "He thinks:"

msgctxt "dn16:61.5"
msgid ""
"‘ye kho keci oḷārikā pāṇā imaṃ nagaraṃ pavisanti vā nikkhamanti vā, sabbe te "
"imināva dvārena pavisanti vā nikkhamanti vā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Whatever sizable creatures enter or leave the citadel, all of them do so "
"via this gate.’"

msgctxt "dn16:61.6"
msgid "Evameva kho me, bhante, dhammanvayo vidito:"
msgstr "In the same way, I understand this by inference from the teaching:"

msgctxt "dn16:61.7"
msgid ""
"‘ye te, bhante, ahesuṃ atītamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā, sabbe te "
"bhagavanto pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe "
"catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu supatiṭṭhitacittā sattabojjhaṅge yathābhūtaṃ bhāvetvā "
"anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambujjhiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"‘All the perfected ones, fully awakened Buddhas—whether past, future, or "
"present—give up the five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken "
"wisdom. Their mind is firmly established in the four kinds of mindfulness "
"meditation. They correctly develop the seven awakening factors. And they "
"wake up to the supreme perfect awakening.’”"

msgctxt "dn16:61.8"
msgid ""
"Yepi te, bhante, bhavissanti anāgatamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā, sabbe "
"te bhagavanto pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe "
"catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu supatiṭṭhitacittā satta bojjhaṅge yathābhūtaṃ bhāvetvā "
"anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambujjhissanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:61.9"
msgid ""
"Bhagavāpi, bhante, etarahi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya "
"cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu "
"supatiṭṭhitacitto satta bojjhaṅge yathābhūtaṃ bhāvetvā anuttaraṃ "
"sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddho’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="55"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.18"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.84"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:62.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrapi sudaṃ bhagavā nāḷandāyaṃ viharanto pāvārikambavane etadeva bahulaṃ "
"bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ karoti:"
msgstr ""
"And while staying at Nāḷandā, too, the Buddha often gave this Dhamma talk to "
"the mendicants:"

msgctxt "dn16:62.2"
msgid "“iti sīlaṃ, iti samādhi, iti paññā."
msgstr "“Such is ethics, such is immersion, such is wisdom."

msgctxt "dn16:62.3"
msgid "Sīlaparibhāvito samādhi mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso."
msgstr "When immersion is imbued with ethics it’s very fruitful and beneficial."

msgctxt "dn16:62.4"
msgid "Samādhiparibhāvitā paññā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā."
msgstr "When wisdom is imbued with immersion it’s very fruitful and beneficial."

msgctxt "dn16:62.5"
msgid "Paññāparibhāvitaṃ cittaṃ sammadeva āsavehi vimuccati, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"When the mind is imbued with wisdom it is rightly freed from the "
"defilements, namely,"

msgctxt "dn16:62.6"
msgid "kāmāsavā, bhavāsavā, avijjāsavā”ti."
msgstr "the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:63.1"
msgid "5. Dussīlaādīnava"
msgstr "The Drawbacks of Unethical Conduct"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="56"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.19"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.85"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:64.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā nāḷandāyaṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ "
"āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha had stayed in Nāḷandā as long as he wished, he addressed "
"Venerable Ānanda:"

msgctxt "dn16:64.2"
msgid "“āyāmānanda, yena pāṭaligāmo tenupasaṅkamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Ānanda, let’s go to Pāṭaligāma.”"

msgctxt "dn16:64.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

msgctxt "dn16:64.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ yena pāṭaligāmo tadavasari."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants arrived at "
"Pāṭaligāma."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp1.20"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:64.5"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho pāṭaligāmikā upāsakā:"
msgstr "The lay followers of Pāṭaligāma heard"

msgctxt "dn16:64.6"
msgid "“bhagavā kira pāṭaligāmaṃ anuppatto”ti."
msgstr "that he had arrived."

msgctxt "dn16:64.7"
msgid "Atha kho pāṭaligāmikā upāsakā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr "So they went to see him,"

msgctxt "dn16:64.8"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr "bowed, sat down to one side, "

msgctxt "dn16:64.9"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho pāṭaligāmikā upāsakā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

msgctxt "dn16:64.10"
msgid "“adhivāsetu no, bhante, bhagavā āvasathāgāran”ti."
msgstr "“Sir, please consent to come to our guest house.”"

msgctxt "dn16:64.11"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena."
msgstr "The Buddha consented in silence. "

#. <a class="wp" id="wp1.21"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:64.12"
msgid ""
"Atha kho pāṭaligāmikā upāsakā bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā yena āvasathāgāraṃ "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr ""
"Then, knowing that the Buddha had accepted, the lay followers of Pāṭaligāma "
"got up from their seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping "
"him on his right. Then they went to the guest house,"

#. VAR: sabbasanthariṃ → sabba­san­tha­ri­taṃ santhataṃ (s1-3, km) |
#. sabbasanthariṃ santhataṃ (mr)
msgctxt "dn16:64.13"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā sabbasanthariṃ āvasathāgāraṃ santharitvā āsanāni paññapetvā "
"udakamaṇikaṃ patiṭṭhāpetvā telapadīpaṃ āropetvā yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu."
msgstr ""
"where they spread carpets all over, prepared seats, set up a water jar, and "
"placed a lamp. Then they went back to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side,"

msgctxt "dn16:64.14"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho pāṭaligāmikā upāsakā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "and told him of their preparations, saying:"

msgctxt "dn16:64.15"
msgid ""
"“sabbasantharisanthataṃ, bhante, āvasathāgāraṃ, āsanāni paññattāni, "
"udakamaṇiko patiṭṭhāpito, telapadīpo āropito;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:64.16"
msgid "yassadāni, bhante, bhagavā kālaṃ maññatī”ti."
msgstr "“Please, sir, come at your convenience.” "

#. <a class="wp" id="wp1.22"></a>
#. VAR: sāyanhasamayaṃ → pubbaṇ­ha­samayaṃ (km)
msgctxt "dn16:64.17"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya saddhiṃ "
"bhikkhusaṃghena yena āvasathāgāraṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha got dressed and, taking his bowl and robes, went to the "
"guest house together with the Saṅgha of mendicants."

msgctxt "dn16:64.18"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā pāde pakkhāletvā āvasathāgāraṃ pavisitvā majjhimaṃ thambhaṃ "
"nissāya puratthābhimukho nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Having washed his feet he entered the town hall and sat against the central "
"column facing east."

msgctxt "dn16:64.19"
msgid ""
"Bhikkhusaṃghopi kho pāde pakkhāletvā āvasathāgāraṃ pavisitvā pacchimaṃ "
"bhittiṃ nissāya puratthābhimukho nisīdi bhagavantameva purakkhatvā."
msgstr ""
"The Saṅgha of mendicants also washed their feet, entered the town hall, and "
"sat against the west wall facing east, with the Buddha right in front of "
"them."

msgctxt "dn16:64.20"
msgid ""
"Pāṭaligāmikāpi kho upāsakā pāde pakkhāletvā āvasathāgāraṃ pavisitvā "
"puratthimaṃ bhittiṃ nissāya pacchimābhimukhā nisīdiṃsu bhagavantameva "
"purakkhatvā."
msgstr ""
"The lay followers of Pāṭaligāma also washed their feet, entered the town "
"hall, and sat against the east wall facing west, with the Buddha right in "
"front of them."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn16:65.1"
msgid "()"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="57"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.23"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:66.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā pāṭaligāmike upāsake āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha addressed them:"

msgctxt "dn16:66.2"
msgid "“pañcime, gahapatayo, ādīnavā dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā."
msgstr ""
"“Householders, there are these five drawbacks for an unethical person "
"because of their failure in ethics."

msgctxt "dn16:66.3"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "dn16:66.4"
msgid ""
"Idha, gahapatayo, dussīlo sīlavipanno pamādādhikaraṇaṃ mahatiṃ bhogajāniṃ "
"nigacchati."
msgstr ""
"Firstly, an unethical person loses substantial wealth on account of "
"negligence."

msgctxt "dn16:66.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamo ādīnavo dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā."
msgstr ""
"This is the first drawback for an unethical person because of their failure "
"in ethics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="58"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:67.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, gahapatayo, dussīlassa sīlavipannassa pāpako kittisaddo "
"abbhuggacchati."
msgstr "Furthermore, an unethical person gets a bad reputation."

msgctxt "dn16:67.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ dutiyo ādīnavo dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā."
msgstr "This is the second drawback."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="59"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:68.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, gahapatayo, dussīlo sīlavipanno yaññadeva parisaṃ upasaṅkamati—"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, an unethical person enters any kind of assembly timid and "
"embarrassed,"

msgctxt "dn16:68.2"
msgid ""
"yadi khattiyaparisaṃ yadi brāhmaṇaparisaṃ yadi gahapatiparisaṃ yadi "
"samaṇaparisaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"whether it’s an assembly of aristocrats, brahmins, householders, or ascetics."

msgctxt "dn16:68.3"
msgid "avisārado upasaṅkamati maṅkubhūto."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:68.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ tatiyo ādīnavo dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā."
msgstr "This is the third drawback."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="60"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:69.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, gahapatayo, dussīlo sīlavipanno sammūḷho kālaṃ karoti."
msgstr "Furthermore, an unethical person dies feeling lost."

msgctxt "dn16:69.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ catuttho ādīnavo dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā."
msgstr "This is the fourth drawback."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="61"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:70.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, gahapatayo, dussīlo sīlavipanno kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, an unethical person, when their body breaks up, after death, is "
"reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "dn16:70.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ pañcamo ādīnavo dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā."
msgstr "This is the fifth drawback."

msgctxt "dn16:70.3"
msgid "Ime kho, gahapatayo, pañca ādīnavā dussīlassa sīlavipattiyā."
msgstr ""
"These are the five drawbacks for an unethical person because of their "
"failure in ethics."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:71.1"
msgid "6. Sīlavantaānisaṃsa"
msgstr "The Benefits of Ethical Conduct"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="62"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.24"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.86"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:72.1"
msgid "Pañcime, gahapatayo, ānisaṃsā sīlavato sīlasampadāya."
msgstr ""
"There are these five benefits for an ethical person because of their "
"accomplishment in ethics."

msgctxt "dn16:72.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "dn16:72.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, gahapatayo, sīlavā sīlasampanno appamādādhikaraṇaṃ mahantaṃ "
"bhogakkhandhaṃ adhigacchati."
msgstr ""
"Firstly, an ethical person gains substantial wealth on account of diligence."

msgctxt "dn16:72.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamo ānisaṃso sīlavato sīlasampadāya."
msgstr "This is the first benefit."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="63"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:73.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, gahapatayo, sīlavato sīlasampannassa kalyāṇo kittisaddo "
"abbhuggacchati."
msgstr "Furthermore, an ethical person gets a good reputation."

msgctxt "dn16:73.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ dutiyo ānisaṃso sīlavato sīlasampadāya."
msgstr "This is the second benefit."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="64"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:74.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, gahapatayo, sīlavā sīlasampanno yaññadeva parisaṃ upasaṅkamati—"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, an ethical person enters any kind of assembly bold and self-"
"assured,"

msgctxt "dn16:74.2"
msgid ""
"yadi khattiyaparisaṃ yadi brāhmaṇaparisaṃ yadi gahapatiparisaṃ yadi "
"samaṇaparisaṃ visārado upasaṅkamati amaṅkubhūto."
msgstr ""
"whether it’s an assembly of aristocrats, brahmins, householders, or ascetics."

msgctxt "dn16:74.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ tatiyo ānisaṃso sīlavato sīlasampadāya."
msgstr "This is the third benefit."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="65"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:75.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, gahapatayo, sīlavā sīlasampanno asammūḷho kālaṃ karoti."
msgstr "Furthermore, an ethical person dies not feeling lost."

msgctxt "dn16:75.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ catuttho ānisaṃso sīlavato sīlasampadāya."
msgstr "This is the fourth benefit."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="66"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:76.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, gahapatayo, sīlavā sīlasampanno kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, when an ethical person’s body breaks up, after death, they’re "
"reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm."

msgctxt "dn16:76.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ pañcamo ānisaṃso sīlavato sīlasampadāya."
msgstr "This is the fifth benefit."

msgctxt "dn16:76.3"
msgid "Ime kho, gahapatayo, pañca ānisaṃsā sīlavato sīlasampadāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"These are the five benefits for an ethical person because of their "
"accomplishment in ethics.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="67"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.25"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:77.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pāṭaligāmike upāsake bahudeva rattiṃ dhammiyā kathāya "
"sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uyyojesi:"
msgstr ""
"The Buddha spent most of the night educating, encouraging, firing up, and "
"inspiring the lay followers of Pāṭaligāma with a Dharma talk. Then he "
"dismissed them:"

msgctxt "dn16:77.2"
msgid "“abhikkantā kho, gahapatayo, ratti, yassadāni tumhe kālaṃ maññathā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The night is getting late, householders. Please go at your convenience.”"

msgctxt "dn16:77.3"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho pāṭaligāmikā upāsakā bhagavato paṭissutvā uṭṭhāyāsanā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkamiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"“Yes, sir,” replied the lay followers of Pāṭaligāma. They got up from their "
"seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on their "
"right, before leaving."

msgctxt "dn16:77.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā acirapakkantesu pāṭaligāmikesu upāsakesu suññāgāraṃ pāvisi."
msgstr "Soon after they left the Buddha entered an empty hut."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:78.1"
msgid "7. Pāṭaliputtanagaramāpana"
msgstr "Building a Citadel"

# Note nagara here, as often, means "citadel, fortress", not "city".
#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="68"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.26"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.87"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:79.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sunidhavassakārā magadhamahāmattā pāṭaligāme nagaraṃ "
"māpenti vajjīnaṃ paṭibāhāya."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the Magadhan ministers Sunidha and Vassakāra were building "
"a citadel at Pāṭaligāma to keep the Vajjians out."

#. VAR: sahasseva → sahas­sa­sahas­seva (bj udānaṭṭhakathā) | sahassasseva
#. (pts1, mr) | sahassaseva (ṭīkāyaṃ pāṭhantaraṃ)
msgctxt "dn16:79.2"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena sambahulā devatāyo sahasseva pāṭaligāme vatthūni pariggaṇhanti."
msgstr ""
"At that time thousands of deities were taking possession of building sites "
"in Pāṭaligāma."

msgctxt "dn16:79.3"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ padese mahesakkhā devatā vatthūni pariggaṇhanti, mahesakkhānaṃ tattha "
"raññaṃ rājamahāmattānaṃ cittāni namanti nivesanāni māpetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Illustrious rulers or royal ministers inclined to build houses at sites "
"possessed by illustrious deities."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp1.27"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:79.4"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ padese majjhimā devatā vatthūni pariggaṇhanti, majjhimānaṃ tattha "
"raññaṃ rājamahāmattānaṃ cittāni namanti nivesanāni māpetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Middling rulers or royal ministers inclined to build houses at sites "
"possessed by middling deities."

msgctxt "dn16:79.5"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ padese nīcā devatā vatthūni pariggaṇhanti, nīcānaṃ tattha raññaṃ "
"rājamahāmattānaṃ cittāni namanti nivesanāni māpetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Lesser rulers or royal ministers inclined to build houses at sites possessed "
"by lesser deities."

msgctxt "dn16:79.6"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho bhagavā dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena tā "
"devatāyo sahasseva pāṭaligāme vatthūni pariggaṇhantiyo."
msgstr ""
"With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, the Buddha saw those "
"deities taking possession of building sites in Pāṭaligāma."

msgctxt "dn16:79.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhāya āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ "
"āmantesi:"
msgstr "The Buddha rose at the crack of dawn and addressed Ānanda:"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="69"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.88"></a>
#. VAR: kho → ko nu kho (bj, s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
#. VAR: māpentī”ti → māpeti (si) | māpetīti (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "dn16:80.1"
msgid "“Ke nu kho, ānanda, pāṭaligāme nagaraṃ māpentī”ti?"
msgstr "“Ānanda, who is building a citadel at Pāṭaligāma?”"

msgctxt "dn16:80.2"
msgid ""
"“Sunidhavassakārā, bhante, magadhamahāmattā pāṭaligāme nagaraṃ māpenti "
"vajjīnaṃ paṭibāhāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, the Magadhan ministers Sunidha and Vassakāra are building a citadel to "
"keep the Vajjians out.”"

#. <a class="wp" id="wp1.28"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:80.3"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, ānanda, devehi tāvatiṃsehi saddhiṃ mantetvā;"
msgstr ""
"“It’s as if they were building the citadel in consultation with the gods of "
"the Thirty-three."

msgctxt "dn16:80.4"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, ānanda, sunidhavassakārā magadhamahāmattā pāṭaligāme nagaraṃ "
"māpenti vajjīnaṃ paṭibāhāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:80.5"
msgid ""
"Idhāhaṃ, ānanda, addasaṃ dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena "
"sambahulā devatāyo sahasseva pāṭaligāme vatthūni pariggaṇhantiyo."
msgstr ""
"With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, I saw those deities "
"taking possession of building sites."

msgctxt "dn16:80.6"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, ānanda, padese mahesakkhā devatā vatthūni pariggaṇhanti, "
"mahesakkhānaṃ tattha raññaṃ rājamahāmattānaṃ cittāni namanti nivesanāni "
"māpetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Illustrious rulers or royal ministers inclined to build houses at sites "
"possessed by illustrious deities."

msgctxt "dn16:80.7"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ padese majjhimā devatā vatthūni pariggaṇhanti, majjhimānaṃ tattha "
"raññaṃ rājamahāmattānaṃ cittāni namanti nivesanāni māpetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Middling rulers or royal ministers inclined to build houses at sites "
"possessed by middling deities."

msgctxt "dn16:80.8"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ padese nīcā devatā vatthūni pariggaṇhanti, nīcānaṃ tattha raññaṃ "
"rājamahāmattānaṃ cittāni namanti nivesanāni māpetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Lesser rulers or royal ministers inclined to build houses at sites possessed "
"by lesser deities."

# Comm. is surely correct here: putabhedana refers to the breaking of packages, i.e. a trade center.
msgctxt "dn16:80.9"
msgid ""
"Yāvatā, ānanda, ariyaṃ āyatanaṃ yāvatā vaṇippatho idaṃ agganagaraṃ "
"bhavissati pāṭaliputtaṃ puṭabhedanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"As far as the civilized region extends, as far as the trading zone extends, "
"this will be the chief city: the Pāṭaliputta trade center."

msgctxt "dn16:80.10"
msgid "Pāṭaliputtassa kho, ānanda, tayo antarāyā bhavissanti—"
msgstr "But Pāṭaliputta will face three threats:"

msgctxt "dn16:80.11"
msgid "aggito vā udakato vā mithubhedā vā”ti."
msgstr "from fire, flood, and dissension.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="70"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.29"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:81.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sunidhavassakārā magadhamahāmattā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr ""
"Then the Magadhan ministers Sunidha and Vassakāra approached the Buddha,"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:81.2"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ "
"vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu, ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho sunidhavassakārā "
"magadhamahāmattā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"and exchanged greetings with him. When the greetings and polite conversation "
"were over, they stood to one side and said:"

msgctxt "dn16:81.3"
msgid ""
"“adhivāsetu no bhavaṃ gotamo ajjatanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghenā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Would Master Gotama together with the mendicant Saṅgha please accept today’"
"s meal from me?”"

msgctxt "dn16:81.4"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena."
msgstr "The Buddha consented in silence. "

#. <a class="wp" id="wp1.30"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:81.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sunidhavassakārā magadhamahāmattā bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā "
"yena sako āvasatho tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr ""
"Then, knowing that the Buddha had accepted, they went to their own guest "
"house,"

msgctxt "dn16:81.6"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā sake āvasathe paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā "
"bhagavato kālaṃ ārocāpesuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"where they had a variety of delicious foods prepared. Then they had the "
"Buddha informed of the time, saying:"

msgctxt "dn16:81.7"
msgid "“kālo, bho gotama, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti."
msgstr "“Itʼs time, Master Gotama, the meal is ready.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="71"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:82.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya saddhiṃ "
"bhikkhusaṅghena yena sunidhavassakārānaṃ magadhamahāmattānaṃ āvasatho "
"tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha got dressed in the morning and, taking his bowl and robes, "
"went to their guest house,"

msgctxt "dn16:82.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "where he sat on the seat spread out. "

msgctxt "dn16:82.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sunidhavassakārā magadhamahāmattā buddhappamukhaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ "
"paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappesuṃ sampavāresuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then Sunidha and Vassakāra served and satisfied the mendicant Saṅgha headed "
"by the Buddha with their own hands with a variety of delicious foods."

msgctxt "dn16:82.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sunidhavassakārā magadhamahāmattā bhagavantaṃ bhuttāviṃ "
"onītapattapāṇiṃ aññataraṃ nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha had eaten and washed his hand and bowl, Sunidha and "
"Vassakāra took a low seat and sat to one side."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp1.31"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:82.5"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho sunidhavassakāre magadhamahāmatte bhagavā imāhi "
"gāthāhi anumodi:"
msgstr "The Buddha expressed his appreciation with these verses:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="72"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:83.1"
msgid "“Yasmiṃ padese kappeti,"
msgstr "“In the place he makes his dwelling, "

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:83.2"
msgid "vāsaṃ paṇḍitajātiyo;"
msgstr "having fed the astute"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:83.3"
msgid "Sīlavantettha bhojetvā,"
msgstr "and the virtuous here, "

#. <br>
#. VAR: brahmacārayo → brahmacārino (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn16:83.4"
msgid "saññate brahmacārayo."
msgstr "the restrained spiritual practitioners,"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="73"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:84.1"
msgid "Yā tattha devatā āsuṃ,"
msgstr "he should dedicate an offering"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:84.2"
msgid "tāsaṃ dakkhiṇamādise;"
msgstr "to the deities there."

#. <br>
#. VAR: pūjitā pūjayanti → pūjitā pūjayanti naṃ (mr)
msgctxt "dn16:84.3"
msgid "Tā pūjitā pūjayanti,"
msgstr "Venerated, they venerate him;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:84.4"
msgid "mānitā mānayanti naṃ."
msgstr "honored, they honor him."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="74"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.89"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:85.1"
msgid "Tato naṃ anukampanti,"
msgstr "After that they have compassion for him,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:85.2"
msgid "mātā puttaṃva orasaṃ;"
msgstr "like a mother for the child at her breast."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:85.3"
msgid "Devatānukampito poso,"
msgstr "A man beloved of the deities"

# I think it's unlikely bhadrani means 'auspcious". Most commonly it's used to describe chariots. And the similar line at AN 4.67 is applied to animals.
#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:85.4"
msgid "sadā bhadrāni passatī”ti."
msgstr "always sees nice things.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="75"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:86.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā sunidhavassakāre magadhamahāmatte imāhi gāthāhi anumoditvā "
"uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha had expressed his appreciation to Sunidha and Vassakāra with "
"these verses, he got up from his seat and left."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="76"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.32"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:87.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sunidhavassakārā magadhamahāmattā bhagavantaṃ "
"piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhā honti:"
msgstr "Sunidha and Vassakāra followed behind the Buddha, thinking:"

msgctxt "dn16:87.2"
msgid ""
"“yenajja samaṇo gotamo dvārena nikkhamissati, taṃ gotamadvāraṃ nāma "
"bhavissati."
msgstr ""
"“The gate through which the ascetic Gotama departs today shall be named the "
"Gotama Gate."

msgctxt "dn16:87.3"
msgid ""
"Yena titthena gaṅgaṃ nadiṃ tarissati, taṃ gotamatitthaṃ nāma bhavissatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"The ford at which he crosses the Ganges River shall be named the Gotama "
"Ford.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="77"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:88.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā yena dvārena nikkhami, taṃ gotamadvāraṃ nāma ahosi."
msgstr ""
"Then the gate through which the Buddha departed was named the Gotama Gate."

msgctxt "dn16:88.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā yena gaṅgā nadī tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr "Then the Buddha came to the Ganges River."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp1.33"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:88.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena gaṅgā nadī pūrā hoti samatittikā kākapeyyā."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the Ganges was full to the brim so a crow could drink from "
"it."

# Dinghy is a Hindi word : "any of various rowing or sailing boats used in sheltered waters along the Indian coasts to transport passengers and freight."
#. VAR: apārā → orā (bj ^pi-tv-kd6#100 [Bhesaj­jak­khan­dhaka/
#. Sunidha­vassakā­ravat­thu]) | pārā (si, s1-3, km, mr) | aparā (pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:88.4"
msgid ""
"Appekacce manussā nāvaṃ pariyesanti, appekacce uḷumpaṃ pariyesanti, "
"appekacce kullaṃ bandhanti apārā, pāraṃ gantukāmā."
msgstr ""
"Wanting to cross from the near to the far shore, some people were seeking a "
"boat, some a dinghy, while some were tying up a raft."

msgctxt "dn16:88.5"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:88.6"
msgid ""
"seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā "
"bāhaṃ samiñjeyya;"
msgstr "Then, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm,"

msgctxt "dn16:88.7"
msgid "evameva—"
msgstr ""

# Note the use of paccuṭṭhāsi rather than pāturahosi here.
msgctxt "dn16:88.8"
msgid ""
"gaṅgāya nadiyā orimatīre antarahito pārimatīre paccuṭṭhāsi saddhiṃ "
"bhikkhusaṃghena."
msgstr ""
"the Buddha, together with the mendicant Saṅgha, vanished from the near shore "
"and landed on the far shore."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="78"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1.34"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:89.1"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho bhagavā te manusse appekacce nāvaṃ pariyesante appekacce uḷumpaṃ "
"pariyesante appekacce kullaṃ bandhante apārā pāraṃ gantukāme."
msgstr "He saw all those people wanting to cross over."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="79"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:90.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etamatthaṃ viditvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ udānaṃ udānesi:"
msgstr ""
"Then, knowing the meaning of this, on that occasion the Buddha spoke these "
"words of inspiration:"

# annava can hardly mean "sea" here, if it is to be crossed with a bridge.
#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="80"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:91.1"
msgid "“Ye taranti aṇṇavaṃ saraṃ,"
msgstr "“Some cross a river or stream"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:91.2"
msgid "Setuṃ katvāna visajja pallalāni;"
msgstr "having built a bridge or drained the swamps."

#. <br>
#. VAR: Kullañhi jano bandhati → kullaṃ hi jano pabandhati (bj, pts1, mr) |
#. kullaṃ jano ca bandhati (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn16:91.3"
msgid "Kullañhi jano bandhati,"
msgstr "While one man is still tying a raft,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Tiṇṇā → na tiṇṇā (mr)
msgctxt "dn16:91.4"
msgid "Tiṇṇā medhāvino janā”ti."
msgstr "intelligent people have already crossed over.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn16:92.1"
msgid "Paṭhamabhāṇavāro."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:93.1"
msgid "8. Ariyasaccakathā"
msgstr "Talk on the Noble Truths"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="81"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.1"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.90"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:94.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to Venerable Ānanda:"

msgctxt "dn16:94.2"
msgid "“āyāmānanda, yena koṭigāmo tenupasaṅkamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Ānanda, let’s go to Koṭigāma.”"

msgctxt "dn16:94.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

msgctxt "dn16:94.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ yena koṭigāmo tadavasari."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants arrived at "
"Koṭigāma,"

msgctxt "dn16:94.5"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā koṭigāme viharati."
msgstr "and stayed on there."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp2.2"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:94.6"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There he addressed the mendicants: "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="82"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:95.1"
msgid ""
"“Catunnaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasaccānaṃ ananubodhā appaṭivedhā evamidaṃ "
"dīghamaddhānaṃ sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva tumhākañca."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, not understanding and not penetrating four noble truths, both "
"you and I have wandered and transmigrated for such a very long time."

msgctxt "dn16:95.2"
msgid "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "dn16:95.3"
msgid ""
"Dukkhassa, bhikkhave, ariyasaccassa ananubodhā appaṭivedhā evamidaṃ "
"dīghamaddhānaṃ sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva tumhākañca."
msgstr "The noble truths of suffering,"

msgctxt "dn16:95.4"
msgid ""
"Dukkhasamudayassa, bhikkhave, ariyasaccassa ananubodhā appaṭivedhā evamidaṃ "
"dīghamaddhānaṃ sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva tumhākañca."
msgstr "the origin of suffering,"

msgctxt "dn16:95.5"
msgid ""
"Dukkhanirodhassa, bhikkhave, ariyasaccassa ananubodhā appaṭivedhā evamidaṃ "
"dīghamaddhānaṃ sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva tumhākañca."
msgstr "the cessation of suffering,"

msgctxt "dn16:95.6"
msgid ""
"Dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya, bhikkhave, ariyasaccassa ananubodhā "
"appaṭivedhā evamidaṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva "
"tumhākañca."
msgstr "and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering."

#. VAR: dukkhanirodhaṃ → dukkhanirodho (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "dn16:95.7"
msgid ""
"Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ anubuddhaṃ paṭividdhaṃ, "
"dukkhasamudayaṃ ariyasaccaṃ anubuddhaṃ paṭividdhaṃ, dukkhanirodhaṃ "
"ariyasaccaṃ anubuddhaṃ paṭividdhaṃ, dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā ariyasaccaṃ "
"anubuddhaṃ paṭividdhaṃ, ucchinnā bhavataṇhā, khīṇā bhavanetti, natthi dāni "
"punabbhavo”ti."
msgstr ""
"These noble truths of suffering, origin, cessation, and the path have been "
"understood and penetrated. Craving to be reborn has been cut off; the "
"attachment to being reborn is ended; now there are no more future lives.” "

#. <a class="wp" id="wp2.3"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:95.8"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "This is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "dn16:95.9"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="83"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.91"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:96.1"
msgid "“Catunnaṃ ariyasaccānaṃ,"
msgstr "“Because of not truly seeing"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:96.2"
msgid "yathābhūtaṃ adassanā;"
msgstr "the four noble truths,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:96.3"
msgid "Saṃsitaṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ,"
msgstr "we have transmigrated for a long time"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:96.4"
msgid "tāsu tāsveva jātisu."
msgstr "from one rebirth to the next."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="84"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:97.1"
msgid "Tāni etāni diṭṭhāni,"
msgstr "But now that these truths have been seen,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:97.2"
msgid "bhavanetti samūhatā;"
msgstr "the attachment to being reborn is undone."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:97.3"
msgid "Ucchinnaṃ mūlaṃ dukkhassa,"
msgstr "The root of suffering is cut off,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:97.4"
msgid "natthi dāni punabbhavo”ti."
msgstr "now there are no more future lives.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="85"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.4"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:98.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrapi sudaṃ bhagavā koṭigāme viharanto etadeva bahulaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiṃ "
"kathaṃ karoti:"
msgstr ""
"And while staying at Koṭigāma, too, the Buddha often gave this Dhamma talk "
"to the mendicants:"

msgctxt "dn16:98.2"
msgid "“iti sīlaṃ, iti samādhi, iti paññā."
msgstr "“Such is ethics, such is immersion, such is wisdom."

msgctxt "dn16:98.3"
msgid "Sīlaparibhāvito samādhi mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso."
msgstr "When immersion is imbued with ethics it’s very fruitful and beneficial."

msgctxt "dn16:98.4"
msgid "Samādhiparibhāvitā paññā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā."
msgstr "When wisdom is imbued with immersion it’s very fruitful and beneficial."

msgctxt "dn16:98.5"
msgid "Paññāparibhāvitaṃ cittaṃ sammadeva āsavehi vimuccati, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"When the mind is imbued with wisdom it is rightly freed from the "
"defilements, namely,"

msgctxt "dn16:98.6"
msgid "kāmāsavā, bhavāsavā, avijjāsavā”ti."
msgstr "the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:99.1"
msgid "9. Anāvattidhammasambodhiparāyaṇa"
msgstr "The Deaths in Nādika"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="86"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.5"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.92"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:100.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā koṭigāme yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ "
"āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha had stayed in Koṭigāma as long as he wished, he said to "
"Ānanda:"

# The plural is used here, so strictly speaking "(the land of the) Nadikas".
#. VAR: nātikā → nādikā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:100.2"
msgid "“āyāmānanda, yena nātikā tenupaṅkamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Ānanda, let’s go to Nādika.”"

msgctxt "dn16:100.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

msgctxt "dn16:100.4"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ yena nātikā tadavasari."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants arrived at Nādika,"

msgctxt "dn16:100.5"
msgid "Tatrapi sudaṃ bhagavā nātike viharati giñjakāvasathe."
msgstr "where he stayed in the brick house."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp2.6"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:100.6"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha,  "

msgctxt "dn16:100.7"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed, sat down to one side, "

msgctxt "dn16:100.8"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

msgctxt "dn16:100.9"
msgid ""
"“sāḷho nāma, bhante, bhikkhu nātike kālaṅkato, tassa kā gati, ko "
"abhisamparāyo?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, the monk named Sāḷha has passed away in Nādika. Where has he been "
"reborn in his next life?"

msgctxt "dn16:100.10"
msgid ""
"Nandā nāma, bhante, bhikkhunī nātike kālaṅkatā, tassā kā gati, ko "
"abhisamparāyo?"
msgstr "The nun named Nandā,"

msgctxt "dn16:100.11"
msgid ""
"Sudatto nāma, bhante, upāsako nātike kālaṅkato, tassa kā gati, ko "
"abhisamparāyo?"
msgstr "the layman named Sudatta,"

msgctxt "dn16:100.12"
msgid ""
"Sujātā nāma, bhante, upāsikā nātike kālaṅkatā, tassā kā gati, ko "
"abhisamparāyo?"
msgstr ""
"and the laywoman named Sujātā have passed away in Nādika. Where have they "
"been reborn in the next life?"

# I spell the names the same as at SN 55.10.
#. VAR: Kukkuṭo → kakudho (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:100.13"
msgid ""
"Kukkuṭo nāma, bhante, upāsako nātike kālaṅkato, tassa kā gati, ko "
"abhisamparāyo?"
msgstr "The laymen named Kakkaṭa,"

#. VAR: Kāḷimbo → kālimbo (bj) | kāraḷimbho (s1-3, km) | kāliṅgo (pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:100.14"
msgid "Kāḷimbo nāma, bhante, upāsako …"
msgstr "Kaḷibha,"

msgctxt "dn16:100.15"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:100.16"
msgid "nikaṭo nāma, bhante, upāsako …"
msgstr "Nikata,"

#. VAR: kaṭissaho → kaṭissabho (pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:100.17"
msgid "kaṭissaho nāma, bhante, upāsako …"
msgstr "Kaṭissaha,"

msgctxt "dn16:100.18"
msgid "tuṭṭho nāma, bhante, upāsako …"
msgstr "Tuṭṭha,"

msgctxt "dn16:100.19"
msgid "santuṭṭho nāma, bhante, upāsako …"
msgstr "Santuṭṭha,"

#. VAR: bhaddo → bhaṭo (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn16:100.20"
msgid "bhaddo nāma, bhante, upāsako …"
msgstr "Bhadda, and"

#. VAR: subhaddo → subhaṭo (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn16:100.21"
msgid ""
"subhaddo nāma, bhante, upāsako nātike kālaṅkato, tassa kā gati, ko "
"abhisamparāyo”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Subhadda have passed away in Nādika. Where have they been reborn in the next "
"life?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="87"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.7"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.93"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:101.1"
msgid ""
"“Sāḷho, ānanda, bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ "
"diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi."
msgstr ""
"“Ānanda, the monk Sāḷha had realized the undefiled freedom of heart and "
"freedom by wisdom in this very life, having achieved it with his own insight "
"due to the end of defilements."

msgctxt "dn16:101.2"
msgid ""
"Nandā, ānanda, bhikkhunī pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā "
"opapātikā tattha parinibbāyinī anāvattidhammā tasmā lokā."
msgstr ""
"The nun Nandā had ended the five lower fetters. She’s been reborn "
"spontaneously, and will be extinguished there, not liable to return from "
"that world."

msgctxt "dn16:101.3"
msgid ""
"Sudatto, ānanda, upāsako tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ "
"tanuttā sakadāgāmī sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karissati."
msgstr ""
"The layman Sudatta had ended three fetters, and weakened greed, hate, and "
"delusion. He’s a once-returner; he will come back to this world once only, "
"then make an end of suffering."

msgctxt "dn16:101.4"
msgid ""
"Sujātā, ānanda, upāsikā tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sotāpannā "
"avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā."
msgstr ""
"The laywoman Sujātā had ended three fetters. She’s a stream-enterer, not "
"liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening."

msgctxt "dn16:101.5"
msgid ""
"Kukkuṭo, ānanda, upāsako pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā "
"opapātiko tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā."
msgstr "The laymen Kakkaṭa,"

msgctxt "dn16:101.6"
msgid "Kāḷimbo, ānanda, upāsako …"
msgstr "Kaḷibha,"

msgctxt "dn16:101.7"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:101.8"
msgid "nikaṭo, ānanda, upāsako …"
msgstr "Nikata,"

msgctxt "dn16:101.9"
msgid "kaṭissaho, ānanda, upāsako …"
msgstr "Kaṭissaha,"

msgctxt "dn16:101.10"
msgid "tuṭṭho, ānanda, upāsako …"
msgstr "Tuṭṭha,"

msgctxt "dn16:101.11"
msgid "santuṭṭho, ānanda, upāsako …"
msgstr "Santuṭṭha,"

msgctxt "dn16:101.12"
msgid "bhaddo, ānanda, upāsako …"
msgstr "Bhadda, and"

msgctxt "dn16:101.13"
msgid ""
"subhaddo, ānanda, upāsako pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā "
"opapātiko tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā."
msgstr ""
"and Subhadda had ended the five lower fetters. They’ve been reborn "
"spontaneously, and will be extinguished there, not liable to return from "
"that world."

msgctxt "dn16:101.14"
msgid ""
"Paropaññāsaṃ, ānanda, nātike upāsakā kālaṅkatā, pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ "
"saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātikā tattha parinibbāyino anāvattidhammā tasmā "
"lokā."
msgstr ""
"Over fifty laymen in Nādika have passed away having ended the five lower "
"fetters. They’ve been reborn spontaneously, and will be extinguished there, "
"not liable to return from that world."

#. VAR: Sādhikā navuti → chādhikā navuti (s1-3) | nādhikā navuti (km)
msgctxt "dn16:101.15"
msgid ""
"Sādhikā navuti, ānanda, nātike upāsakā kālaṅkatā tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ "
"parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā sakadāgāmino sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā "
"dukkhassantaṃ karissanti."
msgstr ""
"More than ninety laymen in Nādika have passed away having ended three "
"fetters, and weakened greed, hate, and delusion. They’re once-returners, who "
"will come back to this world once only, then make an end of suffering."

#. VAR: Sātirekāni → dasātirekāni (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn16:101.16"
msgid ""
"Sātirekāni, ānanda, pañcasatāni nātike upāsakā kālaṅkatā, tiṇṇaṃ "
"saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā."
msgstr ""
"In excess of five hundred laymen in Nādika have passed away having ended "
"three fetters. They’re stream-enterers, not liable to be reborn in the "
"underworld, bound for awakening."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:102.1"
msgid "10. Dhammādāsadhammapariyāya"
msgstr "The Mirror of the Teaching"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="88"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.8"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:103.1"
msgid "Anacchariyaṃ kho panetaṃ, ānanda, yaṃ manussabhūto kālaṃ kareyya."
msgstr "It’s hardly surprising that a human being should pass away. "

#. VAR: Tasmiṃyeva → tasmiṃ tasmiṃ kho (s1-3, km) | tasmiṃ tasmiṃ ce (pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:103.2"
msgid ""
"Tasmiṃyeva kālaṅkate tathāgataṃ upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ pucchissatha, "
"vihesā hesā, ānanda, tathāgatassa."
msgstr ""
"But if you should come and ask me about it each and every time someone "
"passes away, that would be a bother for me."

msgctxt "dn16:103.3"
msgid ""
"Tasmātihānanda, dhammādāsaṃ nāma dhammapariyāyaṃ desessāmi, yena samannāgato "
"ariyasāvako ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ byākareyya:"
msgstr ""
"So Ānanda, I will teach you the explanation of the Dhamma called ‘the mirror "
"of the teaching’. A noble disciple who has this may declare of themselves: "

msgctxt "dn16:103.4"
msgid ""
"‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo "
"khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto, sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato "
"sambodhiparāyaṇo’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I’ve finished with rebirth in hell, the animal realm, and the ghost realm. "
"I’ve finished with all places of loss, bad places, the underworld. I am a "
"stream enterer! I’m not liable to be reborn in the underworld, and am bound "
"for awakening.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="89"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.9"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:104.1"
msgid ""
"Katamo ca so, ānanda, dhammādāso dhammapariyāyo, yena samannāgato "
"ariyasāvako ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ byākareyya:"
msgstr "And what is that mirror of the teaching? "

msgctxt "dn16:104.2"
msgid ""
"‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo "
"khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto, sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato "
"sambodhiparāyaṇo’ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="90"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:105.1"
msgid "Idhānanda, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti:"
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn16:105.2"
msgid ""
"‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū "
"anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘That Blessed One is perfect, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in "
"knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme trainer of people, "
"teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="91"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:106.1"
msgid "Dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti:"
msgstr "They have experiential confidence in the teaching: "

msgctxt "dn16:106.2"
msgid ""
"‘svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo sandiṭṭhiko akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko "
"paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The teaching is well explained by the Buddha—realizable in this very life, "
"immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible "
"people can know it for themselves.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="92"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.94"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:107.1"
msgid "Saṅghe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti:"
msgstr "They have experiential confidence in the Saṅgha:"

msgctxt "dn16:107.2"
msgid ""
"‘suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, ujuppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, "
"ñāyappaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, sāmīcippaṭipanno bhagavato "
"sāvakasaṅgho yadidaṃ cattāri purisayugāni aṭṭha purisapuggalā, esa bhagavato "
"sāvakasaṅgho āhuneyyo pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ "
"puññakkhettaṃ lokassā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is practicing the way that’s good, "
"direct, principled, and proper. It consists of the four pairs, the eight "
"individuals. This Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is worthy of offerings "
"dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a teacher’s "
"offering, and worthy of greeting with folded palms. It is a supreme field of "
"merit for the world.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="93"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:108.1"
msgid ""
"Ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi acchiddehi asabalehi "
"akammāsehi bhujissehi viññūpasatthehi aparāmaṭṭhehi samādhisaṃvattanikehi."
msgstr ""
"And a noble disciple’s ethical conduct is loved by the noble ones, "
"uncorrupted, unflawed, unblemished, untainted, liberating, praised by "
"sensible people, not mistaken, and leading to immersion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="94"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:109.1"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho so, ānanda, dhammādāso dhammapariyāyo, yena samannāgato ariyasāvako "
"ākaṅkhamāno attanāva attānaṃ byākareyya:"
msgstr "This is that mirror of the teaching. "

msgctxt "dn16:109.2"
msgid ""
"‘khīṇanirayomhi khīṇatiracchānayoni khīṇapettivisayo "
"khīṇāpāyaduggativinipāto, sotāpannohamasmi avinipātadhammo niyato "
"sambodhiparāyaṇo’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="95"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.10"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:110.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrapi sudaṃ bhagavā nātike viharanto giñjakāvasathe etadeva bahulaṃ "
"bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ karoti:"
msgstr ""
"And while staying there in Nādika the Buddha often gave this Dhamma talk to "
"the mendicants:"

msgctxt "dn16:110.2"
msgid "“Iti sīlaṃ iti samādhi iti paññā."
msgstr "“Such is ethics, such is immersion, such is wisdom."

msgctxt "dn16:110.3"
msgid "Sīlaparibhāvito samādhi mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso."
msgstr "When immersion is imbued with ethics it’s very fruitful and beneficial."

msgctxt "dn16:110.4"
msgid "Samādhiparibhāvitā paññā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā."
msgstr "When wisdom is imbued with immersion it’s very fruitful and beneficial."

msgctxt "dn16:110.5"
msgid "Paññāparibhāvitaṃ cittaṃ sammadeva āsavehi vimuccati, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"When the mind is imbued with wisdom it is rightly freed from the "
"defilements, namely,"

msgctxt "dn16:110.6"
msgid "kāmāsavā, bhavāsavā, avijjāsavā”ti."
msgstr "the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn16:111.1"
msgid "()"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="96"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.11"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:112.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā nātike yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha had stayed in Nādika as long as he wished, he addressed "
"Venerable Ānanda:"

msgctxt "dn16:112.2"
msgid "“āyāmānanda, yena vesālī tenupasaṅkamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Ānanda, let’s go to Vesālī.”"

msgctxt "dn16:112.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

msgctxt "dn16:112.4"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ yena vesālī tadavasari."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants arrived at Vesālī,"

msgctxt "dn16:112.5"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati ambapālivane."
msgstr "where he stayed in Ambapālī’s mango grove."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp2.12"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:112.6"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants: "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="97"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.95"></a>
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:113.1"
msgid ""
"“Sato, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vihareyya sampajāno, ayaṃ vo amhākaṃ anusāsanī."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a mendicant should live mindful and aware. This is my "
"instruction to you. "

msgctxt "dn16:113.2"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sato hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant mindful? "

msgctxt "dn16:113.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā "
"vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body, keen, "
"aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "dn16:113.4"
msgid "Vedanāsu vedanānupassī …"
msgstr "They meditate by observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "dn16:113.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:113.6"
msgid "citte cittānupassī …"
msgstr "mind …"

msgctxt "dn16:113.7"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:113.8"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"principles, keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the "
"world. "

msgctxt "dn16:113.9"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sato hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is mindful. "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="98"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.13"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:114.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sampajāno hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant aware? "

msgctxt "dn16:114.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu abhikkante paṭikkante sampajānakārī hoti, ālokite "
"vilokite sampajānakārī hoti, samiñjite pasārite sampajānakārī hoti, "
"saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇe sampajānakārī hoti, asite pīte khāyite sāyite "
"sampajānakārī hoti, uccārapassāvakamme sampajānakārī hoti, gate ṭhite "
"nisinne sutte jāgarite bhāsite tuṇhībhāve sampajānakārī hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant acts with situational awareness when going out and "
"coming back; when looking ahead and aside; when bending and extending the "
"limbs; when bearing the outer robe, bowl and robes; when eating, drinking, "
"chewing, and tasting; when urinating and defecating; when walking, standing, "
"sitting, sleeping, waking, speaking, and keeping silent."

msgctxt "dn16:114.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sampajāno hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is aware. "

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:114.4"
msgid ""
"Sato, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vihareyya sampajāno, ayaṃ vo amhākaṃ anusāsanī”ti."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant should live mindful and aware. This is my instruction to you.”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:115.1"
msgid "11. Ambapālīgaṇikā"
msgstr "Ambapālī the Courtesan"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="99"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.14"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:116.1"
msgid "Assosi kho ambapālī gaṇikā:"
msgstr "Ambapālī the courtesan heard that"

msgctxt "dn16:116.2"
msgid "“bhagavā kira vesāliṃ anuppatto vesāliyaṃ viharati mayhaṃ ambavane”ti."
msgstr "the Buddha had arrived and was staying in her mango grove."

msgctxt "dn16:116.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho ambapālī gaṇikā bhaddāni bhaddāni yānāni yojāpetvā bhaddaṃ bhaddaṃ "
"yānaṃ abhiruhitvā bhaddehi bhaddehi yānehi vesāliyā niyyāsi."
msgstr ""
"She had the finest carriages harnessed. Then she mounted a fine carriage "
"and, along with other fine carriages, set out from Vesālī for her own park."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:116.4"
msgid "Yena sako ārāmo tena pāyāsi."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn16:116.5"
msgid ""
"Yāvatikā yānassa bhūmi, yānena gantvā, yānā paccorohitvā pattikāva yena "
"bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"She went by carriage as far as the terrain allowed, then descended and "
"entered the monastery on foot. "

msgctxt "dn16:116.6"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "She bowed and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "dn16:116.7"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho ambapāliṃ gaṇikaṃ bhagavā dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi "
"samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi."
msgstr ""
"The Buddha educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired her with a Dharma "
"talk."

msgctxt "dn16:116.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho ambapālī gaṇikā bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā "
"samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then she said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn16:116.9"
msgid ""
"“adhivāsetu me, bhante, bhagavā svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghenā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, may the Buddha together with the mendicant Saṅgha please accept "
"tomorrow’s meal from me.”"

msgctxt "dn16:116.10"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena."
msgstr "The Buddha consented in silence. "

msgctxt "dn16:116.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho ambapālī gaṇikā bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"Then, knowing that the Buddha had accepted, Ambapālī got up from her seat, "
"bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before "
"leaving."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="100"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.15"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.96"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:117.1"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho vesālikā licchavī:"
msgstr "The Licchavis of Vesālī also heard that"

msgctxt "dn16:117.2"
msgid "“bhagavā kira vesāliṃ anuppatto vesāliyaṃ viharati ambapālivane”ti."
msgstr "the Buddha had arrived and was staying in Ambapālī’s mango grove."

msgctxt "dn16:117.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te licchavī bhaddāni bhaddāni yānāni yojāpetvā bhaddaṃ bhaddaṃ "
"yānaṃ abhiruhitvā bhaddehi bhaddehi yānehi vesāliyā niyyiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"They had the finest carriages harnessed. Then they mounted a fine carriage "
"and, along with other fine carriages, set out from Vesālī."

msgctxt "dn16:117.4"
msgid ""
"Tatra ekacce licchavī nīlā honti nīlavaṇṇā nīlavatthā nīlālaṅkārā, ekacce "
"licchavī pītā honti pītavaṇṇā pītavatthā pītālaṅkārā, ekacce licchavī lohitā "
"honti lohitavaṇṇā lohitavatthā lohitālaṅkārā, ekacce licchavī odātā honti "
"odātavaṇṇā odātavatthā odātālaṅkārā."
msgstr ""
"Some of the Licchavis were in blue, of blue color, clad in blue, adorned "
"with blue. And some were similarly colored in yellow, red, or white."

# There are various reading for pativattesi. I quite like that reading "forced the back". Anandajoti has "rolled alongside" evidently reading parivattesi. Comm, however, has "Parivaṭṭesīti pahari".
#. <a class="wp" id="wp2.16"></a>
#. VAR: paṭivaṭṭesi → parivattesi (^pi-tv-kd6#116 [Bhesaj­jak­khan­dhaka/
#. Licchavīvatthu])
msgctxt "dn16:117.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho ambapālī gaṇikā daharānaṃ daharānaṃ licchavīnaṃ akkhena akkhaṃ "
"cakkena cakkaṃ yugena yugaṃ paṭivaṭṭesi."
msgstr ""
"Then Ambapālī the courtesan collided with those Licchavi youths, axle to "
"axle, wheel to wheel, yoke to yoke."

msgctxt "dn16:117.6"
msgid "Atha kho te licchavī ambapāliṃ gaṇikaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "The Licchavis said to her:"

# I don't know if it's possible to be very literal, but i thgink it's important to preserve something of the flavor of the insulting vocative je here, otherwise used of the "bad girl" Kali in MN 21.
msgctxt "dn16:117.7"
msgid ""
"“kiṃ, je ambapāli, daharānaṃ daharānaṃ licchavīnaṃ akkhena akkhaṃ cakkena "
"cakkaṃ yugena yugaṃ paṭivaṭṭesī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“What the hell, Ambapālī, are you doing colliding with us axle to axle, "
"wheel to wheel, yoke to yoke?”"

msgctxt "dn16:117.8"
msgid ""
"“Tathā hi pana me, ayyaputtā, bhagavā nimantito svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ "
"bhikkhusaṃghenā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Well, my lords, it’s because I’ve invited the Buddha for tomorrow’s meal "
"together with the mendicant Saṅgha.” "

#. VAR: etaṃ → ekaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "dn16:117.9"
msgid "“Dehi, je ambapāli, etaṃ bhattaṃ satasahassenā”ti."
msgstr "“Girl, give us that meal for a hundred thousand!”"

#. VAR: evamahaṃ taṃ → evaṃ mahantaṃ (bj, pts1) | evaṃpi mahantaṃ (s1-3, km)
#. VAR: bhattaṃ na dassāmī”ti → neva dajjāhaṃ taṃ bhattanti (^pi-tv-kd6#116
#. [Bhesaj­jak­khan­dhaka/ Licchavīvatthu])
#. VAR: dassatha → dajjeyyātha (^pi-tv-kd6#116 [Bhesaj­jak­khan­dhaka/
#. Licchavīvatthu])
msgctxt "dn16:117.10"
msgid ""
"“Sacepi me, ayyaputtā, vesāliṃ sāhāraṃ dassatha, evamahaṃ taṃ bhattaṃ na "
"dassāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“My lords, even if you were to give me Vesālī with her fiefdoms, I still "
"wouldn’t give that meal to you.”"

msgctxt "dn16:117.11"
msgid "Atha kho te licchavī aṅguliṃ phoṭesuṃ:"
msgstr "Then the Licchavis snapped their fingers, saying:"

#. VAR: jitamha → jitamhā (bahūsu)
#. VAR: vata bho ambakāya, jitamha vata bho ambakāyā”ti → \
msgctxt "dn16:117.12"
msgid "“jitamha vata bho ambakāya, jitamha vata bho ambakāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“We’ve been beaten by the mango-matron! We’ve been beaten by the mango-"
"matron!”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="101"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.97"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:118.1"
msgid "Atha kho te licchavī yena ambapālivanaṃ tena pāyiṃsu."
msgstr "Then the Licchavis continued on to Ambapālī’s grove."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp2.17"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:118.2"
msgid "Addasā kho bhagavā te licchavī dūratova āgacchante."
msgstr "The Buddha saw them coming off in the distance,"

msgctxt "dn16:118.3"
msgid "Disvāna bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "and addressed the mendicants:"

#. VAR: yesaṃ → yehi (^pi-tv-kd6#116 [Bhesaj­jak­khan­dhaka/ Licchavīvatthu])
msgctxt "dn16:118.4"
msgid ""
"“yesaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ devā tāvatiṃsā adiṭṭhapubbā, oloketha, "
"bhikkhave, licchaviparisaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"“Any of the mendicants who’ve never seen the gods of the Thirty-Three, just "
"have a look at the assembly of Licchavis."

msgctxt "dn16:118.5"
msgid "apaloketha, bhikkhave, licchaviparisaṃ;"
msgstr "See the assembly of Licchavis,"

msgctxt "dn16:118.6"
msgid "upasaṃharatha, bhikkhave, licchaviparisaṃ—"
msgstr "check them out:"

msgctxt "dn16:118.7"
msgid "tāvatiṃsasadisan”ti."
msgstr "they’re just like the Thirty-Three!”"

#. <a class="wp" id="wp2.18"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:118.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te licchavī yāvatikā yānassa bhūmi, yānena gantvā, yānā "
"paccorohitvā pattikāva yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr ""
"The Licchavis went by carriage as far as the terrain allowed, then descended "
"and approached the Buddha on foot. "

msgctxt "dn16:118.9"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr "They bowed to the Buddha, sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "dn16:118.10"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho te licchavī bhagavā dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi "
"samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi."
msgstr ""
"and the Buddha educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired them with a "
"Dharma talk."

msgctxt "dn16:118.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te licchavī bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā "
"samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "Then they said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn16:118.12"
msgid ""
"“adhivāsetu no, bhante, bhagavā svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghenā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, may the Buddha together with the mendicant Saṅgha please accept "
"tomorrow’s meal from us.”"

msgctxt "dn16:118.13"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā te licchavī etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to the Licchavis:"

#. VAR: adhivutthaṃ → adhivāsitaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn16:118.14"
msgid ""
"“adhivutthaṃ kho me, licchavī, svātanāya ambapāliyā gaṇikāya bhattan”ti."
msgstr "“I have already accepted tomorrow’s meal from Ambapālī the courtesan.”"

msgctxt "dn16:118.15"
msgid "Atha kho te licchavī aṅguliṃ phoṭesuṃ:"
msgstr "Then the Licchavis snapped their fingers, saying:"

msgctxt "dn16:118.16"
msgid "“jitamha vata bho ambakāya, jitamha vata bho ambakāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“We’ve been beaten by the mango-matron! We’ve been beaten by the mango-"
"matron!”"

msgctxt "dn16:118.17"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te licchavī bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkamiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"And then those Licchavis approved and agreed with what the Buddha said. They "
"got up from their seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping "
"him on their right, before leaving."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="102"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.19"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.98"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:119.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho ambapālī gaṇikā tassā rattiyā accayena sake ārāme paṇītaṃ "
"khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā bhagavato kālaṃ ārocāpesi:"
msgstr ""
"And when the night had passed Ambapālī had a variety of delicious foods "
"prepared in her own home. Then she had the Buddha informed of the time, "
"saying:"

msgctxt "dn16:119.2"
msgid "“kālo, bhante, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti."
msgstr "“Sir, it’s time. The meal is ready.”"

msgctxt "dn16:119.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya saddhiṃ "
"bhikkhusaṅghena yena ambapāliyā gaṇikāya nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha got dressed in the morning and, taking his bowl and robes, "
"went to the home of Ambapālī together with the mendicant Saṅgha,"

msgctxt "dn16:119.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "where he sat on the seat spread out."

msgctxt "dn16:119.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho ambapālī gaṇikā buddhappamukhaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena "
"bhojanīyena sahatthā santappesi sampavāresi."
msgstr ""
"Then Ambapālī served and satisfied the mendicant Saṅgha headed by the Buddha "
"with her own hands with a variety of delicious foods."

msgctxt "dn16:119.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho ambapālī gaṇikā bhagavantaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ aññataraṃ "
"nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha had eaten and washed his hand and bowl, Ambapālī took a low "
"seat, sat to one side,"

msgctxt "dn16:119.7"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho ambapālī gaṇikā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn16:119.8"
msgid "“imāhaṃ, bhante, ārāmaṃ buddhappamukhassa bhikkhusaṅghassa dammī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, I present this park to the mendicant Saṅgha headed by the Buddha.”"

msgctxt "dn16:119.9"
msgid "Paṭiggahesi bhagavā ārāmaṃ."
msgstr "The Buddha accepted the park."

msgctxt "dn16:119.10"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā ambapāliṃ gaṇikaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā samādapetvā "
"samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired her with a "
"Dharma talk, after which he got up from his seat and left."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="103"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.20"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:120.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrapi sudaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharanto ambapālivane etadeva bahulaṃ "
"bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ karoti:"
msgstr ""
"And while staying at Vesālī, too, the Buddha often gave this Dhamma talk to "
"the mendicants:"

msgctxt "dn16:120.2"
msgid "“iti sīlaṃ, iti samādhi, iti paññā."
msgstr "“Such is ethics, such is immersion, such is wisdom."

msgctxt "dn16:120.3"
msgid "Sīlaparibhāvito samādhi mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso."
msgstr "When immersion is imbued with ethics it’s very fruitful and beneficial."

msgctxt "dn16:120.4"
msgid "Samādhiparibhāvitā paññā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā."
msgstr "When wisdom is imbued with immersion it’s very fruitful and beneficial."

msgctxt "dn16:120.5"
msgid "Paññāparibhāvitaṃ cittaṃ sammadeva āsavehi vimuccati, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"When the mind is imbued with wisdom it is rightly freed from the "
"defilements, namely,"

msgctxt "dn16:120.6"
msgid "kāmāsavā, bhavāsavā, avijjāsavā”ti."
msgstr "the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:121.1"
msgid "12. Veḷuvagāmavassūpagamana"
msgstr "Commencing the Rains at Beluva"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="104"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.21"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.99"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:122.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā ambapālivane yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ "
"āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha had stayed in Ambapālī’s grove as long as he wished, he "
"addressed Venerable Ānanda:"

#. VAR: veḷuvagāmako → beluvagāmako (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:122.2"
msgid "“āyāmānanda, yena veḷuvagāmako tenupasaṅkamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Ānanda, let’s go to the little village of Beluva.”"

msgctxt "dn16:122.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

msgctxt "dn16:122.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ yena veḷuvagāmako tadavasari."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants arrived at the "
"little village of Beluva,"

msgctxt "dn16:122.5"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā veḷuvagāmake viharati."
msgstr "and stayed on there."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp2.22"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:122.6"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

#. VAR: vassaṃ upetha → upagacchatha (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn16:122.7"
msgid ""
"“etha tumhe, bhikkhave, samantā vesāliṃ yathāmittaṃ yathāsandiṭṭhaṃ "
"yathāsambhattaṃ vassaṃ upetha."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, please enter the rainy season residence with whatever friends "
"or acquaintances you have around Vesālī."

msgctxt "dn16:122.8"
msgid "Ahaṃ pana idheva veḷuvagāmake vassaṃ upagacchāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"I’ll commence the rainy season residence right here in the little village of "
"Beluva.”"

msgctxt "dn16:122.9"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paṭissutvā samantā vesāliṃ "
"yathāmittaṃ yathāsandiṭṭhaṃ yathāsambhattaṃ vassaṃ upagacchiṃsu."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” those mendicants replied. They did as the Buddha said,"

msgctxt "dn16:122.10"
msgid "Bhagavā pana tattheva veḷuvagāmake vassaṃ upagacchi."
msgstr ""
"while the Buddha commenced the rainy season residence right there in the "
"little village of Beluva."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="105"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.23"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:123.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavato vassūpagatassa kharo ābādho uppajji, bāḷhā vedanā "
"vattanti māraṇantikā."
msgstr ""
"After the Buddha had commenced the rainy season residence, he fell severely "
"ill, struck by dreadful pains close to death."

msgctxt "dn16:123.2"
msgid "Tā sudaṃ bhagavā sato sampajāno adhivāsesi avihaññamāno."
msgstr ""
"But he endured with mindfulness and situational awareness, without worrying."

msgctxt "dn16:123.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavato etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to the Buddha: "

msgctxt "dn16:123.4"
msgid ""
"“na kho metaṃ patirūpaṃ, yvāhaṃ anāmantetvā upaṭṭhāke anapaloketvā "
"bhikkhusaṃghaṃ parinibbāyeyyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“It would not be appropriate for me to become finally extinguished before "
"informing my attendants and taking leave of the mendicant Saṅgha."

msgctxt "dn16:123.5"
msgid ""
"Yannūnāhaṃ imaṃ ābādhaṃ vīriyena paṭipaṇāmetvā jīvitasaṅkhāraṃ adhiṭṭhāya "
"vihareyyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t I forcefully suppress this illness, stabilize the life force, and "
"live on?”"

#. <a class="wp" id="wp2.24"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:123.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā taṃ ābādhaṃ vīriyena paṭipaṇāmetvā jīvitasaṅkhāraṃ "
"adhiṭṭhāya vihāsi."
msgstr "So that is what he did."

msgctxt "dn16:123.7"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavato so ābādho paṭippassambhi."
msgstr "Then the Buddha’s illness died down."

#. VAR: gilānā vuṭṭhito → gilānavuṭṭhito (saddanīti)
msgctxt "dn16:123.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā gilānā vuṭṭhito aciravuṭṭhito gelaññā vihārā nikkhamma "
"vihārapacchāyāyaṃ paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Soon after the Buddha had recovered from that sickness, he came out from his "
"dwelling and sat in the shade of the porch on the seat spread out."

msgctxt "dn16:123.9"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha,  "

msgctxt "dn16:123.10"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed, sat down to one side, "

msgctxt "dn16:123.11"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

msgctxt "dn16:123.12"
msgid "“diṭṭho me, bhante, bhagavato phāsu;"
msgstr "“Sir, it’s fantastic that the Buddha is comfortable"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:123.13"
msgid ""
"diṭṭhaṃ me, bhante, bhagavato khamanīyaṃ, api ca me, bhante, madhurakajāto "
"viya kāyo."
msgstr "and well."

msgctxt "dn16:123.14"
msgid "Disāpi me na pakkhāyanti;"
msgstr ""
"Because when the Buddha was sick, my body felt like it was drugged. I was "
"disorientated, and the teachings weren’t clear to me."

msgctxt "dn16:123.15"
msgid ""
"dhammāpi maṃ na paṭibhanti bhagavato gelaññena, api ca me, bhante, ahosi "
"kācideva assāsamattā:"
msgstr "Still, at least I was consoled by the thought that"

msgctxt "dn16:123.16"
msgid ""
"‘na tāva bhagavā parinibbāyissati, na yāva bhagavā bhikkhusaṃghaṃ ārabbha "
"kiñcideva udāharatī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"the Buddha won’t become finally extinguished without making some statement "
"regarding the Saṅgha of mendicants.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="106"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2.25"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.100"></a>
#. VAR: paccāsīsati → paccāsiṃsati (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:124.1"
msgid "“Kiṃ panānanda, bhikkhusaṃgho mayi paccāsīsati?"
msgstr "“But what could the mendicant Saṅgha expect from me, Ānanda?"

msgctxt "dn16:124.2"
msgid "Desito, ānanda, mayā dhammo anantaraṃ abāhiraṃ karitvā."
msgstr ""
"I’ve taught the Dhamma without making any distinction between secret and "
"public teachings."

msgctxt "dn16:124.3"
msgid "Natthānanda, tathāgatassa dhammesu ācariyamuṭṭhi."
msgstr ""
"The Realized One doesn’t have the closed fist of a teacher when it comes to "
"the teachings."

msgctxt "dn16:124.4"
msgid "Yassa nūna, ānanda, evamassa:"
msgstr "If there’s anyone who thinks"

msgctxt "dn16:124.5"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ bhikkhusaṃghaṃ pariharissāmī’ti vā ‘mamuddesiko bhikkhusaṃgho’ti vā, "
"so nūna, ānanda, bhikkhusaṃghaṃ ārabbha kiñcideva udāhareyya."
msgstr ""
"‘I’ll take charge of the Saṅgha of mendicants,’ or ‘the Saṅgha of mendicants "
"is meant for me,’ let them make a statement regarding the Saṅgha."

msgctxt "dn16:124.6"
msgid "Tathāgatassa kho, ānanda, na evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "But the Realized One doesn’t think like this,"

msgctxt "dn16:124.7"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ bhikkhusaṃghaṃ pariharissāmī’ti vā ‘mamuddesiko bhikkhusaṃgho’ti vā."
msgstr ""

#. VAR: Sakiṃ → sa kiṃ (bj) | kiṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:124.8"
msgid "Sakiṃ, ānanda, tathāgato bhikkhusaṃghaṃ ārabbha kiñcideva udāharissati."
msgstr "so why should he make some statement regarding the Saṅgha?"

msgctxt "dn16:124.9"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ kho panānanda, etarahi jiṇṇo vuddho mahallako addhagato vayo anuppatto."
msgstr ""
"I’m now old, elderly and senior. I’m advanced in years and have reached the "
"final stage of life."

msgctxt "dn16:124.10"
msgid "Āsītiko me vayo vattati."
msgstr "I’m currently eighty years old."

# Reading vedhanissayena following Levman
#. VAR: veṭhamissakena → vek­kha­mis­sa­kena (bj) | veḷumissakena (s1-3, km) |
#. veghamissakena (pts1) | vekhamissakena (mr)
msgctxt "dn16:124.11"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, ānanda, jajjarasakaṭaṃ veṭhamissakena yāpeti;"
msgstr "Just as a decrepit cart keeps going by relying on straps,"

msgctxt "dn16:124.12"
msgid "evameva kho, ānanda, veṭhamissakena maññe tathāgatassa kāyo yāpeti."
msgstr ""
"in the same way, the Realized One’s body keeps going by relying on straps, "
"or so you’d think."

msgctxt "dn16:124.13"
msgid ""
"Yasmiṃ, ānanda, samaye tathāgato sabbanimittānaṃ amanasikārā ekaccānaṃ "
"vedanānaṃ nirodhā animittaṃ cetosamādhiṃ upasampajja viharati, phāsutaro, "
"ānanda, tasmiṃ samaye tathāgatassa kāyo hoti."
msgstr ""
"Sometimes the Realized One, not focusing on any signs, and with the "
"cessation of certain feelings, enters and remains in the signless samādhi of "
"the heart. Only then does the Realized One’s body become more comfortable."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp2.26"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:124.14"
msgid ""
"Tasmātihānanda, attadīpā viharatha attasaraṇā anaññasaraṇā, dhammadīpā "
"dhammasaraṇā anaññasaraṇā."
msgstr ""
"So Ānanda, be your own island, your own refuge, with no other refuge. Let "
"the teaching be your island and your refuge, with no other refuge. "

msgctxt "dn16:124.15"
msgid ""
"Kathañcānanda, bhikkhu attadīpo viharati attasaraṇo anaññasaraṇo, dhammadīpo "
"dhammasaraṇo anaññasaraṇo?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant do this? "

msgctxt "dn16:124.16"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati atāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya "
"loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body, keen, "
"aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "dn16:124.17"
msgid "Vedanāsu …"
msgstr "They meditate by observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "dn16:124.18"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:124.19"
msgid "citte …"
msgstr "mind …"

msgctxt "dn16:124.20"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:124.21"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"principles, keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the "
"world. "

msgctxt "dn16:124.22"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, ānanda, bhikkhu attadīpo viharati attasaraṇo anaññasaraṇo, "
"dhammadīpo dhammasaraṇo anaññasaraṇo."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant is their own island, their own refuge, with no other "
"refuge. That’s how the teaching is their island and their refuge, with no "
"other refuge."

msgctxt "dn16:124.23"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, ānanda, etarahi vā mama vā accayena attadīpā viharissanti "
"attasaraṇā anaññasaraṇā, dhammadīpā dhammasaraṇā anaññasaraṇā, tamatagge me "
"te, ānanda, bhikkhū bhavissanti ye keci sikkhākāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Whether now or after I have passed, any of my mendicants who shall live as "
"their own island, their own refuge, with no other refuge; with the teaching "
"as their island and their refuge, with no other refuge, shall be among the "
"best of the best—any who want to train.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn16:125.1"
msgid "Dutiyabhāṇavāro."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:126.1"
msgid "13. Nimittobhāsakathā"
msgstr "An Obvious Hint"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="107"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.1"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.102"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:127.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya vesāliṃ piṇḍāya "
"pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha got dressed in the morning and, taking his bowl and robes, "
"entered Vesālī for alms."

msgctxt "dn16:127.2"
msgid ""
"Vesāliyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto āyasmantaṃ "
"ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"Then, after the meal, when he had returned from alms-round, he addressed "
"Venerable Ānanda: "

#. VAR: cāpālaṃ cetiyaṃ → pāvālaṃ cetiyaṃ (s1-3, km)
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:127.3"
msgid ""
"“gaṇhāhi, ānanda, nisīdanaṃ, yena cāpālaṃ cetiyaṃ tenupasaṅkamissāma divā "
"vihārāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Ānanda, get your sitting cloth. Let’s go to the Cāpāla tree shrine for the "
"day’s meditation.”"

msgctxt "dn16:127.4"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paṭissutvā nisīdanaṃ ādāya "
"bhagavantaṃ piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhi."
msgstr ""
"“Yes, sir,” replied Ānanda. Taking his sitting cloth he followed behind the "
"Buddha."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp3.2"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:127.5"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā yena cāpālaṃ cetiyaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then the Buddha went up to the Cāpāla shrine, "

msgctxt "dn16:127.6"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "where he sat on the seat spread out. "

msgctxt "dn16:127.7"
msgid "Āyasmāpi kho ānando bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "Ānanda bowed to the Buddha and sat down to one side."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="108"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.103"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:128.1"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said to him: "

#. VAR: sattambaṃ → sattamba (bj) | sattambakaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:128.2"
msgid ""
"“ramaṇīyā, ānanda, vesālī, ramaṇīyaṃ udenaṃ cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ gotamakaṃ "
"cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ sattambaṃ cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ bahuputtaṃ cetiyaṃ, "
"ramaṇīyaṃ sārandadaṃ cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ cāpālaṃ cetiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Ānanda, Vesālī is lovely. And the Udena, Gotamaka, Sattamba, Bahuputta, "
"Sārandada, and Cāpāla tree shrines are all lovely."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp3.3"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:128.3"
msgid ""
"Yassa kassaci, ānanda, cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā yānīkatā "
"vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā, so ākaṅkhamāno kappaṃ vā "
"tiṭṭheyya kappāvasesaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"Whoever has developed and cultivated the four bases for psychic power—made "
"them a vehicle and a basis, kept them up, consolidated them, and properly "
"implemented them—may, if they wish, live on for the eon or what’s left of "
"the eon."

msgctxt "dn16:128.4"
msgid ""
"Tathāgatassa kho, ānanda, cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā yānīkatā "
"vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā, so ākaṅkhamāno, ānanda, "
"tathāgato kappaṃ vā tiṭṭheyya kappāvasesaṃ vā”ti."
msgstr ""
"The Realized One has developed and cultivated the four bases for psychic "
"power, made them a vehicle and a basis, kept them up, consolidated them, and "
"properly implemented them. If he wished, the Realized One could live on for "
"the eon or what’s left of the eon.” "

#. <a class="wp" id="wp3.4"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:128.5"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho āyasmā ānando bhagavatā oḷārike nimitte kayiramāne oḷārike obhāse "
"kayiramāne nāsakkhi paṭivijjhituṃ;"
msgstr ""
"But Ānanda didn’t get it, even though the Buddha dropped such an obvious "
"hint, such a clear sign."

msgctxt "dn16:128.6"
msgid "na bhagavantaṃ yāci:"
msgstr "He didn’t beg the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn16:128.7"
msgid ""
"“tiṭṭhatu, bhante, bhagavā kappaṃ, tiṭṭhatu sugato kappaṃ bahujanahitāya "
"bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan”ti, "
"yathā taṃ mārena pariyuṭṭhitacitto."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, may the Blessed One please remain for the eon! May the Holy One please "
"remain for the eon! That would be for the welfare and happiness of many "
"people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans.” For his "
"mind was as if possessed by Māra. "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="109"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.5"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.104"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:129.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho bhagavā …"
msgstr "For a second time …"

msgctxt "dn16:129.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:129.3"
msgid "tatiyampi kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "And for a third time, the Buddha said to Ānanda: "

msgctxt "dn16:129.4"
msgid ""
"“ramaṇīyā, ānanda, vesālī, ramaṇīyaṃ udenaṃ cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ gotamakaṃ "
"cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ sattambaṃ cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ bahuputtaṃ cetiyaṃ, "
"ramaṇīyaṃ sārandadaṃ cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ cāpālaṃ cetiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Ānanda, Vesālī is lovely. And the Udena, Gotamaka, Sattamba, and Bahuputta, "
"Sārandada, and Cāpāla tree shrines are all lovely."

msgctxt "dn16:129.5"
msgid ""
"Yassa kassaci, ānanda, cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā yānīkatā "
"vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā, so ākaṅkhamāno kappaṃ vā "
"tiṭṭheyya kappāvasesaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"Whoever has developed and cultivated the four bases for psychic power—made "
"them a vehicle and a basis, kept them up, consolidated them, and properly "
"implemented them—may, if they wish, live on for the eon, or what’s left of "
"it."

msgctxt "dn16:129.6"
msgid ""
"Tathāgatassa kho, ānanda, cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā yānīkatā "
"vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā, so ākaṅkhamāno, ānanda, "
"tathāgato kappaṃ vā tiṭṭheyya kappāvasesaṃ vā”ti."
msgstr ""
"The Realized One has developed and cultivated the four bases for psychic "
"power, made them a vehicle and a basis, kept them up, consolidated them, and "
"properly implemented them. If he wished, the Realized One could live on for "
"the eon, or what’s left of it.” "

msgctxt "dn16:129.7"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho āyasmā ānando bhagavatā oḷārike nimitte kayiramāne oḷārike obhāse "
"kayiramāne nāsakkhi paṭivijjhituṃ;"
msgstr ""
"But Ānanda didn’t get it, even though the Buddha dropped such an obvious "
"hint, such a clear sign."

msgctxt "dn16:129.8"
msgid "na bhagavantaṃ yāci:"
msgstr "He didn’t beg the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn16:129.9"
msgid ""
"“tiṭṭhatu, bhante, bhagavā kappaṃ, tiṭṭhatu sugato kappaṃ bahujanahitāya "
"bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan”ti, "
"yathā taṃ mārena pariyuṭṭhitacitto."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, may the Blessed One please remain for the eon! May the Holy One please "
"remain for the eon! That would be for the welfare and happiness of many "
"people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans.” For his "
"mind was as if possessed by Māra. "

#. <a class="wp" id="wp3.6"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:129.10"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha got up and said to Venerable Ānanda:"

msgctxt "dn16:129.11"
msgid "“gaccha tvaṃ, ānanda, yassadāni kālaṃ maññasī”ti."
msgstr "“Go now, Ānanda, at your convenience.”"

msgctxt "dn16:129.12"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paṭissutvā uṭṭhāyāsanā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā avidūre aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle "
"nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"“Yes, sir,” replied Ānanda. He rose from his seat, bowed, and respectfully "
"circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before sitting at the root of "
"a tree close by. "

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:130.1"
msgid "14. Mārayācanakathā"
msgstr "The Appeal of Māra"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="110"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.7"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.105"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:131.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā acirapakkante āyasmante ānande yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"And then, not long after Ānanda had left, Māra the Wicked went up to the the "
"Buddha,"

msgctxt "dn16:131.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr "stood to one side,"

msgctxt "dn16:131.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho māro pāpimā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

msgctxt "dn16:131.4"
msgid ""
"“parinibbātu dāni, bhante, bhagavā, parinibbātu sugato, parinibbānakālo "
"dāni, bhante, bhagavato."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, may the Blessed One now become finally extinguished! May the Holy One "
"now become finally extinguished! Now is the time for the Buddha to become "
"finally extinguished."

msgctxt "dn16:131.5"
msgid "Bhāsitā kho panesā, bhante, bhagavatā vācā:"
msgstr "Sir, you once made this statement:"

msgctxt "dn16:131.6"
msgid ""
"‘na tāvāhaṃ, pāpima, parinibbāyissāmi, yāva me bhikkhū na sāvakā bhavissanti "
"viyattā vinītā visāradā bahussutā dhammadharā dhammānudhammappaṭipannā "
"sāmīcippaṭipannā anudhammacārino, sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ uggahetvā ācikkhissanti "
"desessanti paññapessanti paṭṭhapessanti vivarissanti vibhajissanti "
"uttānīkarissanti, uppannaṃ parappavādaṃ sahadhammena suniggahitaṃ niggahetvā "
"sappāṭihāriyaṃ dhammaṃ desessantī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Wicked One, I will not become fully extinguished until I have monk "
"disciples who are competent, educated, assured, learned, have memorized the "
"teachings, and practice in line with the teachings. Not until they practice "
"properly, living in line with the teaching. Not until they’ve learned their "
"tradition, and explain, teach, advocate, establish, disclose, analyze, and "
"make it clear. Not until they can legitimately and completely refute the "
"doctrines of others that come up, and teach with a demonstrable basis.’"

#. <a class="wp" id="wp3.8"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:131.7"
msgid ""
"Etarahi kho pana, bhante, bhikkhū bhagavato sāvakā viyattā vinītā visāradā "
"bahussutā dhammadharā dhammānudhammappaṭipannā sāmīcippaṭipannā "
"anudhammacārino, sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ uggahetvā ācikkhanti desenti paññapenti "
"paṭṭhapenti vivaranti vibhajanti uttānīkaronti, uppannaṃ parappavādaṃ "
"sahadhammena suniggahitaṃ niggahetvā sappāṭihāriyaṃ dhammaṃ desenti."
msgstr "Today you do have such monk disciples."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:131.8"
msgid ""
"Parinibbātu dāni, bhante, bhagavā, parinibbātu sugato, parinibbānakālo dāni, "
"bhante, bhagavato."
msgstr ""
"May the Blessed One now become finally extinguished! May the Holy One now "
"become finally extinguished! Now is the time for the Buddha to become "
"finally extinguished."

