#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="114"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:135.1"
msgid "Bhāsitā kho panesā, bhante, bhagavatā vācā:"
msgstr "Sir, you once made this statement:"

msgctxt "dn16:135.2"
msgid ""
"‘na tāvāhaṃ, pāpima, parinibbāyissāmi, yāva me idaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na "
"iddhañceva bhavissati phītañca vitthārikaṃ bāhujaññaṃ puthubhūtaṃ yāva "
"devamanussehi suppakāsitan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Wicked One, I will not become fully extinguished until my spiritual life is "
"successful and prosperous, extensive, popular, widespread, and well "
"proclaimed wherever there are gods and humans.’"

msgctxt "dn16:135.3"
msgid ""
"Etarahi kho pana, bhante, bhagavato brahmacariyaṃ iddhañceva phītañca "
"vitthārikaṃ bāhujaññaṃ puthubhūtaṃ, yāva devamanussehi suppakāsitaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Today your spiritual life is successful and prosperous, extensive, popular, "
"widespread, and well proclaimed wherever there are gods and humans."

msgctxt "dn16:135.4"
msgid ""
"Parinibbātu dāni, bhante, bhagavā, parinibbātu sugato, parinibbānakālo dāni, "
"bhante, bhagavato”ti."
msgstr ""
"May the Blessed One now become finally extinguished! May the Holy One now "
"become finally extinguished! Now is the time for the Buddha to become "
"finally extinguished.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="115"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.9"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:136.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā māraṃ pāpimantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When this was said, the Buddha said to Māra:"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:136.2"
msgid ""
"“appossukko tvaṃ, pāpima, hohi, na ciraṃ tathāgatassa parinibbānaṃ "
"bhavissati."
msgstr ""
"“Relax, Wicked One. The final extinguishment of the Realized One will be "
"soon."

msgctxt "dn16:136.3"
msgid "Ito tiṇṇaṃ māsānaṃ accayena tathāgato parinibbāyissatī”ti."
msgstr "Three months from now the Realized One will finally be extinguished.” "

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:137.1"
msgid "15. Āyusaṅkhāraossajjana"
msgstr "Surendering the Life Force"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="116"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.10"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.107"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:138.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā cāpāle cetiye sato sampajāno āyusaṅkhāraṃ ossaji."
msgstr ""
"So at the Cāpāla tree shrine the Buddha, mindful and aware, surrendered the "
"life force."

#. VAR: salomahaṃso → lomahaṃso (s1-3, km) | lomahaṃsano (pts1)
#. VAR: devadundubhiyo → devadundabhiyo (s1-3) | devadudrabhiyo (mr)
msgctxt "dn16:138.2"
msgid ""
"Ossaṭṭhe ca bhagavatā āyusaṅkhāre mahābhūmicālo ahosi bhiṃsanako "
"salomahaṃso, devadundubhiyo ca phaliṃsu."
msgstr ""
"When he did so there was a great earthquake, awe-inspiring and hair-raising, "
"and thunder cracked the sky."

msgctxt "dn16:138.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etamatthaṃ viditvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ udānaṃ udānesi:"
msgstr ""
"Then, knowing the meaning of this, on that occasion the Buddha spoke these "
"words of inspiration:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="117"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:139.1"
msgid "“Tulamatulañca sambhavaṃ,"
msgstr "“Comparing the incomparable with an extension of life,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:139.2"
msgid "Bhavasaṅkhāramavassaji muni;"
msgstr "the sage surrendered the life force. "

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:139.3"
msgid "Ajjhattarato samāhito,"
msgstr "Happy inside, immersed, "

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:139.4"
msgid "Abhindi kavacamivattasambhavan”ti."
msgstr "he broke his extended existence like a suit of armor.”"

#. </p></blockquote><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:140.1"
msgid "16. Mahābhūmicālahetu"
msgstr "The Causes of Earthquakes"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="118"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.11"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:141.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato ānandassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda thought:"

msgctxt "dn16:141.2"
msgid "“acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho, mahā vatāyaṃ bhūmicālo;"
msgstr "“How incredible, how amazing! That was a really big earthquake!"

msgctxt "dn16:141.3"
msgid "sumahā vatāyaṃ bhūmicālo bhiṃsanako salomahaṃso;"
msgstr ""
"That was really a very big earthquake; awe-inspiring and hair-raising, and "
"thunder cracked the sky!"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:141.4"
msgid "devadundubhiyo ca phaliṃsu."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn16:141.5"
msgid "Ko nu kho hetu ko paccayo mahato bhūmicālassa pātubhāvāyā”ti?"
msgstr "What’s the cause, what’s the reason for a great earthquake?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="119"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.12"></a>
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:142.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami, upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi, ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "
"and said to him:"

msgctxt "dn16:142.2"
msgid "“acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "“How incredible, sir, how amazing!"

msgctxt "dn16:142.3"
msgid "Mahā vatāyaṃ, bhante, bhūmicālo;"
msgstr "That was a really big earthquake!"

msgctxt "dn16:142.4"
msgid "sumahā vatāyaṃ, bhante, bhūmicālo bhiṃsanako salomahaṃso;"
msgstr ""
"That was really a very big earthquake; awe-inspiring and hair-raising, and "
"thunder cracked the sky!"

msgctxt "dn16:142.5"
msgid "devadundubhiyo ca phaliṃsu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:142.6"
msgid "Ko nu kho, bhante, hetu ko paccayo mahato bhūmicālassa pātubhāvāyā”ti?"
msgstr "What’s the cause, what’s the reason for a great earthquake?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="120"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.13"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.108"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:143.1"
msgid ""
"“Aṭṭha kho ime, ānanda, hetū, aṭṭha paccayā mahato bhūmicālassa pātubhāvāya."
msgstr ""
"“Ānanda, there are these eight causes and reasons for a great earthquake."

msgctxt "dn16:143.2"
msgid "Katame aṭṭha?"
msgstr "What eight? "

msgctxt "dn16:143.3"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, ānanda, mahāpathavī udake patiṭṭhitā, udakaṃ vāte patiṭṭhitaṃ, vāto "
"ākāsaṭṭho."
msgstr ""
"This great earth is grounded on water, the water is grounded on air, and the "
"air stands in space."

msgctxt "dn16:143.4"
msgid "Hoti kho so, ānanda, samayo, yaṃ mahāvātā vāyanti."
msgstr "At a time when a great wind blows,"

msgctxt "dn16:143.5"
msgid "Mahāvātā vāyantā udakaṃ kampenti."
msgstr "it stirs the water,"

msgctxt "dn16:143.6"
msgid "Udakaṃ kampitaṃ pathaviṃ kampeti."
msgstr "and the water stirs the earth."

msgctxt "dn16:143.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamo hetu paṭhamo paccayo mahato bhūmicālassa pātubhāvāya."
msgstr "This is the first cause and reason for a great earthquake."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="121"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.14"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:144.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, samaṇo vā hoti brāhmaṇo vā iddhimā cetovasippatto, "
"devo vā mahiddhiko mahānubhāvo, tassa parittā pathavīsaññā bhāvitā hoti, "
"appamāṇā āposaññā."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, there is an ascetic or brahmin with psychic powers who has "
"achieved mastery of the mind, or a god who is mighty and powerful. They’ve "
"developed a limited perception of earth and a limitless perception of water. "

msgctxt "dn16:144.2"
msgid "So imaṃ pathaviṃ kampeti saṅkampeti sampakampeti sampavedheti."
msgstr "They make the earth shake and rock and tremble."

msgctxt "dn16:144.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ dutiyo hetu dutiyo paccayo mahato bhūmicālassa pātubhāvāya."
msgstr "This is the second cause and reason for a great earthquake."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="122"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.15"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:145.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, yadā bodhisatto tusitakāyā cavitvā sato sampajāno "
"mātukucchiṃ okkamati, tadāyaṃ pathavī kampati saṅkampati sampakampati "
"sampavedhati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, when the being intent on awakening passes away from the group "
"of Joyful Gods, he’s conceived in his mother’s belly, mindful and aware. "
"Then the earth shakes and rocks and trembles."

msgctxt "dn16:145.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ tatiyo hetu tatiyo paccayo mahato bhūmicālassa pātubhāvāya."
msgstr "This is the third cause and reason for a great earthquake."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="123"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.16"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:146.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, yadā bodhisatto sato sampajāno mātukucchismā "
"nikkhamati, tadāyaṃ pathavī kampati saṅkampati sampakampati sampavedhati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, when the being intent on awakening comes out of his mother’s "
"belly mindful and aware, the earth shakes and rocks and trembles."

msgctxt "dn16:146.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ catuttho hetu catuttho paccayo mahato bhūmicālassa pātubhāvāya."
msgstr "This is the fourth cause and reason for a great earthquake."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="124"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.17"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:147.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, yadā tathāgato anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ "
"abhisambujjhati, tadāyaṃ pathavī kampati saṅkampati sampakampati "
"sampavedhati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, when the Realized One realizes the supreme perfect awakening, "
"the earth shakes and rocks and trembles."

msgctxt "dn16:147.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ pañcamo hetu pañcamo paccayo mahato bhūmicālassa pātubhāvāya."
msgstr "This is the fifth cause and reason for a great earthquake."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="125"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.18"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:148.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, yadā tathāgato anuttaraṃ dhammacakkaṃ pavatteti, "
"tadāyaṃ pathavī kampati saṅkampati sampakampati sampavedhati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, when the Realized One rolls forth the supreme Wheel of Dharma, "
"the earth shakes and rocks and trembles."

msgctxt "dn16:148.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ chaṭṭho hetu chaṭṭho paccayo mahato bhūmicālassa pātubhāvāya."
msgstr "This is the sixth cause and reason for a great earthquake."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="126"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.19"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:149.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, yadā tathāgato sato sampajāno āyusaṅkhāraṃ ossajjati, "
"tadāyaṃ pathavī kampati saṅkampati sampakampati sampavedhati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, when the Realized One, mindful and aware, surrenders the life "
"force, the earth shakes and rocks and trembles."

msgctxt "dn16:149.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ sattamo hetu sattamo paccayo mahato bhūmicālassa pātubhāvāya."
msgstr "This is the seventh cause and reason for a great earthquake."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="127"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.20"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.109"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:150.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, yadā tathāgato anupādisesāya nibbānadhātuyā "
"parinibbāyati, tadāyaṃ pathavī kampati saṅkampati sampakampati sampavedhati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, when the Realized One becomes fully extinguished through the "
"natural principle of extinguishment, without anything left over, the earth "
"shakes and rocks and trembles."

msgctxt "dn16:150.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ aṭṭhamo hetu aṭṭhamo paccayo mahato bhūmicālassa pātubhāvāya."
msgstr "This is the eighth cause and reason for a great earthquake."

msgctxt "dn16:150.3"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, ānanda, aṭṭha hetū, aṭṭha paccayā mahato bhūmicālassa pātubhāvāya."
msgstr "These are the eight causes and reasons for a great earthquake."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:151.1"
msgid "17. Aṭṭhaparisā"
msgstr "Eight Assemblies"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="128"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.21"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.110"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:152.1"
msgid "Aṭṭha kho imā, ānanda, parisā."
msgstr "There are, Ānanda, these eight assemblies."

msgctxt "dn16:152.2"
msgid "Katamā aṭṭha?"
msgstr "What eight?"

msgctxt "dn16:152.3"
msgid ""
"Khattiyaparisā, brāhmaṇaparisā, gahapatiparisā, samaṇaparisā, "
"cātumahārājikaparisā, tāvatiṃsaparisā, māraparisā, brahmaparisā."
msgstr ""
"The assemblies of aristocrats, brahmins, householders, and ascetics. An "
"assembly of the gods of the Four Great Kings. An assembly of the gods of the "
"Thirty-Three. An assembly of Māras. An assembly of Brahmās."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp3.22"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:152.4"
msgid ""
"Abhijānāmi kho panāhaṃ, ānanda, anekasataṃ khattiyaparisaṃ upasaṅkamitā."
msgstr "I recall having approached an assembly of hundreds of aristocrats."

msgctxt "dn16:152.5"
msgid ""
"Tatrapi mayā sannisinnapubbañceva sallapitapubbañca sākacchā ca "
"samāpajjitapubbā."
msgstr "There I used to sit with them, converse, and engage in discussion. "

msgctxt "dn16:152.6"
msgid "Tattha yādisako tesaṃ vaṇṇo hoti, tādisako mayhaṃ vaṇṇo hoti."
msgstr "And my appearance and voice became just like theirs."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:152.7"
msgid "Yādisako tesaṃ saro hoti, tādisako mayhaṃ saro hoti."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn16:152.8"
msgid "Dhammiyā kathāya sandassemi samādapemi samuttejemi sampahaṃsemi."
msgstr "I educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired them with a Dharma talk."

msgctxt "dn16:152.9"
msgid "Bhāsamānañca maṃ na jānanti:"
msgstr "But when I spoke they didn’t know:"

msgctxt "dn16:152.10"
msgid "‘ko nu kho ayaṃ bhāsati devo vā manusso vā’ti?"
msgstr "‘Who is this that speaks? Is it a god or a human?’"

msgctxt "dn16:152.11"
msgid ""
"Dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā "
"antaradhāyāmi."
msgstr "And when my Dharma talk was finished I vanished. "

msgctxt "dn16:152.12"
msgid "Antarahitañca maṃ na jānanti:"
msgstr "But when I vanished they didn’t know: "

msgctxt "dn16:152.13"
msgid "‘ko nu kho ayaṃ antarahito devo vā manusso vā’ti?"
msgstr "‘Who was that who vanished? Was it a god or a human?’"

#. <a class="wp" id="wp3.23"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:152.14"
msgid "Abhijānāmi kho panāhaṃ, ānanda, anekasataṃ brāhmaṇaparisaṃ …"
msgstr "I recall having approached an assembly of hundreds of brahmins …"

msgctxt "dn16:152.15"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:152.16"
msgid "gahapatiparisaṃ …"
msgstr "householders …"

msgctxt "dn16:152.17"
msgid "samaṇaparisaṃ …"
msgstr "ascetics …"

msgctxt "dn16:152.18"
msgid "cātumahārājikaparisaṃ …"
msgstr "the gods of the Four Great Kings …"

msgctxt "dn16:152.19"
msgid "tāvatiṃsaparisaṃ …"
msgstr "the gods of the Thirty-Three …"

msgctxt "dn16:152.20"
