#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:162.1"
msgid "19. Aṭṭhavimokkha"
msgstr "The Eight Liberations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="137"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.33"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.112"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:163.1"
msgid "Aṭṭha kho ime, ānanda, vimokkhā."
msgstr "Ānanda, there are these eight liberations."

msgctxt "dn16:163.2"
msgid "Katame aṭṭha?"
msgstr "What eight? "

msgctxt "dn16:163.3"
msgid "Rūpī rūpāni passati, ayaṃ paṭhamo vimokkho."
msgstr "Having form, they see visions. This is the first liberation."

msgctxt "dn16:163.4"
msgid "Ajjhattaṃ arūpasaññī bahiddhā rūpāni passati, ayaṃ dutiyo vimokkho."
msgstr ""
"Not perceiving form internally, they see visions externally. This is the "
"second liberation."

msgctxt "dn16:163.5"
msgid "Subhanteva adhimutto hoti, ayaṃ tatiyo vimokkho."
msgstr "They’re focused only on beauty. This is the third liberation."

msgctxt "dn16:163.6"
msgid ""
"Sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ "
"amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati, ayaṃ "
"catuttho vimokkho."
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of "
"impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is "
"infinite’, they enter and remain in the dimension of infinite space. This is "
"the fourth liberation."

msgctxt "dn16:163.7"
msgid ""
"Sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti "
"viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati, ayaṃ pañcamo vimokkho."
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘"
"consciousness is infinite’, they enter and remain in the dimension of "
"infinite consciousness. This is the fifth liberation."

msgctxt "dn16:163.8"
msgid ""
"Sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati, ayaṃ chaṭṭho vimokkho."
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘"
"there is nothing at all’, they enter and remain in the dimension of "
"nothingness. This is the sixth liberation."

msgctxt "dn16:163.9"
msgid ""
"Sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati, ayaṃ sattamo vimokkho."
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, they enter and remain in "
"the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception. This is the seventh "
"liberation."

msgctxt "dn16:163.10"
msgid ""
"Sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati, ayaṃ aṭṭhamo vimokkho."
msgstr ""
"Going totally beyond the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, "
"they enter and remain in the cessation of perception and feeling. This is "
"the eighth liberation."

msgctxt "dn16:163.11"
msgid "Ime kho, ānanda, aṭṭha vimokkhā."
msgstr "These are the eight liberations."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn16:164.1"
msgid "()"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="138"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.34"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:165.1"
msgid ""
"Ekamidāhaṃ, ānanda, samayaṃ uruvelāyaṃ viharāmi najjā nerañjarāya tīre "
"ajapālanigrodhe paṭhamābhisambuddho."
msgstr ""
"Ānanda, this one time, when I was first awakened, I was staying near Uruvelā "
"at the goatherd’s banyan tree on the bank of the Nerañjarā River."

msgctxt "dn16:165.2"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, māro pāpimā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then Māra the wicked approached me,"

msgctxt "dn16:165.3"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr "stood to one side,"

msgctxt "dn16:165.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho, ānanda, māro pāpimā maṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said:"

msgctxt "dn16:165.5"
msgid "‘parinibbātu dāni, bhante, bhagavā;"
msgstr ""
"‘Sir, may the Blessed One now become finally extinguished! May the Holy One "
"now become finally extinguished! Now is the time for the Buddha to become "
"finally extinguished.’"

msgctxt "dn16:165.6"
msgid "parinibbātu sugato, parinibbānakālo dāni, bhante, bhagavato’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:165.7"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, ānanda, māraṃ pāpimantaṃ etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, I said to Māra:"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="139"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.35"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.113"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:166.1"
msgid ""
"‘Na tāvāhaṃ, pāpima, parinibbāyissāmi, yāva me bhikkhū na sāvakā bhavissanti "
"viyattā vinītā visāradā bahussutā dhammadharā dhammānudhammappaṭipannā "
"sāmīcippaṭipannā anudhammacārino, sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ uggahetvā ācikkhissanti "
"desessanti paññapessanti paṭṭhapessanti vivarissanti vibhajissanti "
"uttānīkarissanti, uppannaṃ parappavādaṃ sahadhammena suniggahitaṃ niggahetvā "
"sappāṭihāriyaṃ dhammaṃ desessanti."
msgstr ""
"‘Wicked One, I will not become fully extinguished until I have monk "
"disciples …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="140"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:167.1"
msgid ""
"Na tāvāhaṃ, pāpima, parinibbāyissāmi, yāva me bhikkhuniyo na sāvikā "
"bhavissanti viyattā vinītā visāradā bahussutā dhammadharā "
"dhammānudhammappaṭipannā sāmīcippaṭipannā anudhammacāriniyo, sakaṃ "
"ācariyakaṃ uggahetvā ācikkhissanti desessanti paññapessanti paṭṭhapessanti "
"vivarissanti vibhajissanti uttānīkarissanti, uppannaṃ parappavādaṃ "
"sahadhammena suniggahitaṃ niggahetvā sappāṭihāriyaṃ dhammaṃ desessanti."
msgstr "nun disciples …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="141"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:168.1"
msgid ""
"Na tāvāhaṃ, pāpima, parinibbāyissāmi, yāva me upāsakā na sāvakā bhavissanti "
"viyattā vinītā visāradā bahussutā dhammadharā dhammānudhammappaṭipannā "
"sāmīcippaṭipannā anudhammacārino, sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ uggahetvā ācikkhissanti "
"desessanti paññapessanti paṭṭhapessanti vivarissanti vibhajissanti "
"uttānīkarissanti, uppannaṃ parappavādaṃ sahadhammena suniggahitaṃ niggahetvā "
"sappāṭihāriyaṃ dhammaṃ desessanti."
msgstr "layman disciples …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="142"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:169.1"
msgid ""
"Na tāvāhaṃ, pāpima, parinibbāyissāmi, yāva me upāsikā na sāvikā bhavissanti "
"viyattā vinītā visāradā bahussutā dhammadharā dhammānudhammappaṭipannā "
"sāmīcippaṭipannā anudhammacāriniyo, sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ uggahetvā ācikkhissanti "
"desessanti paññapessanti paṭṭhapessanti vivarissanti vibhajissanti "
"uttānīkarissanti, uppannaṃ parappavādaṃ sahadhammena suniggahitaṃ niggahetvā "
"sappāṭihāriyaṃ dhammaṃ desessanti."
msgstr "laywoman disciples who are competent, educated, assured, learned."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="143"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:170.1"
msgid ""
"Na tāvāhaṃ, pāpima, parinibbāyissāmi, yāva me idaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na "
"iddhañceva bhavissati phītañca vitthārikaṃ bāhujaññaṃ puthubhūtaṃ yāva "
"devamanussehi suppakāsitan’ti."
msgstr ""
"Not until my spiritual life is successful and prosperous, extensive, "
"popular, widespread, and well proclaimed wherever there are gods and humans.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="144"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.36"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.114"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:171.1"
msgid ""
"Idāneva kho, ānanda, ajja cāpāle cetiye māro pāpimā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"Today, just now at the Cāpāla shrine Māra the Wicked approached me once more "
"with the same request, reminding me of my former statement, and saying that "
"those conditions had been fulfilled."

msgctxt "dn16:171.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:171.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho, ānanda, māro pāpimā maṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:171.4"
msgid ""
"‘parinibbātu dāni, bhante, bhagavā, parinibbātu sugato, parinibbānakālo "
"dāni, bhante, bhagavato."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:171.5"
msgid "Bhāsitā kho panesā, bhante, bhagavatā vācā:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:171.6"
msgid ""
"“na tāvāhaṃ, pāpima, parinibbāyissāmi, yāva me bhikkhū na sāvakā bhavissanti "
"…"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:171.7"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:171.8"
msgid "yāva me bhikkhuniyo na sāvikā bhavissanti …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:171.9"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:171.10"
msgid "yāva me upāsakā na sāvakā bhavissanti …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:171.11"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:171.12"
msgid "yāva me upāsikā na sāvikā bhavissanti …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:171.13"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:171.14"
msgid ""
"yāva me idaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na iddhañceva bhavissati phītañca vitthārikaṃ "
"bāhujaññaṃ puthubhūtaṃ, yāva devamanussehi suppakāsitan”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:171.15"
msgid ""
"Etarahi kho pana, bhante, bhagavato brahmacariyaṃ iddhañceva phītañca "
"vitthārikaṃ bāhujaññaṃ puthubhūtaṃ, yāva devamanussehi suppakāsitaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:171.16"
msgid ""
"Parinibbātu dāni, bhante, bhagavā, parinibbātu sugato, parinibbānakālo dāni, "
"bhante, bhagavato’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="145"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.37"></a>
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:172.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, ānanda, māraṃ pāpimantaṃ etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, I said to Māra:"

msgctxt "dn16:172.2"
msgid ""
"‘appossukko tvaṃ, pāpima, hohi, na ciraṃ tathāgatassa parinibbānaṃ "
"bhavissati."
msgstr ""
"‘Relax, Wicked One. The final extinguishment of the Realized One will be "
"soon."

msgctxt "dn16:172.3"
msgid "Ito tiṇṇaṃ māsānaṃ accayena tathāgato parinibbāyissatī’ti."
msgstr "Three months from now the Realized One will finally be extinguished.’"

msgctxt "dn16:172.4"
msgid ""
"Idāneva kho, ānanda, ajja cāpāle cetiye tathāgatena satena sampajānena "
"āyusaṅkhāro ossaṭṭho”ti."
msgstr ""
"So today, just now at the Cāpāla tree shrine, mindful and aware, I "
"surrendered the life force.”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:173.1"
msgid "20. Ānandayācanakathā"
msgstr "The Appeal of Ānanda"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="146"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.38"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.115"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:174.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Ānanda said to the Buddha: "

msgctxt "dn16:174.2"
msgid ""
"“tiṭṭhatu, bhante, bhagavā kappaṃ, tiṭṭhatu sugato kappaṃ bahujanahitāya "
"bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, may the Blessed One please remain for the eon! May the Holy One please "
"remain for the eon! That would be for the welfare and happiness of many "
"people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="147"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:175.1"
msgid "“Alaṃ dāni, ānanda."
msgstr "“Enough now, Ānanda."

msgctxt "dn16:175.2"
msgid "Mā tathāgataṃ yāci, akālo dāni, ānanda, tathāgataṃ yācanāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Do not beg the Realized One. Now is not the time to beg the Realized One.”"

#. <a class="wp" id="wp3.39"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:175.3"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āyasmā ānando …"
msgstr "For a second time …"

msgctxt "dn16:175.4"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:175.5"
msgid "tatiyampi kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "For a third time, Ānanda said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn16:175.6"
msgid ""
"“tiṭṭhatu, bhante, bhagavā kappaṃ, tiṭṭhatu sugato kappaṃ bahujanahitāya "
"bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, may the Blessed One please remain for the eon! May the Holy One please "
"remain for the eon! That would be for the welfare and happiness of many "
"people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="148"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:176.1"
msgid "“Saddahasi tvaṃ, ānanda, tathāgatassa bodhin”ti?"
msgstr "“Ānanda, do you have faith in the Realized One’s awakening?”"

msgctxt "dn16:176.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

msgctxt "dn16:176.3"
msgid ""
"“Atha kiñcarahi tvaṃ, ānanda, tathāgataṃ yāvatatiyakaṃ abhinippīḷesī”ti? <a "
"class=\"wp\" id=\"wp3.40\"></a>“"
msgstr "“Then why do you keep pressing me up to the third time?”"

msgctxt "dn16:176.4"
msgid "Sammukhā metaṃ, bhante, bhagavato sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ:"
msgstr "“Sir, I have heard and learned this directly from the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn16:176.5"
msgid ""
"‘yassa kassaci, ānanda, cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā yānīkatā "
"vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā, so ākaṅkhamāno kappaṃ vā "
"tiṭṭheyya kappāvasesaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"‘Whoever has developed and cultivated the four bases for psychic power—made "
"them a vehicle and a basis, kept them up, consolidated them, and properly "
"implemented them—may, if they wish, live on for the eon or what’s left of "
"the eon."

msgctxt "dn16:176.6"
msgid ""
"Tathāgatassa kho, ānanda, cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā yānīkatā "
"vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā."
msgstr ""
"The Realized One has developed and cultivated the four bases for psychic "
"power, made them a vehicle and a basis, kept them up, consolidated them, and "
"properly implemented them. "

msgctxt "dn16:176.7"
msgid ""
"So ākaṅkhamāno, ānanda, tathāgato kappaṃ vā tiṭṭheyya kappāvasesaṃ vā’”ti."
msgstr ""
"If he wished, the Realized One could live on for the eon or what’s left of "
"the eon.’"

msgctxt "dn16:176.8"
msgid "“Saddahasi tvaṃ, ānandā”ti?"
msgstr "“Do you have faith, Ānanda?”"

msgctxt "dn16:176.9"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "dn16:176.10"
msgid ""
"“Tasmātihānanda, tuyhevetaṃ dukkaṭaṃ, tuyhevetaṃ aparaddhaṃ, yaṃ tvaṃ "
"tathāgatena evaṃ oḷārike nimitte kayiramāne oḷārike obhāse kayiramāne "
"nāsakkhi paṭivijjhituṃ, na tathāgataṃ yāci:"
msgstr ""
"Therefore, Ānanda, the misdeed is yours alone, the mistake is yours alone. "
"For even though the Realized One dropped such an obvious hint, such a clear "
"sign, you didn’t beg me to remain for the eon, or what’s left of it."

msgctxt "dn16:176.11"
msgid ""
"‘tiṭṭhatu, bhante, bhagavā kappaṃ, tiṭṭhatu sugato kappaṃ bahujanahitāya "
"bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:176.12"
msgid ""
"Sace tvaṃ, ānanda, tathāgataṃ yāceyyāsi, dveva te vācā tathāgato "
"paṭikkhipeyya, atha tatiyakaṃ adhivāseyya."
msgstr ""
"If you had begged me, I would have refused you twice, but consented on the "
"third time."

msgctxt "dn16:176.13"
msgid "Tasmātihānanda, tuyhevetaṃ dukkaṭaṃ, tuyhevetaṃ aparaddhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Therefore, Ānanda, the misdeed is yours alone, the mistake is yours alone."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="149"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.41"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.116"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:177.1"
msgid "Ekamidāhaṃ, ānanda, samayaṃ rājagahe viharāmi gijjhakūṭe pabbate."
msgstr ""
"Ānanda, this one time I was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak "
"Mountain."

msgctxt "dn16:177.2"
msgid "Tatrāpi kho tāhaṃ, ānanda, āmantesiṃ:"
msgstr "There I said to you:"

msgctxt "dn16:177.3"
msgid "‘ramaṇīyaṃ, ānanda, rājagahaṃ, ramaṇīyo, ānanda, gijjhakūṭo pabbato."
msgstr "‘Ānanda, Rājagaha is lovely, and so is the Vulture’s Peak."

msgctxt "dn16:177.4"
msgid ""
"Yassa kassaci, ānanda, cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā yānīkatā "
"vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā, so ākaṅkhamāno kappaṃ vā "
"tiṭṭheyya kappāvasesaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"Whoever has developed and cultivated the four bases for psychic power—made "
"them a vehicle and a basis, kept them up, consolidated them, and properly "
"implemented them—may, if they wish, live on for the eon or what’s left of "
"the eon."

msgctxt "dn16:177.5"
msgid ""
"Tathāgatassa kho, ānanda, cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā yānīkatā "
"vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā, so ākaṅkhamāno, ānanda, "
"tathāgato kappaṃ vā tiṭṭheyya kappāvasesaṃ vā’ti."
msgstr ""
"The Realized One has developed and cultivated the four bases for psychic "
"power, made them a vehicle and a basis, kept them up, consolidated them, and "
"properly implemented them. If he wished, the Realized One could live on for "
"the eon or what’s left of the eon.’"

msgctxt "dn16:177.6"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho tvaṃ, ānanda, tathāgatena oḷārike nimitte kayiramāne oḷārike "
"obhāse kayiramāne nāsakkhi paṭivijjhituṃ, na tathāgataṃ yāci:"
msgstr ""
"But you didn’t get it, even though I dropped such an obvious hint, such a "
"clear sign. You didn’t beg me to remain for the eon, or what’s left of it."

msgctxt "dn16:177.7"
msgid ""
"‘tiṭṭhatu, bhante, bhagavā kappaṃ, tiṭṭhatu sugato kappaṃ bahujanahitāya "
"bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:177.8"
msgid ""
"Sace tvaṃ, ānanda, tathāgataṃ yāceyyāsi, dveva te vācā tathāgato "
"paṭikkhipeyya, atha tatiyakaṃ adhivāseyya."
msgstr ""
"If you had begged me, I would have refused you twice, but consented on the "
"third time."

msgctxt "dn16:177.9"
msgid "Tasmātihānanda, tuyhevetaṃ dukkaṭaṃ, tuyhevetaṃ aparaddhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Therefore, Ānanda, the misdeed is yours alone, the mistake is yours alone."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="150"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.42"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.117"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:178.1"
msgid "Ekamidāhaṃ, ānanda, samayaṃ tattheva rājagahe viharāmi gotamanigrodhe …"
msgstr ""
"Ānanda, this one time I was staying right there near Rājagaha, at the Gotama "
"banyan tree …"

msgctxt "dn16:178.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:178.3"
msgid "tattheva rājagahe viharāmi corapapāte …"
msgstr "at Bandit’s Cliff …"

msgctxt "dn16:178.4"
msgid "tattheva rājagahe viharāmi vebhārapasse sattapaṇṇiguhāyaṃ …"
msgstr "in the Sattapaṇṇi cave on the slopes of Vebhara …"

msgctxt "dn16:178.5"
msgid "tattheva rājagahe viharāmi isigilipasse kāḷasilāyaṃ …"
msgstr "at the Black rock on the slopes of Isigili …"

msgctxt "dn16:178.6"
msgid "tattheva rājagahe viharāmi sītavane sappasoṇḍikapabbhāre …"
msgstr "in the Cool Wood, under the Snake’s Hood Grotto …"

msgctxt "dn16:178.7"
msgid "tattheva rājagahe viharāmi tapodārāme …"
msgstr "in the Hot Springs Monastery …"

msgctxt "dn16:178.8"
msgid "tattheva rājagahe viharāmi veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe …"
msgstr "in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground …"

msgctxt "dn16:178.9"
msgid "tattheva rājagahe viharāmi jīvakambavane …"
msgstr "in Jīvaka’s mango grove …"

msgctxt "dn16:178.10"
msgid "tattheva rājagahe viharāmi maddakucchismiṃ migadāye."
msgstr "in the Maddakucchi deer park …"

#. <a class="wp" id="wp3.43"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:178.11"
msgid "Tatrāpi kho tāhaṃ, ānanda, āmantesiṃ:"
msgstr "And in each place I said to you:"

msgctxt "dn16:178.12"
msgid ""
"‘ramaṇīyaṃ, ānanda, rājagahaṃ, ramaṇīyo gijjhakūṭo pabbato, ramaṇīyo "
"gotamanigrodho, ramaṇīyo corapapāto, ramaṇīyā vebhārapasse sattapaṇṇiguhā, "
"ramaṇīyā isigilipasse kāḷasilā, ramaṇīyo sītavane sappasoṇḍikapabbhāro, "
"ramaṇīyo tapodārāmo, ramaṇīyo veḷuvane kalandakanivāpo, ramaṇīyaṃ "
"jīvakambavanaṃ, ramaṇīyo maddakucchismiṃ migadāyo."
msgstr "‘Ānanda, Rājagaha is lovely, and so are all these places. …"

#. <a class="wp" id="wp3.44"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:178.13"
msgid ""
"Yassa kassaci, ānanda, cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā yānīkatā "
"vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:178.14"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:178.15"
msgid "ākaṅkhamāno, ānanda, tathāgato kappaṃ vā tiṭṭheyya kappāvasesaṃ vā’ti."
msgstr ""
"If he wished, the Realized One could live on for the eon or what’s left of "
"the eon.’"

msgctxt "dn16:178.16"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho tvaṃ, ānanda, tathāgatena oḷārike nimitte kayiramāne oḷārike "
"obhāse kayiramāne nāsakkhi paṭivijjhituṃ, na tathāgataṃ yāci:"
msgstr ""
"But you didn’t get it, even though I dropped such an obvious hint, such a "
"clear sign. You didn’t beg me to remain for the eon, or what’s left of it."

msgctxt "dn16:178.17"
msgid ""
"‘tiṭṭhatu, bhante, bhagavā kappaṃ, tiṭṭhatu sugato kappaṃ bahujanahitāya "
"bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:178.18"
msgid ""
"Sace tvaṃ, ānanda, tathāgataṃ yāceyyāsi, dveva te vācā tathāgato "
"paṭikkhipeyya, atha tatiyakaṃ adhivāseyya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:178.19"
msgid "Tasmātihānanda, tuyhevetaṃ dukkaṭaṃ, tuyhevetaṃ aparaddhaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="151"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.45"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:179.1"
msgid "Ekamidāhaṃ, ānanda, samayaṃ idheva vesāliyaṃ viharāmi udene cetiye."
msgstr ""
"Ānanda, this one time I was staying right here near Vesālī, at the Udena "
"shrine …"

msgctxt "dn16:179.2"
msgid "Tatrāpi kho tāhaṃ, ānanda, āmantesiṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:179.3"
msgid "‘ramaṇīyā, ānanda, vesālī, ramaṇīyaṃ udenaṃ cetiyaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:179.4"
msgid ""
"Yassa kassaci, ānanda, cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā yānīkatā "
"vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā, so ākaṅkhamāno kappaṃ vā "
"tiṭṭheyya kappāvasesaṃ vā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:179.5"
msgid ""
"Tathāgatassa kho, ānanda, cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā yānīkatā "
"vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā, so ākaṅkhamāno, ānanda, "
"tathāgato kappaṃ vā tiṭṭheyya kappāvasesaṃ vā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:179.6"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho tvaṃ, ānanda, tathāgatena oḷārike nimitte kayiramāne oḷārike "
"obhāse kayiramāne nāsakkhi paṭivijjhituṃ, na tathāgataṃ yāci:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:179.7"
msgid ""
"‘tiṭṭhatu, bhante, bhagavā kappaṃ, tiṭṭhatu sugato kappaṃ bahujanahitāya "
"bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:179.8"
msgid ""
"Sace tvaṃ, ānanda, tathāgataṃ yāceyyāsi, dveva te vācā tathāgato "
"paṭikkhipeyya, atha tatiyakaṃ adhivāseyya, tasmātihānanda, tuyhevetaṃ "
"dukkaṭaṃ, tuyhevetaṃ aparaddhaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="152"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.46"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.118"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:180.1"
msgid "Ekamidāhaṃ, ānanda, samayaṃ idheva vesāliyaṃ viharāmi gotamake cetiye …"
msgstr "at the Gotamaka shrine …"

msgctxt "dn16:180.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:180.3"
msgid "idheva vesāliyaṃ viharāmi sattambe cetiye …"
msgstr "at the Sattamba shrine …"

msgctxt "dn16:180.4"
msgid "idheva vesāliyaṃ viharāmi bahuputte cetiye …"
msgstr "at the Many Sons shrine …"

msgctxt "dn16:180.5"
msgid "idheva vesāliyaṃ viharāmi sārandade cetiye …"
msgstr "at the Sārandada shrine …"

#. <a class="wp" id="wp3.47"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:180.6"
msgid "idāneva kho tāhaṃ, ānanda, ajja cāpāle cetiye āmantesiṃ:"
msgstr "and just now, today at the Cāpāla shrine. There I said to you:"

msgctxt "dn16:180.7"
msgid ""
"‘ramaṇīyā, ānanda, vesālī, ramaṇīyaṃ udenaṃ cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ gotamakaṃ "
"cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ sattambaṃ cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ bahuputtaṃ cetiyaṃ, "
"ramaṇīyaṃ sārandadaṃ cetiyaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ cāpālaṃ cetiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Ānanda, Vesālī is lovely. And the Udena, Gotamaka, Sattamba, and Bahuputta, "
"Sārandada, and Cāpāla tree shrines are all lovely."

msgctxt "dn16:180.8"
msgid ""
"Yassa kassaci, ānanda, cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā yānīkatā "
"vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā, so ākaṅkhamāno kappaṃ vā "
"tiṭṭheyya kappāvasesaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"Whoever has developed and cultivated the four bases for psychic power—made "
"them a vehicle and a basis, kept them up, consolidated them, and properly "
"implemented them—may, if they wish, live on for the eon or what’s left of "
"the eon."

msgctxt "dn16:180.9"
msgid ""
"Tathāgatassa kho, ānanda, cattāro iddhipādā bhāvitā bahulīkatā yānīkatā "
"vatthukatā anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā, so ākaṅkhamāno, ānanda, "
"tathāgato kappaṃ vā tiṭṭheyya kappāvasesaṃ vā’ti."
msgstr ""
"The Realized One has developed and cultivated the four bases for psychic "
"power, made them a vehicle and a basis, kept them up, consolidated them, and "
"properly implemented them. If he wished, the Realized One could live on for "
"the eon or what’s left of the eon.’"

msgctxt "dn16:180.10"
msgid ""
"Evampi kho tvaṃ, ānanda, tathāgatena oḷārike nimitte kayiramāne oḷārike "
"obhāse kayiramāne nāsakkhi paṭivijjhituṃ, na tathāgataṃ yāci:"
msgstr ""
"But you didn’t get it, even though I dropped such an obvious hint, such a "
"clear sign. You didn’t beg me to remain for the eon, or what’s left of it:"

msgctxt "dn16:180.11"
msgid ""
"‘tiṭṭhatu bhagavā kappaṃ, tiṭṭhatu sugato kappaṃ bahujanahitāya "
"bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Sir, may the Blessed One please remain for the eon! May the Holy One please "
"remain for the eon! That would be for the welfare and happiness of many "
"people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans.’"

msgctxt "dn16:180.12"
msgid ""
"Sace tvaṃ, ānanda, tathāgataṃ yāceyyāsi, dveva te vācā tathāgato "
"paṭikkhipeyya, atha tatiyakaṃ adhivāseyya."
msgstr ""
"If you had begged me, I would have refused you twice, but consented on the "
"third time."

msgctxt "dn16:180.13"
msgid "Tasmātihānanda, tuyhevetaṃ dukkaṭaṃ, tuyhevetaṃ aparaddhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Therefore, Ānanda, the misdeed is yours alone, the mistake is yours alone."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="153"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.48"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.119"></a>
#. VAR: paṭikacceva → paṭigacceva (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: etaṃ → evaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:181.1"
msgid "Nanu etaṃ, ānanda, mayā paṭikacceva akkhātaṃ:"
msgstr "Did I not prepare for this when I explained that"

msgctxt "dn16:181.2"
msgid "‘sabbeheva piyehi manāpehi nānābhāvo vinābhāvo aññathābhāvo."
msgstr "we must be parted and separated from all we hold dear and beloved?"

msgctxt "dn16:181.3"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kutettha, ānanda, labbhā, yaṃ taṃ jātaṃ bhūtaṃ saṅkhataṃ palokadhammaṃ, "
"taṃ vata mā palujjīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati’."
msgstr ""
"How could anyone make it so that what is born, created, conditioned, and "
"liable to fall apart should not fall apart?"

msgctxt "dn16:181.4"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho panetaṃ, ānanda, tathāgatena cattaṃ vantaṃ muttaṃ pahīnaṃ "
"paṭinissaṭṭhaṃ ossaṭṭho āyusaṅkhāro, ekaṃsena vācā bhāsitā:"
msgstr ""
"The Realized One has discarded, eliminated, released, given up, "
"relinquished, and surrendered the life force. He has definitively stated:"

msgctxt "dn16:181.5"
msgid "‘na ciraṃ tathāgatassa parinibbānaṃ bhavissati."
msgstr "‘The final extinguishment of the Realized One will be soon."

msgctxt "dn16:181.6"
msgid "Ito tiṇṇaṃ māsānaṃ accayena tathāgato parinibbāyissatī’ti."
msgstr "Three months from now the Realized One will finally be extinguished.’"

# paccāvamissati has several variants, but this should be the correct one. It occurs in Ja 69 and Ja 509, where it is the opposite of vamati (which is in the passage above), i.e. you wouldn't swallow back what you have vomited out. Comm: Puna paccāvamissatīti yaṃ cattaṃ vantaṃ, taṃ vata puna paṭikhādissatīti attho
#. VAR: Tañca → tañcetaṃ (bj) | taṃ vacanaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:181.7"
msgid "Tañca tathāgato jīvitahetu puna paccāvamissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"It’s not possible for the Realized One, for the sake of life, to take back "
"the life force once it has been given up like that."

msgctxt "dn16:181.8"
msgid "Āyāmānanda, yena mahāvanaṃ kūṭāgārasālā tenupasaṅkamissāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Come, Ānanda, let’s go to the Great Wood, the hall with the peaked roof.”"

msgctxt "dn16:181.9"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="154"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.49"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:182.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ yena mahāvanaṃ kūṭāgārasālā "
"tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "So the Buddha went with Ānanda to the hall with the peaked roof,"

msgctxt "dn16:182.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

msgctxt "dn16:182.3"
msgid ""
"“gaccha tvaṃ, ānanda, yāvatikā bhikkhū vesāliṃ upanissāya viharanti, te "
"sabbe upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ sannipātehī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Go, Ānanda, gather all the mendicants staying in the vicinity of Vesālī "
"together in the assembly hall.”"

msgctxt "dn16:182.4"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paṭissutvā yāvatikā bhikkhū "
"vesāliṃ upanissāya viharanti, te sabbe upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ sannipātetvā yena "
"bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"“Yes, sir,” relied Ānanda. He did what the Buddha asked, went up to him,"

msgctxt "dn16:182.5"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr "bowed, stood to one side,"

msgctxt "dn16:182.6"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

msgctxt "dn16:182.7"
msgid ""
"“sannipatito, bhante, bhikkhusaṅgho, yassadāni, bhante, bhagavā kālaṃ "
"maññatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, the mendicant Sangha has assembled. Please, sir, go at your "
"convenience.” "

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn16:183.1"
msgid "()"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="155"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3.50"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.120"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:184.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā yenupaṭṭhānasālā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then the Buddha went to the assembly hall,"

msgctxt "dn16:184.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "where he sat on the seat spread out"

msgctxt "dn16:184.3"
msgid "Nisajja kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "and addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "dn16:184.4"
msgid ""
"“tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ye te mayā dhammā abhiññā desitā, te vo sādhukaṃ "
"uggahetvā āsevitabbā bhāvetabbā bahulīkātabbā, yathayidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ "
"addhaniyaṃ assa ciraṭṭhitikaṃ, tadassa bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya "
"lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“So, mendicants, having carefully memorized those things I have taught you "
"from my direct knowledge, you should cultivate, develop, and make much of "
"them so that this spiritual practice may last for a long time. That would be "
"for the welfare and happiness of many people, for the benefit, welfare, and "
"happiness of gods and humans."

msgctxt "dn16:184.5"
msgid ""
"Katame ca te, bhikkhave, dhammā mayā abhiññā desitā, ye vo sādhukaṃ "
"uggahetvā āsevitabbā bhāvetabbā bahulīkātabbā, yathayidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ "
"addhaniyaṃ assa ciraṭṭhitikaṃ, tadassa bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya "
"lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānaṃ."
msgstr "And what are those things I have taught from my direct knowledge?"

msgctxt "dn16:184.6"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "They are:"

msgctxt "dn16:184.7"
msgid ""
"cattāro satipaṭṭhānā, cattāro sammappadhānā, cattāro iddhipādā, "
"pañcindriyāni, pañca balāni, satta bojjhaṅgā, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo."
msgstr ""
"the four kinds of mindfulness meditation, the four right endeavors, the four "
"bases for psychic power, the five faculties, the five powers, the seven "
"factors of awakening, and the eightfold noble path."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp3.51"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:184.8"
msgid ""
"Ime kho te, bhikkhave, dhammā mayā abhiññā desitā, ye vo sādhukaṃ uggahetvā "
"āsevitabbā bhāvetabbā bahulīkātabbā, yathayidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ addhaniyaṃ "
"assa ciraṭṭhitikaṃ, tadassa bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya "
"atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan”ti."
msgstr ""
"These are the things I have taught from my direct knowledge. Having "
"carefully memorized them, you should cultivate, develop, and make much of "
"them so that this spiritual practice may last for a long time. That would be "
"for the welfare and happiness of many people, for the benefit, welfare, and "
"happiness of gods and humans.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="156"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:185.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to the mendicants:"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:185.2"
msgid ""
"“handa dāni, bhikkhave, āmantayāmi vo, vayadhammā saṅkhārā, appamādena "
"sampādetha."
msgstr ""
"“Come now, mendicants, I say to you all: Conditions fall apart. Persist with "
"diligence."

msgctxt "dn16:185.3"
msgid "Naciraṃ tathāgatassa parinibbānaṃ bhavissati."
msgstr "The final extinguishment of the Realized One will be soon."

msgctxt "dn16:185.4"
msgid "Ito tiṇṇaṃ māsānaṃ accayena tathāgato parinibbāyissatī”ti."
msgstr "Three months from now the Realized One will finally be extinguished.” "

msgctxt "dn16:185.5"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "This is what the Buddha said."

#. VAR: satthā → ito paraṃ s1-3 potthakesu evampi pāṭho dissati-- \
msgctxt "dn16:185.6"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="157"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:186.1"
msgid "“Paripakko vayo mayhaṃ,"
msgstr "“I’ve reached a ripe old age,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:186.2"
msgid "parittaṃ mama jīvitaṃ;"
msgstr "and little of my life is left."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:186.3"
msgid "Pahāya vo gamissāmi,"
msgstr "Having given it up, I’ll depart;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:186.4"
msgid "kataṃ me saraṇamattano."
msgstr "I’ve made a refuge for myself."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="158"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:187.1"
msgid "Appamattā satīmanto,"
msgstr "Diligent and mindful,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:187.2"
msgid "susīlā hotha bhikkhavo;"
msgstr "be of good virtues, mendicants!"

# Cp. AN 4.22
#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:187.3"
msgid "Susamāhitasaṅkappā,"
msgstr "With well-settled thoughts,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:187.4"
msgid "sacittamanurakkhatha."
msgstr "take good care of your minds."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="159"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.121"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:188.1"
msgid "Yo imasmiṃ dhammavinaye,"
msgstr "Whoever meditates diligently"

#. <br>
#. VAR: vihassati → vihessati (si, pts1) | viharissati (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn16:188.2"
msgid "appamatto vihassati;"
msgstr "in this teaching and training,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:188.3"
msgid "Pahāya jātisaṃsāraṃ,"
msgstr "giving up transmigration through rebirths,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:188.4"
msgid "dukkhassantaṃ karissatī”ti."
msgstr "will make an end to suffering.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn16:189.1"
msgid "Tatiyo bhāṇavāro."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:190.1"
msgid "21. Nāgāpalokita"
msgstr "The Elephant Look"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="160"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.1"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.122"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:191.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya vesāliṃ piṇḍāya "
"pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha got dressed in the morning and, taking his bowl and robes, "
"entered Vesālī for alms."

msgctxt "dn16:191.2"
msgid ""
"Vesāliyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto nāgāpalokitaṃ "
"vesāliṃ apaloketvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"Then, after the meal, when he had returned from alms-round, he turned his "
"whole body, the way that elephants do, to look back at Vesālī. He Venerable "
"Ānanda:"

msgctxt "dn16:191.3"
msgid "“idaṃ pacchimakaṃ, ānanda, tathāgatassa vesāliyā dassanaṃ bhavissati."
msgstr "“Ānanda, this will be the last time the Realized One sees Vesālī."

#. VAR: bhaṇḍagāmo → bhaṇḍaggāmo (km) | bhaṇḍugāmo (mr)
msgctxt "dn16:191.4"
msgid "Āyāmānanda, yena bhaṇḍagāmo tenupasaṅkamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "Come, Ānanda, let’s go to Bhaṇḍagāma.”"

msgctxt "dn16:191.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="161"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.2"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.123"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:192.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ yena bhaṇḍagāmo tadavasari."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants arrived at "
"Bhaṇḍagāma,"

msgctxt "dn16:192.2"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā bhaṇḍagāme viharati."
msgstr "and stayed on there."

msgctxt "dn16:192.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants: "

msgctxt "dn16:192.4"
msgid ""
"“catunnaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammānaṃ ananubodhā appaṭivedhā evamidaṃ "
"dīghamaddhānaṃ sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva tumhākañca."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, not understanding and not penetrating four things, both you and "
"I have wandered and transmigrated for such a very long time."

msgctxt "dn16:192.5"
msgid "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "dn16:192.6"
msgid ""
"Ariyassa, bhikkhave, sīlassa ananubodhā appaṭivedhā evamidaṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ "
"sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva tumhākañca."
msgstr "Noble ethics,"

msgctxt "dn16:192.7"
msgid ""
"Ariyassa, bhikkhave, samādhissa ananubodhā appaṭivedhā evamidaṃ "
"dīghamaddhānaṃ sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva tumhākañca."
msgstr "immersion,"

msgctxt "dn16:192.8"
msgid ""
"Ariyāya, bhikkhave, paññāya ananubodhā appaṭivedhā evamidaṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ "
"sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva tumhākañca."
msgstr "wisdom,"

msgctxt "dn16:192.9"
msgid ""
"Ariyāya, bhikkhave, vimuttiyā ananubodhā appaṭivedhā evamidaṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ "
"sandhāvitaṃ saṃsaritaṃ mamañceva tumhākañca."
msgstr "and freedom."

msgctxt "dn16:192.10"
msgid ""
"Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyaṃ sīlaṃ anubuddhaṃ paṭividdhaṃ, ariyo samādhi "
"anubuddho paṭividdho, ariyā paññā anubuddhā paṭividdhā, ariyā vimutti "
"anubuddhā paṭividdhā, ucchinnā bhavataṇhā, khīṇā bhavanetti, natthi dāni "
"punabbhavo”ti."
msgstr ""
"This noble ethics, samādhi, wisdom, and freedom have been understood and "
"penetrated. Craving to be reborn has been cut off; the attachment to being "
"reborn is ended; now there are no more future lives.”"

#. <a class="wp" id="wp4.3"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:192.11"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "This is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "dn16:192.12"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="162"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:193.1"
msgid "“Sīlaṃ samādhi paññā ca,"
msgstr "“Ethics, immersion, and wisdom, "

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:193.2"
msgid "vimutti ca anuttarā;"
msgstr "and the supreme freedom: "

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:193.3"
msgid "Anubuddhā ime dhammā,"
msgstr "these things have been understood"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:193.4"
msgid "gotamena yasassinā."
msgstr "by Gotama the renowned. "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="163"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:194.1"
msgid "Iti buddho abhiññāya,"
msgstr "And so the Buddha, having insight,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:194.2"
msgid "dhammamakkhāsi bhikkhunaṃ;"
msgstr "explained this teaching to the mendicants."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:194.3"
msgid "Dukkhassantakaro satthā,"
msgstr "The teacher made an end of suffering,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:194.4"
msgid "cakkhumā parinibbuto”ti."
msgstr "seeing clearly, he is extinguished.” "

#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="164"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.4"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:195.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrāpi sudaṃ bhagavā bhaṇḍagāme viharanto etadeva bahulaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ "
"dhammiṃ kathaṃ karoti:"
msgstr ""
"And while staying there, too, he often gave this Dhamma talk to the "
"mendicants:"

msgctxt "dn16:195.2"
msgid "“iti sīlaṃ, iti samādhi, iti paññā."
msgstr "“Such is ethics, such is immersion, such is wisdom."

msgctxt "dn16:195.3"
msgid "Sīlaparibhāvito samādhi mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso."
msgstr "When immersion is imbued with ethics it’s very fruitful and beneficial."

msgctxt "dn16:195.4"
msgid "Samādhiparibhāvitā paññā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā."
msgstr "When wisdom is imbued with immersion it’s very fruitful and beneficial."

msgctxt "dn16:195.5"
msgid "Paññāparibhāvitaṃ cittaṃ sammadeva āsavehi vimuccati, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"When the mind is imbued with wisdom it is rightly freed from the "
"defilements, namely,"

msgctxt "dn16:195.6"
msgid "kāmāsavā, bhavāsavā, avijjāsavā”ti."
msgstr "the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:196.1"
msgid "22. Catumahāpadesakathā"
msgstr "The Four Great References"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="165"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.5"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.124"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:197.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā bhaṇḍagāme yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ "
"āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha had stayed in Bhaṇḍagāma as long as he wished, he addressed "
"Ānanda:"

msgctxt "dn16:197.2"
msgid ""
"“āyāmānanda, yena hatthigāmo, yena ambagāmo, yena jambugāmo, yena "
"bhoganagaraṃ tenupasaṅkamissāmā”ti. <a class=\"wp\" id=\"wp4.6\"></a>“"
msgstr "Come, Ānanda, let’s go to Hatthigāma, to Jambugāma, to Bhoganagara.”"

msgctxt "dn16:197.3"
msgid "Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

msgctxt "dn16:197.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ yena bhoganagaraṃ tadavasari."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants arrived at "
"Bhoganagara,"

#. <a class="wp" id="wp4.7"></a>
#. VAR: ānande → anande (pts1) | sānandare (mr)
msgctxt "dn16:197.5"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā bhoganagare viharati ānande cetiye."
msgstr "where he stayed at the Ānanda shrine."

msgctxt "dn16:197.6"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "dn16:197.7"
msgid ""
"“cattārome, bhikkhave, mahāpadese desessāmi, taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ "
"manasikarotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, I will teach you the four great references. Listen and pay "
"close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "dn16:197.8"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied.  "

msgctxt "dn16:197.9"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:  "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="166"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.8"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:198.1"
msgid "“Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "“Take a mendicant who says: "

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:198.2"
msgid ""
"‘sammukhā metaṃ, āvuso, bhagavato sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ, ayaṃ dhammo "
"ayaṃ vinayo idaṃ satthusāsanan’ti."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend, I have heard and learned this directly from the Buddha: this is "
"the teaching, this is the training, this is the Teacher’s instruction.’"

msgctxt "dn16:198.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno bhāsitaṃ neva abhinanditabbaṃ nappaṭikkositabbaṃ."
msgstr "You should neither approve nor dismiss that mendicant’s statement."

#. VAR: osāretabbāni → otāretabbāni (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:198.4"
msgid ""
"Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā tāni padabyañjanāni sādhukaṃ uggahetvā sutte "
"osāretabbāni, vinaye sandassetabbāni."
msgstr ""
"Instead, you should carefully memorize those words and phrases, then check "
"if they’re included in the discourses or found in the texts on monastic "
"training."

#. VAR: osaranti → otaranti (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: osāriyamānāni → otāriyamānāni (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:198.5"
msgid ""
"Tāni ce sutte osāriyamānāni vinaye sandassiyamānāni na ceva sutte osaranti, "
"na ca vinaye sandissanti, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"If they’re not included in the discourses or found in the texts on monastic "
"training, you should draw the conclusion:"

msgctxt "dn16:198.6"
msgid "‘addhā idaṃ na ceva tassa bhagavato vacanaṃ;"
msgstr "‘Clearly this is not the word of the Buddha."

msgctxt "dn16:198.7"
msgid "imassa ca bhikkhuno duggahitan’ti."
msgstr "It has been incorrectly memorized by that mendicant.’"

msgctxt "dn16:198.8"
msgid "Iti hetaṃ, bhikkhave, chaḍḍeyyātha."
msgstr "And so you should reject it."

msgctxt "dn16:198.9"
msgid ""
"Tāni ce sutte osāriyamānāni vinaye sandassiyamānāni sutte ceva osaranti, "
"vinaye ca sandissanti, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"If they are included in the discourses or found in the texts on monastic "
"training, you should draw the conclusion:"

msgctxt "dn16:198.10"
msgid "‘addhā idaṃ tassa bhagavato vacanaṃ;"
msgstr "‘Clearly this is the word of the Buddha."

msgctxt "dn16:198.11"
msgid "imassa ca bhikkhuno suggahitan’ti."
msgstr "It has been correctly memorized by that mendicant.’"

# See my note on this phrase in AN 4.180.
msgctxt "dn16:198.12"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamaṃ mahāpadesaṃ dhāreyyātha. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(1)</span>"
msgstr "You should remember it. This is the first great reference."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="167"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.9"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.125"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:199.1"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "Take another mendicant who says: "

msgctxt "dn16:199.2"
msgid "‘amukasmiṃ nāma āvāse saṅgho viharati sathero sapāmokkho."
msgstr "‘In such-and-such monastery lives a Saṅgha with seniors and leaders."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:199.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa me saṅghassa sammukhā sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ, ayaṃ dhammo ayaṃ "
"vinayo idaṃ satthusāsanan’ti."
msgstr ""
"I’ve heard and learned this directly from that Saṅgha: this is the teaching, "
"this is the training, this is the Teacher’s instruction.’"

msgctxt "dn16:199.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno bhāsitaṃ neva abhinanditabbaṃ nappaṭikkositabbaṃ."
msgstr "You should neither approve nor dismiss that mendicant’s statement."

msgctxt "dn16:199.5"
msgid ""
"Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā tāni padabyañjanāni sādhukaṃ uggahetvā sutte "
"osāretabbāni, vinaye sandassetabbāni."
msgstr ""
"Instead, you should carefully memorize those words and phrases, then check "
"if they’re included in the discourses or found in the texts on monastic "
"training."

msgctxt "dn16:199.6"
msgid ""
"Tāni ce sutte osāriyamānāni vinaye sandassiyamānāni na ceva sutte osaranti, "
"na ca vinaye sandissanti, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"If they’re not included in the discourses or found in the texts on monastic "
"training, you should draw the conclusion:"

msgctxt "dn16:199.7"
msgid "‘addhā idaṃ na ceva tassa bhagavato vacanaṃ;"
msgstr "‘Clearly this is not the word of the Buddha."

msgctxt "dn16:199.8"
msgid "tassa ca saṅghassa duggahitan’ti."
msgstr "It has been incorrectly memorized by that Saṅgha.’"

msgctxt "dn16:199.9"
msgid "Itihetaṃ, bhikkhave, chaḍḍeyyātha."
msgstr "And so you should reject it."

msgctxt "dn16:199.10"
msgid ""
"Tāni ce sutte osāriyamānāni vinaye sandassiyamānāni sutte ceva osaranti, "
"vinaye ca sandissanti, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"If they are included in the discourses or found in the texts on monastic "
"training, you should draw the conclusion:"

msgctxt "dn16:199.11"
msgid "‘addhā idaṃ tassa bhagavato vacanaṃ;"
msgstr "‘Clearly this is the word of the Buddha."

msgctxt "dn16:199.12"
msgid "tassa ca saṅghassa suggahitan’ti."
msgstr "It has been correctly memorized by that Saṅgha.’"

msgctxt "dn16:199.13"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyaṃ mahāpadesaṃ dhāreyyātha. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(2)</span>"
msgstr "You should remember it. This is the second great reference."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="168"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.10"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:200.1"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "Take another mendicant who says: "

msgctxt "dn16:200.2"
msgid ""
"‘amukasmiṃ nāma āvāse sambahulā therā bhikkhū viharanti bahussutā āgatāgamā "
"dhammadharā vinayadharā mātikādharā."
msgstr ""
"‘In such-and-such monastery there are several senior mendicants who are very "
"learned, knowledgeable in the scriptures, who have memorized the teachings, "
"the texts on monastic training, and the outlines."

msgctxt "dn16:200.3"
msgid "Tesaṃ me therānaṃ sammukhā sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ—"
msgstr "I’ve heard and learned this directly from those senior mendicants:"

msgctxt "dn16:200.4"
msgid "ayaṃ dhammo ayaṃ vinayo idaṃ satthusāsanan’ti."
msgstr ""
"this is the teaching, this is the training, this is the Teacher’s "
"instruction.’"

msgctxt "dn16:200.5"
msgid "Tassa, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno bhāsitaṃ neva abhinanditabbaṃ …"
msgstr "You should neither approve nor dismiss that mendicant’s statement."

msgctxt "dn16:200.6"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""
"Instead, you should carefully memorize those words and phrases, then check "
"if they’re included in the discourses or found in the texts on monastic "
"training."

msgctxt "dn16:200.7"
msgid "na ca vinaye sandissanti, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"If they’re not included in the discourses or found in the Vinaya, you should "
"draw the conclusion:"

msgctxt "dn16:200.8"
msgid "‘addhā idaṃ na ceva tassa bhagavato vacanaṃ;"
msgstr "‘Clearly this is not the word of the Buddha."

msgctxt "dn16:200.9"
msgid "tesañca therānaṃ duggahitan’ti."
msgstr "It has been correctly memorized by those senior mendicants.’"

msgctxt "dn16:200.10"
msgid "Itihetaṃ, bhikkhave, chaḍḍeyyātha."
msgstr "And so you should reject it."

msgctxt "dn16:200.11"
msgid "Tāni ce sutte osāriyamānāni …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:200.12"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:200.13"
msgid "vinaye ca sandissanti, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"If they are included in the discourses and found in the Vinaya, you should "
"draw the conclusion:"

msgctxt "dn16:200.14"
msgid "‘addhā idaṃ tassa bhagavato vacanaṃ;"
msgstr "‘Clearly this is the word of the Buddha."

msgctxt "dn16:200.15"
msgid "tesañca therānaṃ suggahitan’ti."
msgstr "It has been correctly memorized by those senior mendicants.’"

msgctxt "dn16:200.16"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyaṃ mahāpadesaṃ dhāreyyātha. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(3)</span>"
msgstr "You should remember it. This is the third great reference."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="169"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.11"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.126"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:201.1"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "Take another mendicant who says:"

msgctxt "dn16:201.2"
msgid ""
"‘amukasmiṃ nāma āvāse eko thero bhikkhu viharati bahussuto āgatāgamo "
"dhammadharo vinayadharo mātikādharo."
msgstr ""
"‘In such-and-such monastery there is a single senior mendicant who is very "
"learned and knowledgeable in the scriptures, who has memorized the "
"teachings, the texts on monastic discipline, and the outlines."

msgctxt "dn16:201.3"
msgid "Tassa me therassa sammukhā sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ—"
msgstr "I’ve heard and learned this directly from that senior mendicant:"

msgctxt "dn16:201.4"
msgid "ayaṃ dhammo ayaṃ vinayo idaṃ satthusāsanan’ti."
msgstr ""
"this is the teaching, this is the training, this is the Teacher’s "
"instruction.’"

msgctxt "dn16:201.5"
msgid ""
"Tassa, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno bhāsitaṃ neva abhinanditabbaṃ nappaṭikkositabbaṃ."
msgstr "You should neither approve nor dismiss that mendicant’s statement."

msgctxt "dn16:201.6"
msgid ""
"Anabhinanditvā appaṭikkositvā tāni padabyañjanāni sādhukaṃ uggahetvā sutte "
"osāretabbāni, vinaye sandassetabbāni."
msgstr ""
"Instead, you should carefully memorize those words and phrases, then check "
"if they’re included in the discourses or found in the texts on monastic "
"training."

msgctxt "dn16:201.7"
msgid ""
"Tāni ce sutte osāriyamānāni vinaye sandassiyamānāni na ceva sutte osaranti, "
"na ca vinaye sandissanti, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"If they’re not included in the discourses or found in the texts on monastic "
"training, you should draw the conclusion:"

msgctxt "dn16:201.8"
msgid "‘addhā idaṃ na ceva tassa bhagavato vacanaṃ;"
msgstr "‘Clearly this is not the word of the Buddha."

msgctxt "dn16:201.9"
msgid "tassa ca therassa duggahitan’ti."
msgstr "It has been incorrectly memorized by that senior mendicant.’"

msgctxt "dn16:201.10"
msgid "Itihetaṃ, bhikkhave, chaḍḍeyyātha."
msgstr "And so you should reject it."

msgctxt "dn16:201.11"
msgid ""
"Tāni ca sutte osāriyamānāni vinaye sandassiyamānāni sutte ceva osaranti, "
"vinaye ca sandissanti, niṭṭhamettha gantabbaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"If they are included in the discourses and found in the texts on monastic "
"discipline, you should draw the conclusion:"

msgctxt "dn16:201.12"
msgid "‘addhā idaṃ tassa bhagavato vacanaṃ;"
msgstr "‘Clearly this is the word of the Buddha."

msgctxt "dn16:201.13"
msgid "tassa ca therassa suggahitan’ti."
msgstr "It has been correctly memorized by that senior mendicant.’"

msgctxt "dn16:201.14"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, bhikkhave, catutthaṃ mahāpadesaṃ dhāreyyātha. <span class=\"brnum\""
">(4)</span>"
msgstr "You should remember it. This is the fourth great reference."

msgctxt "dn16:201.15"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro mahāpadese dhāreyyāthā”ti."
msgstr "These are the four great references. You should remember them.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="170"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.12"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:202.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrapi sudaṃ bhagavā bhoganagare viharanto ānande cetiye etadeva bahulaṃ "
"bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ karoti:"
msgstr ""
"And while staying at the Ānanda shrine, too, the Buddha often gave this "
"Dhamma talk to the mendicants:"

msgctxt "dn16:202.2"
msgid "“iti sīlaṃ, iti samādhi, iti paññā."
msgstr "“Such is ethics, such is immersion, such is wisdom."

msgctxt "dn16:202.3"
msgid "Sīlaparibhāvito samādhi mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso."
msgstr "When immersion is imbued with ethics it’s very fruitful and beneficial."

msgctxt "dn16:202.4"
msgid "Samādhiparibhāvitā paññā mahapphalā hoti mahānisaṃsā."
msgstr "When wisdom is imbued with immersion it’s very fruitful and beneficial."

msgctxt "dn16:202.5"
msgid "Paññāparibhāvitaṃ cittaṃ sammadeva āsavehi vimuccati, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"When the mind is imbued with wisdom it is rightly freed from the "
"defilements, namely,"

msgctxt "dn16:202.6"
msgid "kāmāsavā, bhavāsavā, avijjāsavā”ti."
msgstr "the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance.”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:203.1"
msgid "23. Kammāraputtacundavatthu"
msgstr "On Cunda the Smith"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="171"></a><a class="wp" id="4.13"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.127"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:204.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā bhoganagare yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ "
"āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha had stayed in Bhoganagara as long as he wished, he addressed "
"Ānanda:"

msgctxt "dn16:204.2"
msgid "“āyāmānanda, yena pāvā tenupasaṅkamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Ānanda, let’s go to Pāvā.”"

msgctxt "dn16:204.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

msgctxt "dn16:204.4"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ yena pāvā tadavasari."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants arrived at Pāvā,"

msgctxt "dn16:204.5"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā pāvāyaṃ viharati cundassa kammāraputtassa ambavane."
msgstr "where he stayed in Cunda the smith’s mango grove."

#. <a class="wp" id="4.14"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:204.6"
msgid "Assosi kho cundo kammāraputto:"
msgstr "Cunda heard that"

msgctxt "dn16:204.7"
msgid "“ bhagavā kira pāvaṃ anuppatto, pāvāyaṃ viharati mayhaṃ ambavane”ti."
msgstr "the Buddha had arrived and was staying in his mango grove."

msgctxt "dn16:204.8"
msgid "Atha kho cundo kammāraputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then he went to the Buddha,"

msgctxt "dn16:204.9"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "dn16:204.10"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho cundaṃ kammāraputtaṃ bhagavā dhammiyā kathāya "
"sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi."
msgstr ""
"The Buddha educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired him with a Dharma "
"talk."

msgctxt "dn16:204.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho cundo kammāraputto bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito "
"samuttejito sampahaṃsito bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: <a class=\"wp\" id=\"4.15\""
"></a>“"
msgstr "Then Cunda said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn16:204.12"
msgid ""
"adhivāsetu me, bhante, bhagavā svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghenā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, may the Buddha together with the mendicant Saṅgha please accept "
"tomorrow’s meal from me.”"

msgctxt "dn16:204.13"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena."
msgstr "The Buddha consented in silence. "

#. <a class="wp" id="4.16"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:204.14"
msgid ""
"Atha kho cundo kammāraputto bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"Then, knowing that the Buddha had accepted, Cunda got up from his seat, "
"bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before "
"leaving."

# https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/putting-the-tender-in-tender-pork/5762
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="172"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.17"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:205.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho cundo kammāraputto tassā rattiyā accayena sake nivesane paṇītaṃ "
"khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā pahūtañca sūkaramaddavaṃ bhagavato kālaṃ "
"ārocāpesi:"
msgstr ""
"And when the night had passed Cunda had a variety of delicious foods "
"prepared in his own home, and plenty of pork on the turn. Then he had the "
"Buddha informed of the time, saying:"

msgctxt "dn16:205.2"
msgid "“kālo, bhante, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti."
msgstr "“Sir, it’s time. The meal is ready.”"

#. <a class="wp" id="wp4.18"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:205.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya saddhiṃ "
"bhikkhusaṅghena yena cundassa kammāraputtassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha got dressed in the morning and, taking his bowl and robes, "
"went to the home of Cunda together with the mendicant Saṅgha,"

msgctxt "dn16:205.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "where he sat on the seat spread out"

msgctxt "dn16:205.5"
msgid "Nisajja kho bhagavā cundaṃ kammāraputtaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "and addressed Cunda:"

msgctxt "dn16:205.6"
msgid "“yaṃ te, cunda, sūkaramaddavaṃ paṭiyattaṃ, tena maṃ parivisa."
msgstr "“Cunda, please serve me with the pork on the turn that you’ve prepared."

msgctxt "dn16:205.7"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ panaññaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyattaṃ, tena bhikkhusaṅghaṃ "
"parivisā”ti."
msgstr "And serve the mendicant Saṅgha with the other foods.”"

msgctxt "dn16:205.8"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho cundo kammāraputto bhagavato paṭissutvā yaṃ ahosi "
"sūkaramaddavaṃ paṭiyattaṃ, tena bhagavantaṃ parivisi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Cunda, and did as he was asked."

msgctxt "dn16:205.9"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ panaññaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyattaṃ, tena bhikkhusaṅghaṃ parivisi."
msgstr ""

#. <a class="wp" id="wp4.19"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:205.10"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā cundaṃ kammāraputtaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha addressed Cunda:"

msgctxt "dn16:205.11"
msgid "“yaṃ te, cunda, sūkaramaddavaṃ avasiṭṭhaṃ, taṃ sobbhe nikhaṇāhi."
msgstr ""
"“Cunda, any pork on the turn that’s left over, you should bury it in a pond."

msgctxt "dn16:205.12"
msgid ""
"Nāhaṃ taṃ, cunda, passāmi sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake "
"sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya, yassa taṃ paribhuttaṃ sammā "
"pariṇāmaṃ gaccheyya aññatra tathāgatassā”ti."
msgstr ""
"I don’t see anyone in in this world—with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this "
"population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans—who could "
"properly digest it except for the Realized One.”"

msgctxt "dn16:205.13"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho cundo kammāraputto bhagavato paṭissutvā yaṃ ahosi "
"sūkaramaddavaṃ avasiṭṭhaṃ, taṃ sobbhe nikhaṇitvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"“Yes, sir,” replied Cunda. He did as he was asked, then came back to the "
"Buddha,"

msgctxt "dn16:205.14"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "dn16:205.15"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho cundaṃ kammāraputtaṃ bhagavā dhammiyā kathāya "
"sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired him with a "
"Dharma talk, after which he got up from his seat and left."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn16:206.1"
msgid "()"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="173"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.20"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.128"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:207.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavato cundassa kammāraputtassa bhattaṃ bhuttāvissa kharo ābādho "
"uppajji, lohitapakkhandikā pabāḷhā vedanā vattanti māraṇantikā."
msgstr ""
"After the Buddha had eaten Cunda’s meal, he fell severely ill with bloody "
"dysentery, struck by dreadful pains close to death."

msgctxt "dn16:207.2"
msgid "Tā sudaṃ bhagavā sato sampajāno adhivāsesi avihaññamāno."
msgstr ""
"But he endured with mindfulness and situational awareness, without worrying."

msgctxt "dn16:207.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then he addressed Ānanda:"

msgctxt "dn16:207.4"
msgid "“āyāmānanda, yena kusinārā tenupasaṅkamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Ānanda, let’s go to Kusinārā.”"

msgctxt "dn16:207.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="174"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:208.1"
msgid "Cundassa bhattaṃ bhuñjitvā,"
msgstr "I’ve heard that after eating"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:208.2"
msgid "kammārassāti me sutaṃ;"
msgstr "the meal of Cunda the smith,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:208.3"
msgid "Ābādhaṃ samphusī dhīro,"
msgstr "the sage fell severely ill,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:208.4"
msgid "pabāḷhaṃ māraṇantikaṃ."
msgstr "with pains close to death."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="175"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:209.1"
msgid "Bhuttassa ca sūkaramaddavena,"
msgstr "A severe sickness attacked the Teacher"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:209.2"
msgid "Byādhippabāḷho udapādi satthuno;"
msgstr "who had eaten the pork on the turn."

#. <br>
#. VAR: Virecamāno → viriñcamāno (bj) | viriccamāno (si, pts1, mr ^ud8.5#1
#. [Cundasutta])
msgctxt "dn16:209.3"
msgid "Virecamāno bhagavā avoca,"
msgstr "While still purging the Buddha said:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:209.4"
msgid "<span class=\"dquo\">“</span> Gacchāmahaṃ kusināraṃ nagaran”ti."
msgstr "“I’ll go to the citadel of Kusinārā.”"

#. </p></blockquote><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:210.1"
msgid "24. Pānīyāharaṇa"
msgstr "Bringing a Drink"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="176"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.21"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.129"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:211.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā maggā okkamma yena aññataraṃ rukkhamūlaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then the Buddha left the road and went to the root of a tree,"

msgctxt "dn16:211.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "where he addressed Ānanda:"

msgctxt "dn16:211.3"
msgid ""
"“iṅgha me tvaṃ, ānanda, catugguṇaṃ saṅghāṭiṃ paññapehi, kilantosmi, ānanda, "
"nisīdissāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Please, Ānanda, fold my outer robe in four and spread it out for me. I am "
"tired and will sit down.”"

msgctxt "dn16:211.4"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paṭissutvā catugguṇaṃ saṅghāṭiṃ "
"paññapesi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Ānanda, and did as he was asked."

msgctxt "dn16:211.5"
msgid "Nisīdi bhagavā paññatte āsane."
msgstr "The Buddha sat on the seat spread out."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp4.22"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:211.6"
msgid "Nisajja kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "When he was seated he said to Venerable Ānanda:"

msgctxt "dn16:211.7"
msgid ""
"“iṅgha me tvaṃ, ānanda, pānīyaṃ āhara, pipāsitosmi, ānanda, pivissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Please, Ānanda, fetch me some water. I am thirsty and will drink.”"

msgctxt "dn16:211.8"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Ānanda said to the Buddha: "

msgctxt "dn16:211.9"
msgid ""
"“idāni, bhante, pañcamattāni sakaṭasatāni atikkantāni, taṃ cakkacchinnaṃ "
"udakaṃ parittaṃ luḷitaṃ āvilaṃ sandati."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, just now around five hundred carts have passed by. The shallow water "
"has been churned up by their wheels, and it flows cloudy and murky."

#. VAR: setodakā → setakā (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: kakudhā → kakutthā (bj, pts1) | kakudha (s1-3, km) | kukudhā (^ud8.5#1
#. [Cundasutta])
msgctxt "dn16:211.10"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhante, kakudhā nadī avidūre acchodakā sātodakā sītodakā setodakā "
"suppatitthā ramaṇīyā."
msgstr ""
"The Kakutthā river is not far away, with clear, sweet, cool water, clean, "
"with smooth banks, delightful."

#. VAR: sītī → sītaṃ (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "dn16:211.11"
msgid "Ettha bhagavā pānīyañca pivissati, gattāni ca sītī karissatī”ti."
msgstr "There the Buddha can drink and cool his limbs.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="177"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.23"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:212.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "For a second time, the Buddha asked Ānanda for a drink,"

msgctxt "dn16:212.2"
msgid ""
"“iṅgha me tvaṃ, ānanda, pānīyaṃ āhara, pipāsitosmi, ānanda, pivissāmī”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:212.3"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and for a second time Ānanda suggested going to the Kakutthā river."

msgctxt "dn16:212.4"
msgid ""
"“idāni, bhante, pañcamattāni sakaṭasatāni atikkantāni, taṃ cakkacchinnaṃ "
"udakaṃ parittaṃ luḷitaṃ āvilaṃ sandati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:212.5"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhante, kakudhā nadī avidūre acchodakā sātodakā sītodakā setodakā "
"suppatitthā ramaṇīyā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:212.6"
msgid "Ettha bhagavā pānīyañca pivissati, gattāni ca sītīkarissatī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="178"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.24"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:213.1"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "And for a third time, the Buddha said to Ānanda:"

msgctxt "dn16:213.2"
msgid ""
"“iṅgha me tvaṃ, ānanda, pānīyaṃ āhara, pipāsitosmi, ānanda, pivissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Please, Ānanda, fetch me some water. I am thirsty and will drink.”"

msgctxt "dn16:213.3"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paṭissutvā pattaṃ gahetvā yena "
"sā nadikā tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Ānanda. Taking his bowl he went to the river."

#. VAR: sandittha → sandati (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn16:213.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sā nadikā cakkacchinnā parittā luḷitā āvilā sandamānā, āyasmante "
"ānande upasaṅkamante acchā vippasannā anāvilā sandittha."
msgstr ""
"Now, though the shallow water in that creek had been churned up by wheels, "
"and flowed cloudy and murky, when Ānanda approached it flowed transparent, "
"clear, and unclouded."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp4.25"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:213.5"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato ānandassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Ānanda thought:"

msgctxt "dn16:213.6"
msgid ""
"“acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho, tathāgatassa mahiddhikatā "
"mahānubhāvatā."
msgstr ""
"“It’s incredible, it’s amazing! The Realized One has such psychic power and "
"might!"

msgctxt "dn16:213.7"
msgid ""
"Ayañhi sā nadikā cakkacchinnā parittā luḷitā āvilā sandamānā mayi "
"upasaṅkamante acchā vippasannā anāvilā sandatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"For though the shallow water in that creek had been churned up by wheels, "
"and flowed cloudy and murky, when I approached it flowed transparent, clear, "
"and unclouded.”"

msgctxt "dn16:213.8"
msgid "Pattena pānīyaṃ ādāya yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Gathering a bowl of drinking water he went back to the Buddha,"

msgctxt "dn16:213.9"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

msgctxt "dn16:213.10"
msgid ""
"“acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante, tathāgatassa mahiddhikatā "
"mahānubhāvatā."
msgstr ""
"“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing! The Realized One has such psychic power "
"and might!"

msgctxt "dn16:213.11"
msgid ""
"Idāni sā bhante nadikā cakkacchinnā parittā luḷitā āvilā sandamānā mayi "
"upasaṅkamante acchā vippasannā anāvilā sandittha."
msgstr ""
"Just now, though the shallow water in that creek had been churned up by "
"wheels, and flowed cloudy and murky, when I approached it flowed "
"transparent, clear, and unclouded."

msgctxt "dn16:213.12"
msgid "Pivatu bhagavā pānīyaṃ pivatu sugato pānīyan”ti."
msgstr "Drink the water, Blessed One! Drink the water, Holy One!”"

msgctxt "dn16:213.13"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā pānīyaṃ apāyi."
msgstr "So the Buddha drank the water."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:214.1"
msgid "25. Pukkusamallaputtavatthu"
msgstr "On Pukkusa the Mallian"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="179"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.26"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.130"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:215.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena pukkuso mallaputto āḷārassa kālāmassa sāvako "
"kusinārāya pāvaṃ addhānamaggappaṭipanno hoti."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Pukkusa the Mallian, a disciple of Āḷāra Kālāma, was "
"travelling along the road from Kusinārā and Pāvā."

msgctxt "dn16:215.2"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho pukkuso mallaputto bhagavantaṃ aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle nisinnaṃ."
msgstr "He saw the Buddha sitting at the root of a certain tree."

msgctxt "dn16:215.3"
msgid "Disvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "He went up to him, "

msgctxt "dn16:215.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed, sat down to one side, "

msgctxt "dn16:215.5"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho pukkuso mallaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said:"

msgctxt "dn16:215.6"
msgid ""
"“acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante, santena vata, bhante, pabbajitā "
"vihārena viharanti."
msgstr ""
"“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing! Those who have gone forth remain in "
"such peaceful meditations."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp4.27"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:215.7"
msgid ""
"Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhante, āḷāro kālāmo addhānamaggappaṭipanno maggā okkamma "
"avidūre aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Once it so happened that Āḷāra Kālāma, while travelling along a road, left "
"the road and sat at the root of a nearby tree for the day’s meditation."

msgctxt "dn16:215.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhante, pañcamattāni sakaṭasatāni āḷāraṃ kālāmaṃ nissāya nissāya "
"atikkamiṃsu."
msgstr "Then around five hundred carts passed by right next to Āḷāra Kālāma."

msgctxt "dn16:215.9"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhante, aññataro puriso tassa sakaṭasatthassa piṭṭhito piṭṭhito "
"āgacchanto yena āḷāro kālāmo tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then a certain person coming behind those carts went up to Āḷāra Kālāma"

msgctxt "dn16:215.10"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āḷāraṃ kālāmaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

msgctxt "dn16:215.11"
msgid "‘api, bhante, pañcamattāni sakaṭasatāni atikkantāni addasā’ti?"
msgstr "‘Sir, didn’t you see the five hundred carts pass by?’"

msgctxt "dn16:215.12"
msgid "‘Na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, addasan’ti."
msgstr "‘No, friend, I didn’t see them.’"

msgctxt "dn16:215.13"
msgid "‘Kiṃ pana, bhante, saddaṃ assosī’ti?"
msgstr "‘But sir, didn’t you hear a sound?’"

msgctxt "dn16:215.14"
msgid "‘Na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, saddaṃ assosin’ti."
msgstr "‘No, friend, I didn’t hear a sound.’"

msgctxt "dn16:215.15"
msgid "‘Kiṃ pana, bhante, sutto ahosī’ti?"
msgstr "‘But sir, were you asleep?’"

msgctxt "dn16:215.16"
msgid "‘Na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, sutto ahosin’ti."
msgstr "‘No, friend, I wasn’t asleep.’"

msgctxt "dn16:215.17"
msgid "‘Kiṃ pana, bhante, saññī ahosī’ti?"
msgstr "‘But sir, were you conscious?’"

msgctxt "dn16:215.18"
msgid "‘Evamāvuso’ti."
msgstr "‘Yes, friend.’"

msgctxt "dn16:215.19"
msgid ""
"‘So tvaṃ, bhante, saññī samāno jāgaro pañcamattāni sakaṭasatāni nissāya "
"nissāya atikkantāni neva addasa, na pana saddaṃ assosi;"
msgstr ""
"‘So, sir, while conscious and awake you neither saw nor heard a sound as "
"five hundred carts passed by right next to you?"

# As were Mahapajapati's limbs, AN 8.51
#. VAR: apisu → apissu (bj) | api hi (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:215.20"
msgid "apisu te, bhante, saṅghāṭi rajena okiṇṇā’ti?"
msgstr "Why sir, even your outer robe is covered with dust!’"

msgctxt "dn16:215.21"
msgid "‘Evamāvuso’ti."
msgstr "‘Yes, friend.’"

msgctxt "dn16:215.22"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, tassa purisassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then that person thought:"

msgctxt "dn16:215.23"
msgid ""
"‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho, santena vata bho pabbajitā vihārena "
"viharanti."
msgstr ""
"‘It’s incredible, it’s amazing! Those who have gone forth remain in such "
"peaceful meditations,"

msgctxt "dn16:215.24"
msgid ""
"Yatra hi nāma saññī samāno jāgaro pañcamattāni sakaṭasatāni nissāya nissāya "
"atikkantāni neva dakkhati, na pana saddaṃ sossatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"in that, while conscious and awake he neither saw nor heard a sound as five "
"hundred carts passed by right next to him.’"

# Anandajotis' "having gained" is incorrect.
msgctxt "dn16:215.25"
msgid "Āḷāre kālāme uḷāraṃ pasādaṃ pavedetvā pakkāmī”ti."
msgstr "And after declaring his lofty confidence in Āḷāra Kālāma, he left.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="180"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.28"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:216.1"
msgid ""
"“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, pukkusa, katamaṃ nu kho dukkarataraṃ vā "
"durabhisambhavataraṃ vā—"
msgstr ""
"“What do you think, Pukkusa? Which is harder and more challenging to do "
"while conscious and awake:"

msgctxt "dn16:216.2"
msgid ""
"yo vā saññī samāno jāgaro pañcamattāni sakaṭasatāni nissāya nissāya "
"atikkantāni neva passeyya, na pana saddaṃ suṇeyya;"
msgstr ""
"to neither see nor hear a sound as five hundred carts pass by right next to "
"you?"

#. VAR: vijjullatāsu → vijjutāsu (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:216.3"
msgid ""
"yo vā saññī samāno jāgaro deve vassante deve gaḷagaḷāyante vijjullatāsu "
"niccharantīsu asaniyā phalantiyā neva passeyya, na pana saddaṃ suṇeyyā”ti? <"
"a class=\"wp\" id=\"wp4.29\"></a>“"
msgstr ""
"Or to neither see nor hear a sound as it’s raining and pouring, lightning’s "
"flashing, and thunder’s cracking?”"

#. VAR: aṭṭha vā sakaṭasatāni nava vā sakaṭasatāni → nava vā sakaṭasatāni dasa
#. vā sakaṭasatāni (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:216.4"
msgid ""
"Kiñhi, bhante, karissanti pañca vā sakaṭasatāni cha vā sakaṭasatāni satta vā "
"sakaṭasatāni aṭṭha vā sakaṭasatāni nava vā sakaṭasatāni, sakaṭasahassaṃ vā "
"sakaṭasatasahassaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"“What do five hundred carts matter, or six hundred, or seven hundred, or "
"eight hundred, or nine hundred, or a thousand, or even a hundred thousand "
"carts?"

msgctxt "dn16:216.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho etadeva dukkaratarañceva durabhisambhavatarañca yo saññī samāno "
"jāgaro deve vassante deve gaḷagaḷāyante vijjullatāsu niccharantīsu asaniyā "
"phalantiyā neva passeyya, na pana saddaṃ suṇeyyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"It’s far harder and more challenging to neither see nor hear a sound as it’s "
"raining and pouring, lightning’s flashing, and thunder’s cracking!”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="181"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.30"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.132"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:217.1"
msgid "“Ekamidāhaṃ, pukkusa, samayaṃ ātumāyaṃ viharāmi bhusāgāre."
msgstr "“This one time, Pukkusa, I was staying near Ātumā in a threshing-hut."

#. VAR: balibaddā → balivaddā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:217.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena deve vassante deve gaḷagaḷāyante vijjullatāsu "
"niccharantīsu asaniyā phalantiyā avidūre bhusāgārassa dve kassakā bhātaro "
"hatā cattāro ca balibaddā."
msgstr ""
"At that time it was raining and pouring, lightning was flashing, and thunder "
"was cracking. And not far from the threshing-hut two farmers who were "
"brothers were killed, as well as four oxen."

msgctxt "dn16:217.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, pukkusa, ātumāya mahājanakāyo nikkhamitvā yena te dve kassakā "
"bhātaro hatā cattāro ca balibaddā tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr "Then a large crowd came from Ātumā to the place where that happened."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp4.31"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:217.4"
msgid ""
"Tena kho panāhaṃ, pukkusa, samayena bhusāgārā nikkhamitvā bhusāgāradvāre "
"abbhokāse caṅkamāmi."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time I came out of the threshing-hut and was walking meditation "
"in the open near the door of the hut."

msgctxt "dn16:217.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, pukkusa, aññataro puriso tamhā mahājanakāyā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then having left that crowd, a certain person approached me,"

msgctxt "dn16:217.6"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr "bowed, and stood to one side."

msgctxt "dn16:217.7"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ ṭhitaṃ kho ahaṃ, pukkusa, taṃ purisaṃ etadavocaṃ: <a class=\"wp\" "
"id=\"wp4.32\"></a>‘"
msgstr "I said to them:"

msgctxt "dn16:217.8"
msgid "kiṃ nu kho eso, āvuso, mahājanakāyo sannipatito’ti?"
msgstr "‘Why, friend, has this crowd gathered?’"

msgctxt "dn16:217.9"
msgid ""
"‘Idāni, bhante, deve vassante deve gaḷagaḷāyante vijjullatāsu niccharantīsu "
"asaniyā phalantiyā dve kassakā bhātaro hatā cattāro ca balibaddā."
msgstr ""
"‘Just now, sir, it was raining and pouring, lightning was flashing, and "
"thunder was cracking. And two farmers who were brothers were killed, as well "
"as four oxen."

msgctxt "dn16:217.10"
msgid "Ettheso mahājanakāyo sannipatito."
msgstr "Then this crowd gathered here."

#. VAR: kva → kuhiṃ (bj)
msgctxt "dn16:217.11"
msgid "Tvaṃ pana, bhante, kva ahosī’ti?"
msgstr "But sir, where were you?’"

msgctxt "dn16:217.12"
msgid "‘Idheva kho ahaṃ, āvuso, ahosin’ti."
msgstr "‘I was right here, friend.’"

msgctxt "dn16:217.13"
msgid "‘Kiṃ pana, bhante, addasā’ti?"
msgstr "‘But sir, did you see?’"

msgctxt "dn16:217.14"
msgid "‘Na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, addasan’ti."
msgstr "‘No, friend, I didn’t see anything.’"

msgctxt "dn16:217.15"
msgid "‘Kiṃ pana, bhante, saddaṃ assosī’ti?"
msgstr "‘But sir, didn’t you hear a sound?’"

msgctxt "dn16:217.16"
msgid "‘Na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, saddaṃ assosin’ti."
msgstr "‘No, friend, I didn’t hear a sound.’"

msgctxt "dn16:217.17"
msgid "‘Kiṃ pana, bhante, sutto ahosī’ti?"
msgstr "‘But sir, were you asleep?’"

msgctxt "dn16:217.18"
msgid "‘Na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, sutto ahosin’ti."
msgstr "‘No, friend, I wasn’t asleep.’"

msgctxt "dn16:217.19"
msgid "‘Kiṃ pana, bhante, saññī ahosī’ti?"
msgstr "‘But sir, were you conscious?’"

msgctxt "dn16:217.20"
msgid "‘Evamāvuso’ti."
msgstr "‘Yes, friend.’"

msgctxt "dn16:217.21"
msgid ""
"‘So tvaṃ, bhante, saññī samāno jāgaro deve vassante deve gaḷagaḷāyante "
"vijjullatāsu niccharantīsu asaniyā phalantiyā neva addasa, na pana saddaṃ "
"assosī’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘So, sir, while conscious and awake you neither saw nor heard a sound as it "
"was raining and pouring, lightning was flashing, and thunder was cracking?’"

# Question mark is wrong.
msgctxt "dn16:217.22"
msgid "‘Evamāvuso’ti?"
msgstr "‘Yes, friend.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="182"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.33"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:218.1"
msgid "Atha kho, pukkusa, tassa purisassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then that person thought:"

msgctxt "dn16:218.2"
msgid ""
"‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho, santena vata bho pabbajitā vihārena "
"viharanti."
msgstr ""
"‘It’s incredible, it’s amazing! Those who have gone forth remain in such "
"peaceful meditations,"

#. VAR: sossatī’ti → suṇissati (s1-3) | suṇissatīti (km)
msgctxt "dn16:218.3"
msgid ""
"Yatra hi nāma saññī samāno jāgaro deve vassante deve gaḷagaḷāyante "
"vijjullatāsu niccharantīsu asaniyā phalantiyā neva dakkhati, na pana saddaṃ "
"sossatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"in that, while conscious and awake he neither saw nor heard a sound as it "
"was raining and pouring, lightning was flashing, and thunder was cracking.’"

msgctxt "dn16:218.4"
msgid ""
"Mayi uḷāraṃ pasādaṃ pavedetvā maṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"And after declaring their lofty confidence in me, they bowed and "
"respectfully circled me, keeping me on their right, before leaving.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="183"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.34"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.133"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:219.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, pukkuso mallaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Pukkusa said to him:"

#. VAR: sīghasotāya → siṅghasotāya (mr)
msgctxt "dn16:219.2"
msgid ""
"“esāhaṃ, bhante, yo me āḷāre kālāme pasādo taṃ mahāvāte vā ophuṇāmi "
"sīghasotāya vā nadiyā pavāhemi."
msgstr ""
"“Any confidence I had in Āḷāra Kālāma I sweep away as in a strong wind, or "
"float away as down a swift stream."

msgctxt "dn16:219.3"
msgid "Abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "Excellent, sir! Excellent!"

msgctxt "dn16:219.4"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, "
"mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya:"
msgstr ""
"As if he was righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark  "

msgctxt "dn16:219.5"
msgid "‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti;"
msgstr "so people with good eyes can see what’s there,  "

msgctxt "dn16:219.6"
msgid "evamevaṃ bhagavatā anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr "so too the Buddha has made the teaching clear in many ways. "

msgctxt "dn16:219.7"
msgid ""
"Esāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca."
msgstr ""
"I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the Dharma, and to the mendicant Saṅgha."

msgctxt "dn16:219.8"
msgid "Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has "
"gone for refuge for life.” "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="184"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.35"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:220.1"
msgid "Atha kho pukkuso mallaputto aññataraṃ purisaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then Pukkusa addressed a certain man:"

msgctxt "dn16:220.2"
msgid "“iṅgha me tvaṃ, bhaṇe, siṅgīvaṇṇaṃ yugamaṭṭhaṃ dhāraṇīyaṃ āharā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Please, my man, fetch a pair of ready to wear polished golden garments.”"

#. VAR: āhari → āharasi (mr)
msgctxt "dn16:220.3"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho so puriso pukkusassa mallaputtassa paṭissutvā taṃ "
"siṅgīvaṇṇaṃ yugamaṭṭhaṃ dhāraṇīyaṃ āhari."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied that man, and did as he was asked."

# I think the use of verbs for the garments is corrupt through this passage. Skt uses acchadeti throughout. Here upanameti means "brings close" cf Pj1. Below, it means "place on his body", cf. SN 10.3
msgctxt "dn16:220.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho pukkuso mallaputto taṃ siṅgīvaṇṇaṃ yugamaṭṭhaṃ dhāraṇīyaṃ bhagavato "
"upanāmesi:"
msgstr "Then Pukkusa brought the garments to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn16:220.5"
msgid ""
"“idaṃ, bhante, siṅgīvaṇṇaṃ yugamaṭṭhaṃ dhāraṇīyaṃ, taṃ me bhagavā "
"paṭiggaṇhātu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, please accept this pair of ready to wear polished golden garments from "
"me out of compassion.”"

msgctxt "dn16:220.6"
msgid "“Tena hi, pukkusa, ekena maṃ acchādehi, ekena ānandan”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, Pukkusa, clothe me in one, and Ānanda in the other.”"

msgctxt "dn16:220.7"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho pukkuso mallaputto bhagavato paṭissutvā ekena "
"bhagavantaṃ acchādeti, ekena āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Pukkusa, and did so."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp4.36"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:220.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pukkusaṃ mallaputtaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi "
"samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired Pukkusa the "
"Mallian with a Dharma talk,"

msgctxt "dn16:220.9"
msgid ""
"Atha kho pukkuso mallaputto bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito "
"samuttejito sampahaṃsito uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ "
"katvā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"after which he got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the "
"Buddha before leaving."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="185"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.37"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.134"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:221.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando acirapakkante pukkuse mallaputte taṃ siṅgīvaṇṇaṃ "
"yugamaṭṭhaṃ dhāraṇīyaṃ bhagavato kāyaṃ upanāmesi."
msgstr ""
"Then, not long after Pukkusa had left, Ānanda placed the pair of golden "
"garments on the Buddha’s body."

#. VAR: hataccikaṃ viya → vītaccikaṃ viya (bj, pts1) | hatacchikaṃ viya (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn16:221.2"
msgid "Taṃ bhagavato kāyaṃ upanāmitaṃ hataccikaṃ viya khāyati."
msgstr "But when placed on the Buddha’s body they seemed to lose their shine."

msgctxt "dn16:221.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Ānanda said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn16:221.4"
msgid ""
"“acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante, yāva parisuddho, bhante, tathāgatassa "
"chavivaṇṇo pariyodāto."
msgstr ""
"“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing, how pure and bright is the color of the "
"Realized One’s skin."

msgctxt "dn16:221.5"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, bhante, siṅgīvaṇṇaṃ yugamaṭṭhaṃ dhāraṇīyaṃ bhagavato kāyaṃ upanāmitaṃ "
"hataccikaṃ viya khāyatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"When this pair of ready to wear polished golden garments is placed on the "
"Buddha’s body they seem to lose their shine.”"

msgctxt "dn16:221.6"
msgid ""
"“Evametaṃ, ānanda, evametaṃ, ānanda, dvīsu kālesu ativiya tathāgatassa kāyo "
"parisuddho hoti chavivaṇṇo pariyodāto."
msgstr ""
"“That’s so true, Ānanda, that’s so true! There are two times when the color "
"of the Realized One’s skin becomes extra pure and bright."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp4.38"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:221.7"
msgid "Katamesu dvīsu?"
msgstr "What two? "

msgctxt "dn16:221.8"
msgid ""
"Yañca, ānanda, rattiṃ tathāgato anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambujjhati, "
"yañca rattiṃ anupādisesāya nibbānadhātuyā parinibbāyati."
msgstr ""
"The night when a Realized One understands the supreme perfect awakening; and "
"the night he becomes fully extinguished through the natural principle of "
"extinguishment, without anything left over."

msgctxt "dn16:221.9"
msgid ""
"Imesu kho, ānanda, dvīsu kālesu ativiya tathāgatassa kāyo parisuddho hoti "
"chavivaṇṇo pariyodāto."
msgstr ""
"These are the are two times when the color of the Realized One’s skin "
"becomes extra pure and bright."

#. VAR: bhavissati → bhavissatīti (mr)
#. VAR: antarena → antare (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn16:221.10"
msgid ""
"Ajja kho panānanda, rattiyā pacchime yāme kusinārāyaṃ upavattane mallānaṃ "
"sālavane antarena yamakasālānaṃ tathāgatassa parinibbānaṃ bhavissati."
msgstr ""
"Today, Ānanda, in the last watch of the night, between a pair of <i>sal</i> "
"trees in the <i>sal</i> forest of the Mallas at Upavattana near Kusinārā, "
"shall be the Realized One’s full extinguishment."

msgctxt "dn16:221.11"
msgid "Āyāmānanda, yena kakudhā nadī tenupasaṅkamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "Come, Ānanda, let’s go to the Kakutthā River.”"

msgctxt "dn16:221.12"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="186"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:222.1"
msgid "Siṅgīvaṇṇaṃ yugamaṭṭhaṃ,"
msgstr "A pair of golden polished garments"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:222.2"
msgid "pukkuso abhihārayi;"
msgstr "was presented by Pukkusa;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:222.3"
msgid "Tena acchādito satthā,"
msgstr "when the teacher was clothed with them,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:222.4"
msgid "hemavaṇṇo asobhathāti."
msgstr "his golden skin glowed bright."

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn16:223.1"
msgid "()"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="187"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.39"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:224.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ yena kakudhā nadī "
"tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants went to the "
"Kakutthā River."

msgctxt "dn16:224.2"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā kakudhaṃ nadiṃ ajjhogāhetvā nhatvā ca pivitvā ca paccuttaritvā "
"yena ambavanaṃ tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr ""
"He plunged into the river and bathed and drank. And when he had emerged, he "
"went to the mango grove,"

msgctxt "dn16:224.3"
msgid "Upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ cundakaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "where he addressed Venerable Cundaka:"

msgctxt "dn16:224.4"
msgid ""
"“iṅgha me tvaṃ, cundaka, catugguṇaṃ saṅghāṭiṃ paññapehi, kilantosmi, "
"cundaka, nipajjissāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Please, Cundaka, fold my outer robe in four and spread it out for me. I am "
"tired and will lie down.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="188"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4.40"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.135"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:225.1"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā cundako bhagavato paṭissutvā catugguṇaṃ "
"saṅghāṭiṃ paññapesi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Cundaka, and did as he was asked."

msgctxt "dn16:225.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā dakkhiṇena passena sīhaseyyaṃ kappesi pāde pādaṃ accādhāya "
"sato sampajāno uṭṭhānasaññaṃ manasikaritvā."
msgstr ""
"And then the Buddha lay down in the lion’s posture—on the right side, "
"placing one foot on top of the other—mindful and aware, and focused on the "
"time of getting up. "

msgctxt "dn16:225.3"
msgid "Āyasmā pana cundako tattheva bhagavato purato nisīdi."
msgstr "But Cundaka sat down right there in front of the Buddha."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="189"></a><a class="wp"
#. id="wp4.41"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:226.1"
msgid "Gantvāna buddho nadikaṃ kakudhaṃ,"
msgstr "Having gone to Kakutthā Creek,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:226.2"
msgid "Acchodakaṃ sātudakaṃ vippasannaṃ;"
msgstr "whose water was transparent, sweet, and clear,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: akilantarūpo → sukilantarūpo (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:226.3"
msgid "Ogāhi satthā akilantarūpo,"
msgstr "the Teacher, being tired, plunged in,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: appaṭimo ca → appaṭimodha (bj) | appaṭimo va (pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:226.4"
msgid "Tathāgato appaṭimo ca loke."
msgstr "the Realized One, without compare in the world."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="190"></a>
#. VAR: Nhatvā ca pivitvā cudatāri satthā → nhātvā ca pivitvā cudakāni sutvā
#. (s1-3) | nahatvā pitvā cudatāri satthā (pts1) | pivitvā ca uttari (mr)
msgctxt "dn16:227.1"
msgid "Nhatvā ca pivitvā cudatāri satthā,"
msgstr "And after bathing and drinking the Teacher emerged."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:227.2"
msgid "Purakkhato bhikkhugaṇassa majjhe;"
msgstr "Before the group of mendicants, in the middle, the Buddha,"

# Adopt PTS reading. Comm: "pavattā bhagavā idha dhammeti bhagavā idha sāsane dhamme pavattā, caturāsīti dhammakkhandhasahassāni pavattānīti attho"
#. <br>
#. VAR: Vattā → satthā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:227.3"
msgid "Vattā pavattā bhagavā idha dhamme,"
msgstr "the Teacher who rolled forth the present dispensation,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:227.4"
msgid "Upāgami ambavanaṃ mahesi."
msgstr "the great sage went to the mango grove."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="191"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:228.1"
msgid "Āmantayi cundakaṃ nāma bhikkhuṃ,"
msgstr "He addressed the mendicant named Cundaka:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:228.2"
msgid "Catugguṇaṃ santhara me nipajjaṃ;"
msgstr "“Spread out my folded robe so I can lie down.”"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:228.3"
msgid "So codito bhāvitattena cundo,"
msgstr "The self-developed one urged Cunda,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:228.4"
msgid "Catugguṇaṃ santhari khippameva;"
msgstr "who quickly spread the folded robe."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:228.5"
msgid "Nipajji satthā akilantarūpo,"
msgstr "Teacher, being tired, lay down,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: pamukhe → samukhe (mr)
msgctxt "dn16:228.6"
msgid "Cundopi tattha pamukhe nisīdīti."
msgstr "while Cunda sat there before him.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="192"></a><a class="wp"
#. id="wp4.42"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.136"></a>
#. VAR: kho → yo kho (mr)
msgctxt "dn16:229.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to Venerable Ānanda:"

# The subject is unspecified in the Pali. It is not koci, for that forms a regular idiom with vippatisara. The Skt says vipratisāraḥ pareṣām āpāditaḥ
msgctxt "dn16:229.2"
msgid ""
"“siyā kho panānanda, cundassa kammāraputtassa koci vippaṭisāraṃ uppādeyya:"
msgstr ""
"“Now it may happen, Ānanda, that others may give rise to some regret for "
"Cunda the smith:"

msgctxt "dn16:229.3"
msgid ""
"‘tassa te, āvuso cunda, alābhā tassa te dulladdhaṃ, yassa te tathāgato "
"pacchimaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ paribhuñjitvā parinibbuto’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘It’s your loss, friend Cunda, it’s your misfortune, in that the Realized "
"One became fully extinguished after eating his last meal from you.’"

msgctxt "dn16:229.4"
msgid "Cundassa, ānanda, kammāraputtassa evaṃ vippaṭisāro paṭivinetabbo:"
msgstr "You should get rid of remorse in Cunda the smith like this:"

msgctxt "dn16:229.5"
msgid ""
"‘tassa te, āvuso cunda, lābhā tassa te suladdhaṃ, yassa te tathāgato "
"pacchimaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ paribhuñjitvā parinibbuto."
msgstr ""
"‘You’re fortunate, friend Cunda, you’re so very fortunate, in that the "
"Realized One became fully extinguished after eating his last meal from you."

#. VAR: samasamaphalā → samaphalā (bj) | samā samaphalā (mr)
#. VAR: samavipākā → samasamavipākā (s1-3, km, pts1)
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:229.6"
msgid ""
"Sammukhā metaṃ, āvuso cunda, bhagavato sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ– dveme "
"piṇḍapātā samasamaphalā samavipākā, ativiya aññehi piṇḍapātehi "
"mahapphalatarā ca mahānisaṃsatarā ca."
msgstr ""
"I have heard and learned this directly from the Buddha. There are two meal "
"offerings that have identical fruit and result, and are more fruitful and "
"beneficial than other meal offerings."

msgctxt "dn16:229.7"
msgid "Katame dve?"
msgstr "What two?"

msgctxt "dn16:229.8"
msgid ""
"Yañca piṇḍapātaṃ paribhuñjitvā tathāgato anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ "
"abhisambujjhati, yañca piṇḍapātaṃ paribhuñjitvā tathāgato anupādisesāya "
"nibbānadhātuyā parinibbāyati."
msgstr ""
"The meal after eating which a Realized One understands the supreme perfect "
"awakening; and the meal after eating which he becomes fully extinguished "
"through the natural principle of extinguishment, without anything left over."

msgctxt "dn16:229.9"
msgid ""
"Ime dve piṇḍapātā samasamaphalā samavipākā, ativiya aññehi piṇḍapātehi "
"mahapphalatarā ca mahānisaṃsatarā ca."
msgstr ""
"These two meal offerings have identical fruit and result, and are more "
"fruitful and beneficial than other meal offerings."

# Note the text starts to use ayasma here for Cunda. There seems to be some confusion felt between the monk attendant Cundaka and Cunda. But the usage here seems to be driven by grammar. Earlier avuso was used, but as an indeclinable it doesn't work in instrumental, so apparently ayasmata is the fallback instrumental form; they are both from the same root. It is a nice reminder of the fluidity of such usages. The sanskrit too has saṃmukhaṃ ma āyuṣmaṃś cunda
msgctxt "dn16:229.10"
msgid ""
"Āyusaṃvattanikaṃ āyasmatā cundena kammāraputtena kammaṃ upacitaṃ, "
"vaṇṇasaṃvattanikaṃ āyasmatā cundena kammāraputtena kammaṃ upacitaṃ, "
"sukhasaṃvattanikaṃ āyasmatā cundena kammāraputtena kammaṃ upacitaṃ, "
"yasasaṃvattanikaṃ āyasmatā cundena kammāraputtena kammaṃ upacitaṃ, "
"saggasaṃvattanikaṃ āyasmatā cundena kammāraputtena kammaṃ upacitaṃ, "
"ādhipateyyasaṃvattanikaṃ āyasmatā cundena kammāraputtena kammaṃ upacitan’ti."
msgstr ""
"You’ve accumulated a deed that leads to long life, beauty, happiness, fame, "
"heaven, and sovereignty.’"

msgctxt "dn16:229.11"
msgid "Cundassa, ānanda, kammāraputtassa evaṃ vippaṭisāro paṭivinetabbo”ti."
msgstr "That’s how you should get rid of remorse in Cunda the smith.”"

#. <a class="wp" id="wp4.43"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:229.12"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etamatthaṃ viditvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ udānaṃ udānesi:"
msgstr ""
"Then, knowing the meaning of this, on that occasion the Buddha spoke these "
"words of inspiration:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="193"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:230.1"
msgid "“Dadato puññaṃ pavaḍḍhati,"
msgstr "“A giver’s merit grows;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:230.2"
msgid "Saṃyamato veraṃ na cīyati;"
msgstr "emnity doesn’t build up when you have self-control."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:230.3"
msgid "Kusalo ca jahāti pāpakaṃ,"
msgstr "A skillful person gives up bad things—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:230.4"
msgid "Rāgadosamohakkhayā sanibbuto”ti."
msgstr "with the end of greed, hate, and delusion, they’re extinguished.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn16:231.1"
msgid "Catuttho bhāṇavāro."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:232.1"
msgid "26. Yamakasālā"
msgstr "The Pair of Sal Trees"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="194"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.1"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.137"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:233.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to Ānanda: "

msgctxt "dn16:233.2"
msgid ""
"“āyāmānanda, yena hiraññavatiyā nadiyā pārimaṃ tīraṃ, yena kusinārā "
"upavattanaṃ mallānaṃ sālavanaṃ tenupasaṅkamissāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Come, Ānanda, let’s go to the far shore of the Golden River, and on to the "
"<i>sal</i> forest of the Mallas at Upavattana near Kusinārā.”"

msgctxt "dn16:233.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

msgctxt "dn16:233.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ yena hiraññavatiyā nadiyā "
"pārimaṃ tīraṃ, yena kusinārā upavattanaṃ mallānaṃ sālavanaṃ tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr "And that’s where they went."

msgctxt "dn16:233.5"
msgid "Upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha addressed Ānanda:"

msgctxt "dn16:233.6"
msgid ""
"“iṅgha me tvaṃ, ānanda, antarena yamakasālānaṃ uttarasīsakaṃ mañcakaṃ "
"paññapehi, kilantosmi, ānanda, nipajjissāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Please, Ānanda, set up a cot for me between the twin <i>sal</i> trees, with "
"my head to the north. I am tired and will lie down.”"

msgctxt "dn16:233.7"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paṭissutvā antarena "
"yamakasālānaṃ uttarasīsakaṃ mañcakaṃ paññapesi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Ānanda, and did as he was asked."

# A sad detail here: previously when lying down, his mind was focused on getting up. Sob!
msgctxt "dn16:233.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā dakkhiṇena passena sīhaseyyaṃ kappesi pāde pādaṃ accādhāya "
"sato sampajāno."
msgstr ""
"And then the Buddha lay down in the lion’s posture—on the right side, "
"placing one foot on top of the other—mindful and aware."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="195"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.2"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.138"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:234.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena yamakasālā sabbaphāliphullā honti akālapupphehi."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the twin <i>sal</i> trees were in full blossom with flowers "
"out of season."

msgctxt "dn16:234.2"
msgid ""
"Te tathāgatassa sarīraṃ okiranti ajjhokiranti abhippakiranti tathāgatassa "
"pūjāya."
msgstr ""
"They sprinkled and bestrewed the Realized One’s body in honor of the "
"Realized One."

msgctxt "dn16:234.3"
msgid ""
"Dibbānipi mandāravapupphāni antalikkhā papatanti, tāni tathāgatassa sarīraṃ "
"okiranti ajjhokiranti abhippakiranti tathāgatassa pūjāya."
msgstr ""
"And the flowers of the celestial Flame Tree fell from the sky, and they too "
"sprinkled and bestrewed the Realized One’s body in honor of the Realized One."

msgctxt "dn16:234.4"
msgid ""
"Dibbānipi candanacuṇṇāni antalikkhā papatanti, tāni tathāgatassa sarīraṃ "
"okiranti ajjhokiranti abhippakiranti tathāgatassa pūjāya."
msgstr ""
"And celestial sandalwood powder fell from the sky, and it too sprinkled and "
"bestrewed the Realized One’s body in honor of the Realized One."

msgctxt "dn16:234.5"
msgid "Dibbānipi tūriyāni antalikkhe vajjanti tathāgatassa pūjāya."
msgstr "And celestial music played in the sky in honor of the Realized One."

msgctxt "dn16:234.6"
msgid "Dibbānipi saṅgītāni antalikkhe vattanti tathāgatassa pūjāya."
msgstr "And celestial choirs sang in the sky in honor of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="196"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.3"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:235.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha pointed out to Ānanda what was happening, adding:"

msgctxt "dn16:235.2"
msgid "“sabbaphāliphullā kho, ānanda, yamakasālā akālapupphehi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:235.3"
msgid ""
"Te tathāgatassa sarīraṃ okiranti ajjhokiranti abhippakiranti tathāgatassa "
"pūjāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:235.4"
msgid ""
"Dibbānipi mandāravapupphāni antalikkhā papatanti, tāni tathāgatassa sarīraṃ "
"okiranti ajjhokiranti abhippakiranti tathāgatassa pūjāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:235.5"
msgid ""
"Dibbānipi candanacuṇṇāni antalikkhā papatanti, tāni tathāgatassa sarīraṃ "
"okiranti ajjhokiranti abhippakiranti tathāgatassa pūjāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:235.6"
msgid "Dibbānipi tūriyāni antalikkhe vajjanti tathāgatassa pūjāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:235.7"
msgid "Dibbānipi saṅgītāni antalikkhe vattanti tathāgatassa pūjāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:235.8"
msgid ""
"Na kho, ānanda, ettāvatā tathāgato sakkato vā hoti garukato vā mānito vā "
"pūjito vā apacito vā."
msgstr ""
"“That’s not how the Realized One is honored, respected, revered, venerated, "
"and esteemed."

# This calls back to the description of the fourfold assembly in the Mara section above.
#. VAR: apaciyati → idaṃ padaṃ bj, s1-3, km, pts1 potthakesu na
msgctxt "dn16:235.9"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, ānanda, bhikkhu vā bhikkhunī vā upāsako vā upāsikā vā "
"dhammānudhammappaṭipanno viharati sāmīcippaṭipanno anudhammacārī, so "
"tathāgataṃ sakkaroti garuṃ karoti māneti pūjeti apaciyati, paramāya pūjāya."
msgstr ""
"Any monk or nun or male or female lay follower who practices in line with "
"the teachings, practicing properly, living in line with the teachings—they "
"honor, respect, revere, venerate, and esteem the Realized One with the "
"highest honor."

msgctxt "dn16:235.10"
msgid ""
"Tasmātihānanda, dhammānudhammappaṭipannā viharissāma sāmīcippaṭipannā "
"anudhammacārinoti."
msgstr ""
"So Ānanda, you should train like this: ‘We shall practice in line with the "
"teachings, practicing properly, living in line with the teaching.’"

msgctxt "dn16:235.11"
msgid "Evañhi vo, ānanda, sikkhitabban”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:236.1"
msgid "27. Upavāṇatthera"
msgstr "The Monk Upavāṇa"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="197"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.4"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.139"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:237.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upavāṇo bhagavato purato ṭhito hoti "
"bhagavantaṃ bījayamāno."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Venerable Upavāṇa was standing in front of the Buddha "
"fanning him."

msgctxt "dn16:237.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ upavāṇaṃ apasāresi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha made him move:"

msgctxt "dn16:237.3"
msgid "“apehi, bhikkhu, mā me purato aṭṭhāsī”ti."
msgstr "“Move over, mendicant, don’t stand in front of me.”"

msgctxt "dn16:237.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato ānandassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Ānanda thought:"

# In AN 5.166, Ananda goes to Upavana for support when he feels he has disappointed the Buddha.
msgctxt "dn16:237.5"
msgid ""
"“ayaṃ kho āyasmā upavāṇo dīgharattaṃ bhagavato upaṭṭhāko santikāvacaro "
"samīpacārī."
msgstr ""
"“This Venerable Upavāṇa has been the Buddha’s attendant for a long time, "
"close to him, living in his presence."

msgctxt "dn16:237.6"
msgid "Atha ca pana bhagavā pacchime kāle āyasmantaṃ upavāṇaṃ apasāreti:"
msgstr "Yet in his final hour the Buddha makes him move, saying:"

msgctxt "dn16:237.7"
msgid "‘apehi, bhikkhu, mā me purato aṭṭhāsī’ti."
msgstr "‘Move over, mendicant, don’t stand in front of me.’"

msgctxt "dn16:237.8"
msgid "Ko nu kho hetu, ko paccayo, yaṃ bhagavā āyasmantaṃ upavāṇaṃ apasāreti:"
msgstr "What is the cause, what is the reason for this?”"

msgctxt "dn16:237.9"
msgid "‘apehi, bhikkhu, mā me purato aṭṭhāsī’”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="198"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.5"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:238.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Ānanda said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn16:238.2"
msgid ""
"“ayaṃ, bhante, āyasmā upavāṇo dīgharattaṃ bhagavato upaṭṭhāko santikāvacaro "
"samīpacārī."
msgstr ""
"“This Venerable Upavāṇa has been the Buddha’s attendant for a long time, "
"close to him, living in his presence."

msgctxt "dn16:238.3"
msgid "Atha ca pana bhagavā pacchime kāle āyasmantaṃ upavāṇaṃ apasāreti:"
msgstr "Yet in his final hour the Buddha makes him move, saying:"

msgctxt "dn16:238.4"
msgid "‘apehi, bhikkhu, mā me purato aṭṭhāsī’ti."
msgstr "‘Move over, mendicant, don’t stand in front of me.’"

msgctxt "dn16:238.5"
msgid ""
"Ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yaṃ bhagavā āyasmantaṃ upavāṇaṃ "
"apasāreti:"
msgstr "What is the cause, sir, what is the reason for this?”"

msgctxt "dn16:238.6"
msgid "‘apehi, bhikkhu, mā me purato aṭṭhāsī’”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:238.7"
msgid ""
"“Yebhuyyena, ānanda, dasasu lokadhātūsu devatā sannipatitā tathāgataṃ "
"dassanāya."
msgstr ""
"“Most of the deities from ten solar systems have gathered to see the "
"Realized One."

# For this usage of phuta, cp AN 3.56
msgctxt "dn16:238.8"
msgid ""
"Yāvatā, ānanda, kusinārā upavattanaṃ mallānaṃ sālavanaṃ samantato dvādasa "
"yojanāni, natthi so padeso vālaggakoṭinittudanamattopi mahesakkhāhi devatāhi "
"apphuṭo."
msgstr ""
"For twelve leagues all around this <i>sal</i> grove there’s no spot, not "
"even a fraction of a hair’s tip, that’s not crowded full of illustrious "
"deities."

msgctxt "dn16:238.9"
msgid "Devatā, ānanda, ujjhāyanti:"
msgstr "The deities are complaining:"

# Sounding much like whinging tourists!
msgctxt "dn16:238.10"
msgid "‘dūrā ca vatamha āgatā tathāgataṃ dassanāya."
msgstr "‘We’ve come such a long way to see the Realized One!"

msgctxt "dn16:238.11"
msgid "Kadāci karahaci tathāgatā loke uppajjanti arahanto sammāsambuddhā."
msgstr ""
"Only rarely do Realized Ones arise in the world, perfected ones, fully "
"awakened Buddhas."

msgctxt "dn16:238.12"
msgid "Ajjeva rattiyā pacchime yāme tathāgatassa parinibbānaṃ bhavissati."
msgstr ""
"This very day, in the last watch of the night, the Realized One will become "
"fully extinguished."

msgctxt "dn16:238.13"
msgid ""
"Ayañca mahesakkho bhikkhu bhagavato purato ṭhito ovārento, na mayaṃ labhāma "
"pacchime kāle tathāgataṃ dassanāyā’”ti."
msgstr ""
"And this illustrious mendicant is standing in front of the Buddha blocking "
"the view. We won’t get to see the Realized One in his final hour!’”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="199"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.6"></a>
#. VAR: manasikarotī”ti → manasika­ron­tīti (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "dn16:239.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃbhūtā pana, bhante, bhagavā devatā manasikarotī”ti?"
msgstr "“But sir, what kind of deities are you thinking of?”"

# reading chinnaṃpādaṃ viya papatanti
#. VAR: chinnapātaṃ papatanti → chinnaṃpādaṃ viya papatanti (s1-3) |
#. chinnapātaṃ viyapapatanti (km) | chinnapapātaṃ papatanti (pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:239.2"
msgid ""
"“Santānanda, devatā ākāse pathavīsaññiniyo kese pakiriya kandanti, bāhā "
"paggayha kandanti, chinnapātaṃ papatanti, āvaṭṭanti, vivaṭṭanti:"
msgstr ""
"“There are, Ānanda, deities—both in the sky and on the earth—who are "
"percipient of the earth. With hair disheveled and arms raised, they fall "
"down like their feet were chopped off, rolling back and forth, lamenting:"

# Following Anandajoti, cakkhuma is the most obvious reading. Note that while antaradhayi usually takes the locative, the English idiom makes more sense with ablative.
#. VAR: cakkhuṃ → cakkhumā (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "dn16:239.3"
msgid ""
"‘atikhippaṃ bhagavā parinibbāyissati, atikhippaṃ sugato parinibbāyissati, "
"atikhippaṃ cakkhuṃ loke antaradhāyissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Too soon the Blessed One will become fully extinguished! Too soon the Holy "
"One will become fully extinguished! Too soon the seer will vanish from the "
"world!’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="200"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.140"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:240.1"
msgid ""
"Santānanda, devatā pathaviyaṃ pathavīsaññiniyo kese pakiriya kandanti, bāhā "
"paggayha kandanti, chinnapātaṃ papatanti, āvaṭṭanti, vivaṭṭanti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:240.2"
msgid ""
"‘atikhippaṃ bhagavā parinibbāyissati, atikhippaṃ sugato parinibbāyissati, "
"atikhippaṃ cakkhuṃ loke antaradhāyissatī’ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="201"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:241.1"
msgid "Yā pana tā devatā vītarāgā, tā satā sampajānā adhivāsenti:"
msgstr ""
"But the deities who are free of desire endure, mindful and aware, thinking:"

# Thus quoting from the sutta itself.
msgctxt "dn16:241.2"
msgid "‘aniccā saṅkhārā, taṃ kutettha labbhā’”ti."
msgstr "‘Conditions are impermanent. How could it be otherwise?’”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:242.1"
msgid "28. Catusaṃvejanīyaṭhāna"
msgstr "The Four Inspiring Places"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="202"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.7"></a>
#. VAR: vassaṃvuṭṭhā → vassaṃ vutthā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:243.1"
msgid ""
"“Pubbe, bhante, disāsu vassaṃvuṭṭhā bhikkhū āgacchanti tathāgataṃ dassanāya."
msgstr ""
"“Previously, sir, when mendicants had completed the rainy season residence "
"in various districts they came to see the Realized One."

msgctxt "dn16:243.2"
msgid ""
"Te mayaṃ labhāma manobhāvanīye bhikkhū dassanāya, labhāma payirupāsanāya."
msgstr "We got to see the esteemed mendicants, and to pay homage to them."

msgctxt "dn16:243.3"
msgid ""
"Bhagavato pana mayaṃ, bhante, accayena na labhissāma manobhāvanīye bhikkhū "
"dassanāya, na labhissāma payirupāsanāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"But when the Buddha has passed, we won’t get to see the esteemed mendicants "
"or to pay homage to them.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="203"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.8"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.141"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:244.1"
msgid ""
"“Cattārimāni, ānanda, saddhassa kulaputtassa dassanīyāni saṃvejanīyāni "
"ṭhānāni."
msgstr ""
"“Ānanda, a faithful person of good family should go to see these four "
"inspiring places."

msgctxt "dn16:244.2"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "dn16:244.3"
msgid ""
"‘Idha tathāgato jāto’ti, ānanda, saddhassa kulaputtassa dassanīyaṃ "
"saṃvejanīyaṃ ṭhānaṃ."
msgstr "Thinking: ‘Here the Realized One was born!’—that is an inspiring place."

msgctxt "dn16:244.4"
msgid ""
"‘Idha tathāgato anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddho’ti, ānanda, saddhassa "
"kulaputtassa dassanīyaṃ saṃvejanīyaṃ ṭhānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Thinking: ‘Here the Realized One became awakened as a supreme fully awakened "
"Buddha!’—that is an inspiring place."

# Note that this is in passive voice, whereas the parallel at AN 4.118 is active.
msgctxt "dn16:244.5"
msgid ""
"‘Idha tathāgatena anuttaraṃ dhammacakkaṃ pavattitan’ti, ānanda, saddhassa "
"kulaputtassa dassanīyaṃ saṃvejanīyaṃ ṭhānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Thinking: ‘Here the supreme Wheel of Dharma was rolled forth by the Realized "
"One!’—that is an inspiring place."

msgctxt "dn16:244.6"
msgid ""
"‘Idha tathāgato anupādisesāya nibbānadhātuyā parinibbuto’ti, ānanda, "
"saddhassa kulaputtassa dassanīyaṃ saṃvejanīyaṃ ṭhānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Thinking: ‘Here the Realized One became fully extinguished through the "
"natural principle of extinguishment, without anything left over!’—that is an "
"inspiring place."

msgctxt "dn16:244.7"
msgid ""
"Imāni kho, ānanda, cattāri saddhassa kulaputtassa dassanīyāni saṃvejanīyāni "
"ṭhānāni."
msgstr ""
"These are the four inspiring places that a faithful person of good family "
"should go to see."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="204"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:245.1"
msgid "Āgamissanti kho, ānanda, saddhā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo upāsakā upāsikāyo:"
msgstr "Faithful monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen will come, and think:"

msgctxt "dn16:245.2"
msgid ""
"‘idha tathāgato jāto’tipi, ‘idha tathāgato anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ "
"abhisambuddho’tipi, ‘idha tathāgatena anuttaraṃ dhammacakkaṃ pavattitan’"
"tipi, ‘idha tathāgato anupādisesāya nibbānadhātuyā parinibbuto’tipi."
msgstr ""
"‘Here the Realized One was born!’ and ‘Here the Realized One became awakened "
"as a supreme fully awakened Buddha!’ and ‘Here the supreme Wheel of Dharma "
"was rolled forth by the Realized One!’ and ‘Here the Realized One became "
"fully extinguished through the natural principle of extinguishment, without "
"anything left over!’"

msgctxt "dn16:245.3"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, ānanda, cetiyacārikaṃ āhiṇḍantā pasannacittā kālaṃ karissanti, "
"sabbe te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Anyone who passes away while on pilgrimage to these shrines will, when their "
"body breaks up, after death, be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:246.1"
msgid "29. Ānandapucchākathā"
msgstr "Questions for Ānanda"

# https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/what-the-buddha-said-to-ananda-about-women/5779
#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="205"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.9"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:247.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃ mayaṃ, bhante, mātugāme paṭipajjāmā”ti?"
msgstr "“Sir, how do we proceed when it comes to females?”"

msgctxt "dn16:247.2"
msgid "“Adassanaṃ, ānandā”ti."
msgstr "“Without seeing, Ānanda.”"

# https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/what-the-buddha-said-to-ananda-about-women-some-textual-issues/5788
msgctxt "dn16:247.3"
msgid "“Dassane, bhagavā, sati kathaṃ paṭipajjitabban”ti?"
msgstr "“But when seeing, how to proceed?”"

msgctxt "dn16:247.4"
msgid "“Anālāpo, ānandā”ti."
msgstr "“Without getting into conversation, Ānanda.”"

msgctxt "dn16:247.5"
msgid "“Ālapantena pana, bhante, kathaṃ paṭipajjitabban”ti?"
msgstr "“But when in a conversation, how to proceed?”"

msgctxt "dn16:247.6"
msgid "“Sati, ānanda, upaṭṭhāpetabbā”ti."
msgstr "“Be mindful, Ānanda.”"

# I think it is important to specify corpse here, as "body" is too vague, and "remains" might be felt to include relics.
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="206"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.10"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:248.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃ mayaṃ, bhante, tathāgatassa sarīre paṭipajjāmā”ti?"
msgstr "“Sir, how do we proceed when it comes to the Realized One’s corpse?”"

# For Abyāvaṭā, see Samaṇena bhavitabbaṃ abyāvaṭena at SS 5. More don't get involved" than "don't worry". Normally I render puja as "venerate, honor" but here it refers to specific rites, as below.
msgctxt "dn16:248.2"
msgid "“ Abyāvaṭā tumhe, ānanda, hotha tathāgatassa sarīrapūjāya."
msgstr ""
"“Don’t get involved in the rites for venerating the Realized One’s corpse, "
"Ānanda."

# Read sadattha.
#. VAR: ghaṭatha anuyuñjatha → sadat­tha­manu­yuj­ja­tha (bj) | sadatthe
#. anuyuñjatha (s1-3, km) | sadattham anuyuñjatha (pts1) | sāratthe anuyuñjatha
#. (mr)
#. VAR: sāratthe → sadatthe (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:248.3"
msgid ""
"Iṅgha tumhe, ānanda, sāratthe ghaṭatha anuyuñjatha, sāratthe appamattā "
"ātāpino pahitattā viharatha."
msgstr ""
"Please, Ānanda, you must all strive and practice for your own goal! Meditate "
"diligent, keen, and resolute for your own goal!"

msgctxt "dn16:248.4"
msgid ""
"Santānanda, khattiyapaṇḍitāpi brāhmaṇapaṇḍitāpi gahapatipaṇḍitāpi tathāgate "
"abhippasannā, te tathāgatassa sarīrapūjaṃ karissantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"There are astute aristocrats, brahmins, and householders who are devoted to "
"the Realized One. They will perform the rites for venerating the Realized "
"One’s corpse.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="207"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.11"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.142"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:249.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃ pana, bhante, tathāgatassa sarīre paṭipajjitabban”ti?"
msgstr "“But sir, how to proceed when it comes to the Realized One’s corpse?”"

msgctxt "dn16:249.2"
msgid ""
"“Yathā kho, ānanda, rañño cakkavattissa sarīre paṭipajjanti, evaṃ "
"tathāgatassa sarīre paṭipajjitabban”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Proceed in the same way as they do for the corpse of a wheel-turning "
"monarch.”"

msgctxt "dn16:249.3"
msgid "“Kathaṃ pana, bhante, rañño cakkavattissa sarīre paṭipajjantī”ti?"
msgstr "“But how do they proceed with a wheel-turning monarch’s corpse?”"

# Ahata is not "clean" as such. In pi-tv-kd8#93 it is contrasted with cloth that has been stretched thin through use.
#. VAR: sarīraṃ → sarīre (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "dn16:249.4"
msgid ""
"“Rañño, ānanda, cakkavattissa sarīraṃ ahatena vatthena veṭhenti, ahatena "
"vatthena veṭhetvā vihatena kappāsena veṭhenti, vihatena kappāsena veṭhetvā "
"ahatena vatthena veṭhenti."
msgstr ""
"“They wrap a wheel-turning monarch’s corpse with unworn cloth, then with "
"uncarded cotton, then again with unworn cloth."

# https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/the-first-fisk-casket/2245
msgctxt "dn16:249.5"
msgid ""
"Etenupāyena pañcahi yugasatehi rañño cakkavattissa sarīraṃ veṭhetvā āyasāya "
"teladoṇiyā pakkhipitvā aññissā āyasāya doṇiyā paṭikujjitvā sabbagandhānaṃ "
"citakaṃ karitvā rañño cakkavattissa sarīraṃ jhāpenti."
msgstr ""
"In this way they wrap the corpse with five hundred double-layers. Then they "
"place it in an iron case filled with oil and close it up with another case. "
"Then, having built a funeral pyre out of all kinds of fragrant substances, "
"they cremate the corpse."

#. VAR: Cātumahāpathe → cātummahāpathe (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:249.6"
msgid "Cātumahāpathe rañño cakkavattissa thūpaṃ karonti."
msgstr "They build a monument for the wheel-turning monarch at the crossroads."

msgctxt "dn16:249.7"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, ānanda, rañño cakkavattissa sarīre paṭipajjanti."
msgstr "That’s how they proceed with a wheel-turning monarch’s corpse."

msgctxt "dn16:249.8"
msgid ""
"Yathā kho, ānanda, rañño cakkavattissa sarīre paṭipajjanti, evaṃ "
"tathāgatassa sarīre paṭipajjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "Proceed in the same way with the Realized One’s corpse."

msgctxt "dn16:249.9"
msgid "Cātumahāpathe tathāgatassa thūpo kātabbo."
msgstr "A monument for the Realized One is to be built at the crossroads."

#. VAR: cuṇṇakaṃ → vaṇṇakaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:249.10"
msgid ""
"Tattha ye mālaṃ vā gandhaṃ vā cuṇṇakaṃ vā āropessanti vā abhivādessanti vā "
"cittaṃ vā pasādessanti tesaṃ taṃ bhavissati dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāya."
msgstr ""
"When someone there lifts up garlands or fragrance or powder, or bows, or "
"inspires confidence in their heart, that will be for their lasting welfare "
"and happiness."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:250.1"
msgid "30. Thūpārahapuggala"
msgstr "Persons Worthy of Monument"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="208"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.12"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:251.1"
msgid "Cattārome, ānanda, thūpārahā."
msgstr "Ānanda, these four are worthy of a monument."

msgctxt "dn16:251.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four? "

#. VAR: cakkavattī → cakkavatti (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "dn16:251.3"
msgid ""
"Tathāgato arahaṃ sammāsambuddho thūpāraho, paccekasambuddho thūpāraho, "
"tathāgatassa sāvako thūpāraho, rājā cakkavattī thūpārahoti."
msgstr ""
"A Realized One, a perfect one, a fully awakened Buddha; a Buddha awakened "
"for themselves; a disciple of a Realized One; and a wheel-turning monarch."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="209"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:252.1"
msgid ""
"Kiñcānanda, atthavasaṃ paṭicca tathāgato arahaṃ sammāsambuddho thūpāraho?"
msgstr "And for what reason is a Realized One worthy of a monument?"

msgctxt "dn16:252.2"
msgid ""
"‘Ayaṃ tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa thūpo’ti, ānanda, bahujanā "
"cittaṃ pasādenti."
msgstr ""
"So that many people will inspire confidence in their hearts, thinking: ‘This "
"is the monument for that Blessed One, perfected and fully awakened!’"

msgctxt "dn16:252.3"
msgid ""
"Te tattha cittaṃ pasādetvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ "
"upapajjanti."
msgstr ""
"And having done so, when their body breaks up, after death, they are reborn "
"in a good place, a heavenly realm."

msgctxt "dn16:252.4"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ kho, ānanda, atthavasaṃ paṭicca tathāgato arahaṃ sammāsambuddho "
"thūpāraho."
msgstr "It is for this reason that a Realized One is worthy of a monument."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="210"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.143"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:253.1"
msgid "Kiñcānanda, atthavasaṃ paṭicca paccekasambuddho thūpāraho?"
msgstr ""
"And for what reason is a Buddha awakened for themselves worthy of a monument?"

msgctxt "dn16:253.2"
msgid ""
"‘Ayaṃ tassa bhagavato paccekasambuddhassa thūpo’ti, ānanda, bahujanā cittaṃ "
"pasādenti."
msgstr ""
"So that many people will inspire confidence in their hearts, thinking: ‘This "
"is the monument for that Buddha awakened for themeselves!’"

msgctxt "dn16:253.3"
msgid ""
"Te tattha cittaṃ pasādetvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ "
"upapajjanti."
msgstr ""
"And having done so, when their body breaks up, after death, they are reborn "
"in a good place, a heavenly realm."

msgctxt "dn16:253.4"
msgid "Idaṃ kho, ānanda, atthavasaṃ paṭicca paccekasambuddho thūpāraho."
msgstr ""
"It is for this reason that a Buddha awakened for themselves is worthy of a "
"monument."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="211"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:254.1"
msgid "Kiñcānanda, atthavasaṃ paṭicca tathāgatassa sāvako thūpāraho?"
msgstr "And for what reason is a Realized One’s disciple worthy of a monument?"

msgctxt "dn16:254.2"
msgid ""
"‘Ayaṃ tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa sāvakassa thūpo’ti, ānanda, "
"bahujanā cittaṃ pasādenti."
msgstr ""
"So that many people will inspire confidence in their hearts, thinking: ‘This "
"is the monument for that Blessed One’s disciple!’"

msgctxt "dn16:254.3"
msgid ""
"Te tattha cittaṃ pasādetvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ "
"upapajjanti."
msgstr ""
"And having done so, when their body breaks up, after death, they are reborn "
"in a good place, a heavenly realm."

msgctxt "dn16:254.4"
msgid "Idaṃ kho, ānanda, atthavasaṃ paṭicca tathāgatassa sāvako thūpāraho."
msgstr ""
"It is for this reason that a Realized One’s disciple is worthy of a monument."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="212"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:255.1"
msgid "Kiñcānanda, atthavasaṃ paṭicca rājā cakkavattī thūpāraho?"
msgstr "And for what reason is a wheel-turning monarch worthy of a monument?"

msgctxt "dn16:255.2"
msgid ""
"‘Ayaṃ tassa dhammikassa dhammarañño thūpo’ti, ānanda, bahujanā cittaṃ "
"pasādenti."
msgstr ""
"So that many people will inspire confidence in their hearts, thinking: ‘This "
"is the monument for that just and principled king!’"

msgctxt "dn16:255.3"
msgid ""
"Te tattha cittaṃ pasādetvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ "
"upapajjanti."
msgstr ""
"And having done so, when their body breaks up, after death, they are reborn "
"in a good place, a heavenly realm."

msgctxt "dn16:255.4"
msgid "Idaṃ kho, ānanda, atthavasaṃ paṭicca rājā cakkavattī thūpāraho."
msgstr ""
"It is for this reason that a wheel-turning monarch is worthy of a monument."

msgctxt "dn16:255.5"
msgid "Ime kho, ānanda, cattāro thūpārahā”ti."
msgstr "These four are worthy of a monument.”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:256.1"
msgid "31. Ānandaacchariyadhamma"
msgstr "Ānanda’s Incredible Qualities"

# kapisisa is door jamb, not lintel.
#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="213"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.13"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.144"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:257.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando vihāraṃ pavisitvā kapisīsaṃ ālambitvā rodamāno "
"aṭṭhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Ānanda entered a dwelling, and stood there leaning against "
"the door-jamb and crying:"

msgctxt "dn16:257.2"
msgid ""
"“ahañca vatamhi sekho sakaraṇīyo, satthu ca me parinibbānaṃ bhavissati, yo "
"mama anukampako”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Oh! I’m still only a trainee with work left to do; and my Teacher’s about "
"to become fully extinguished, he who is so kind to me!”"

msgctxt "dn16:257.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to the mendicants:"

msgctxt "dn16:257.4"
msgid "“kahaṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, ānando”ti?"
msgstr "“Mendicants, where is Ānanda?”"

msgctxt "dn16:257.5"
msgid ""
"“Eso, bhante, āyasmā ānando vihāraṃ pavisitvā kapisīsaṃ ālambitvā rodamāno "
"ṭhito:"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, Ānanda has entered a dwelling, and stands there leaning against the "
"door-jamb and crying:"

msgctxt "dn16:257.6"
msgid ""
"‘ahañca vatamhi sekho sakaraṇīyo, satthu ca me parinibbānaṃ bhavissati, yo "
"mama anukampako’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Oh! I’m still only a trainee with work left to do; and my Teacher’s about "
"to become fully extinguished, he who is so kind to me!’"

msgctxt "dn16:257.7"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "So the Buddha said to a certain monk: "

msgctxt "dn16:257.8"
msgid "“ehi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mama vacanena ānandaṃ āmantehi:"
msgstr "“Please, monk, in my name tell Ānanda that"

msgctxt "dn16:257.9"
msgid "‘satthā taṃ, āvuso ānanda, āmantetī’”ti."
msgstr "the teacher summons him.”"

msgctxt "dn16:257.10"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato paṭissutvā yenāyasmā ānando "
"tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” that monk replied. He went to Ānanda"

msgctxt "dn16:257.11"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

msgctxt "dn16:257.12"
msgid "“satthā taṃ, āvuso ānanda, āmantetī”ti."
msgstr "“Reverend Ānanda, the teacher calls you.”"

msgctxt "dn16:257.13"
msgid ""
"“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā ānando tassa bhikkhuno paṭissutvā yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” Ānanda replied. He went to the Buddha,"

msgctxt "dn16:257.14"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed, and sat down to one side."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="214"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.14"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:258.1"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said to him: "

msgctxt "dn16:258.2"
msgid ""
"“ alaṃ, ānanda, mā soci mā paridevi, nanu etaṃ, ānanda, mayā paṭikacceva "
"akkhātaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“Enough, Ānanda! Do not grieve, do not lament. Did I not prepare for this "
"when I explained that"

msgctxt "dn16:258.3"
msgid "‘sabbeheva piyehi manāpehi nānābhāvo vinābhāvo aññathābhāvo’;"
msgstr "we must be parted and separated from all we hold dear and beloved?"

msgctxt "dn16:258.4"
msgid "taṃ kutettha, ānanda, labbhā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:258.5"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ taṃ jātaṃ bhūtaṃ saṅkhataṃ palokadhammaṃ, ‘taṃ vata tathāgatassāpi "
"sarīraṃ mā palujjī’ti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"How could anyone make it so that what is born, created, conditioned, and "
"liable to fall apart should not fall apart, even the Realized One’s body?"

# advayena appamāṇena seem out of place here, normally they describe jhana, AN 10.25. But it is also found in the Skt: ānanda maitreṇa kāyakarmaṇā hitena sukhenādvayenāpramāṇena
msgctxt "dn16:258.6"
msgid ""
"Dīgharattaṃ kho te, ānanda, tathāgato paccupaṭṭhito mettena kāyakammena "
"hitena sukhena advayena appamāṇena, mettena vacīkammena hitena sukhena "
"advayena appamāṇena, mettena manokammena hitena sukhena advayena appamāṇena."
msgstr ""
"For a long time, Ānanda, you’ve treated the Realized One with deeds of body, "
"speech, and mind that are loving, beneficial, pleasant, whole-hearted, and "
"limitless."

msgctxt "dn16:258.7"
msgid "Katapuññosi tvaṃ, ānanda, padhānamanuyuñja, khippaṃ hohisi anāsavo”ti."
msgstr ""
"You have done good deeds, Ānanda. Devote yourself to meditation, and you "
"will soon be free of defilements.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="215"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.15"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.145"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:259.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to the mendicants: "

# Cp SN 47.14, DN 20
msgctxt "dn16:259.2"
msgid ""
"“yepi te, bhikkhave, ahesuṃ atītamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā, tesampi "
"bhagavantānaṃ etapparamāyeva upaṭṭhākā ahesuṃ, seyyathāpi mayhaṃ ānando."
msgstr ""
"“The Buddhas of the past or the future have attendants who are no better "
"than Ānanda is for me."

msgctxt "dn16:259.3"
msgid ""
"Yepi te, bhikkhave, bhavissanti anāgatamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā, "
"tesampi bhagavantānaṃ etapparamāyeva upaṭṭhākā bhavissanti, seyyathāpi "
"mayhaṃ ānando."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:259.4"
msgid "Paṇḍito, bhikkhave, ānando;"
msgstr "Ānanda is astute,"

msgctxt "dn16:259.5"
msgid "medhāvī, bhikkhave, ānando."
msgstr "he is intelligent."

msgctxt "dn16:259.6"
msgid ""
"Jānāti ‘ayaṃ kālo tathāgataṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ bhikkhūnaṃ, ayaṃ kālo "
"bhikkhunīnaṃ, ayaṃ kālo upāsakānaṃ, ayaṃ kālo upāsikānaṃ, ayaṃ kālo rañño "
"rājamahāmattānaṃ titthiyānaṃ titthiyasāvakānan’ti."
msgstr ""
"He knows the time for monks, nuns, laymen, laywomen, king’s ministers, "
"religious founders, and the disciples of religious founders to visit the "
"Realized One."

