#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:262.1"
msgid "32. Mahāsudassanasuttadesanā"
msgstr "Teaching the Discourse on Mahāsudassana"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="218"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.17"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:263.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Ānanda said to the Buddha: "

msgctxt "dn16:263.2"
msgid ""
"“ mā, bhante, bhagavā imasmiṃ khuddakanagarake ujjaṅgalanagarake "
"sākhānagarake parinibbāyi."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, please don’t become fully extinguished in this little hamlet, this "
"jungle hamlet, this branch hamlet."

msgctxt "dn16:263.3"
msgid "Santi, bhante, aññāni mahānagarāni, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "There are other great cities such as"

msgctxt "dn16:263.4"
msgid "campā rājagahaṃ sāvatthī sāketaṃ kosambī bārāṇasī;"
msgstr "Campā, Rājagaha, Sāvatthī, Sāketa, Kosambī, and Benares."

msgctxt "dn16:263.5"
msgid "ettha bhagavā parinibbāyatu."
msgstr "Let the Buddha become fully extinguished there."

msgctxt "dn16:263.6"
msgid ""
"Ettha bahū khattiyamahāsālā, brāhmaṇamahāsālā gahapatimahāsālā tathāgate "
"abhippasannā."
msgstr ""
"There are many propertied aristocrats, brahmins, and householders there who "
"are devoted to the Buddha."

msgctxt "dn16:263.7"
msgid "Te tathāgatassa sarīrapūjaṃ karissantī”ti “mā hevaṃ, ānanda, avaca;"
msgstr "They will perform the rites of venerating the Realized One’s corpse.” "

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:263.8"
msgid "mā hevaṃ, ānanda, avaca:"
msgstr "“Don’t say that, Ānanda! Don’t say that"

msgctxt "dn16:263.9"
msgid "‘khuddakanagarakaṃ ujjaṅgalanagarakaṃ sākhānagarakan’ti."
msgstr "this is a little hamlet, a jungle hamlet, a branch hamlet."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="219"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.18"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.147"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:264.1"
msgid ""
"Bhūtapubbaṃ, ānanda, rājā mahāsudassano nāma ahosi cakkavattī dhammiko "
"dhammarājā cāturanto vijitāvī janapadatthāvariyappatto "
"sattaratanasamannāgato."
msgstr ""
"Once upon a time there was a king named Mahāsudassana who was a wheel-"
"turning monarch, a just and principled king. His dominion extended to all "
"four sides, he achieved stability in the country, and he possessed the seven "
"treasures."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:264.2"
msgid ""
"Rañño, ānanda, mahāsudassanassa ayaṃ kusinārā kusāvatī nāma rājadhānī ahosi, "
"puratthimena ca pacchimena ca dvādasayojanāni āyāmena;"
msgstr "His capital was this Kusinārā, which at the time was named Kusāvatī. "

msgctxt "dn16:264.3"
msgid "uttarena ca dakkhiṇena ca sattayojanāni vitthārena."
msgstr ""
"It stretched for twelve leagues east to west, and seven leagues north to "
"south."

msgctxt "dn16:264.4"
msgid ""
"Kusāvatī, ānanda, rājadhānī iddhā ceva ahosi phītā ca bahujanā ca "
"ākiṇṇamanussā ca subhikkhā ca."
msgstr ""
"The royal capital of Kusāvatī was successful, prosperous, populous, full of "
"people, with plenty of food."

msgctxt "dn16:264.5"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, ānanda, devānaṃ āḷakamandā nāma rājadhānī iddhā ceva hoti phītā "
"ca bahujanā ca ākiṇṇayakkhā ca subhikkhā ca;"
msgstr ""
"It was just like Āḷakamandā, the royal capital of the gods, which is "
"successful, prosperous, populous, full of spirits, with plenty of food."

msgctxt "dn16:264.6"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, ānanda, kusāvatī rājadhānī iddhā ceva ahosi phītā ca bahujanā "
"ca ākiṇṇamanussā ca subhikkhā ca."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:264.7"
msgid ""
"Kusāvatī, ānanda, rājadhānī dasahi saddehi avivittā ahosi divā ceva "
"rattiñca, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "Kusāvatī was never free of ten sounds by day or night, namely:"

msgctxt "dn16:264.8"
msgid ""
"hatthisaddena assasaddena rathasaddena bherisaddena mudiṅgasaddena "
"vīṇāsaddena gītasaddena saṅkhasaddena sammasaddena pāṇitāḷasaddena ‘asnātha "
"pivatha khādathā’ti dasamena saddena."
msgstr ""
"the sound of elephants, horses, chariots, drums, clay drums, arched harps, "
"singing, horns, gongs, and handbells; and the cry ‘Eat, drink, be merry!’ as "
"the tenth."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="220"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.19"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:265.1"
msgid ""
"Gaccha tvaṃ, ānanda, kusināraṃ pavisitvā kosinārakānaṃ mallānaṃ ārocehi:"
msgstr "Go, Ānanda, into Kusinārā and inform the Mallians:"

msgctxt "dn16:265.2"
msgid ""
"‘ajja kho, vāseṭṭhā, rattiyā pacchime yāme tathāgatassa parinibbānaṃ "
"bhavissati."
msgstr ""
"‘This very day, Vāseṭṭhas, in the last watch of the night, the Realized One "
"will become fully extinguished."

msgctxt "dn16:265.3"
msgid "Abhikkamatha, vāseṭṭhā, abhikkamatha, vāseṭṭhā."
msgstr "Come forth, Vāseṭṭhas! Come forth, Vāseṭṭhas!"

msgctxt "dn16:265.4"
msgid "Mā pacchā vippaṭisārino ahuvattha—"
msgstr "Don’t regret it later, thinking:"

msgctxt "dn16:265.5"
msgid ""
"amhākañca no gāmakkhette tathāgatassa parinibbānaṃ ahosi, na mayaṃ labhimhā "
"pacchime kāle tathāgataṃ dassanāyā’”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The Realized One became fully extinguished in our own village district, but "
"we didn’t get a chance to see him in his final hour.”’”"

msgctxt "dn16:265.6"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paṭissutvā nivāsetvā "
"pattacīvaramādāya attadutiyo kusināraṃ pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"“Yes, sir,” replied Ānanda. Then he robed up and, taking his bowl and robes, "
"entered Sāvatthī with a companion."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:266.1"
msgid "33. Mallānaṃvandanā"
msgstr "The Mallians Pay Homage"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="221"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.20"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.148"></a>
#. VAR: sandhāgāre → santhāgāre (bj, pts1) | saṇṭhāgāre (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn16:267.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena kosinārakā mallā sandhāgāre sannipatitā honti "
"kenacideva karaṇīyena."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the Mallians of Kusinārā were sitting together at the "
"meeting hall on some business."

msgctxt "dn16:267.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena kosinārakānaṃ mallānaṃ sandhāgāraṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Ānanda went up to them,"

msgctxt "dn16:267.3"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā kosinārakānaṃ mallānaṃ ārocesi:"
msgstr "and announced:"

msgctxt "dn16:267.4"
msgid ""
"“ajja kho, vāseṭṭhā, rattiyā pacchime yāme tathāgatassa parinibbānaṃ "
"bhavissati."
msgstr ""
"“This very day, Vāseṭṭhas, in the last watch of the night, the Realized One "
"will become fully extinguished."

msgctxt "dn16:267.5"
msgid "Abhikkamatha, vāseṭṭhā, abhikkamatha, vāseṭṭhā."
msgstr "Come forth, Vāseṭṭhas! Come forth, Vāseṭṭhas!"

msgctxt "dn16:267.6"
msgid "Mā pacchā vippaṭisārino ahuvattha:"
msgstr "Don’t regret it later, thinking:"

msgctxt "dn16:267.7"
msgid ""
"‘amhākañca no gāmakkhette tathāgatassa parinibbānaṃ ahosi, na mayaṃ labhimhā "
"pacchime kāle tathāgataṃ dassanāyā’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The Realized One became fully extinguished in our own village district, but "
"we didn’t get a chance to see him in his final hour.’”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="222"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.21"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:268.1"
msgid ""
"Idamāyasmato ānandassa vacanaṃ sutvā mallā ca mallaputtā ca mallasuṇisā ca "
"mallapajāpatiyo ca aghāvino dummanā cetodukkhasamappitā appekacce kese "
"pakiriya kandanti, bāhā paggayha kandanti, chinnapātaṃ papatanti, āvaṭṭanti "
"vivaṭṭanti:"
msgstr ""
"When they heard what Ānanda had to say, the Mallians, their sons, daughters-"
"in-law, and wives became distraught, saddened, and grief-stricken. And some, "
"with hair disheveled and arms raised, falling down like their feet were "
"chopped off, rolling back and forth, lamented:"

msgctxt "dn16:268.2"
msgid ""
"“atikhippaṃ bhagavā parinibbāyissati, atikhippaṃ sugato parinibbāyissati, "
"atikhippaṃ cakkhuṃ loke antaradhāyissatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Too soon the Blessed One will become fully extinguished! Too soon the Holy "
"One will become fully extinguished! Too soon the seer will vanish from the "
"world!”"

msgctxt "dn16:268.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho mallā ca mallaputtā ca mallasuṇisā ca mallapajāpatiyo ca aghāvino "
"dummanā cetodukkhasamappitā yena upavattanaṃ mallānaṃ sālavanaṃ yenāyasmā "
"ānando tenupasaṅkamiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then the Mallians, their sons, daughters-in-law, and wives, distraught, "
"saddened, and grief-stricken went to the Mallian <i>sal</i> grove at "
"Upavattana and approached Ānanda."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp5.22"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:268.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato ānandassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Ānanda thought:"

msgctxt "dn16:268.5"
msgid ""
"“sace kho ahaṃ kosinārake malle ekamekaṃ bhagavantaṃ vandāpessāmi, avandito "
"bhagavā kosinārakehi mallehi bhavissati, athāyaṃ ratti vibhāyissati."
msgstr ""
"“If I have the Mallians pay homage to the Buddha one by one, they won’t be "
"finished before first light."

msgctxt "dn16:268.6"
msgid ""
"Yannūnāhaṃ kosinārake malle kulaparivattaso kulaparivattaso ṭhapetvā "
"bhagavantaṃ vandāpeyyaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"I’d better separate them family by family and then have them pay homage, "
"saying:"

msgctxt "dn16:268.7"
msgid ""
"‘itthannāmo, bhante, mallo saputto sabhariyo sapariso sāmacco bhagavato pāde "
"sirasā vandatī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Sir, the Mallian named so-and-so with children, wives, retinue, and "
"ministers bows with his head at your feet.’”"

msgctxt "dn16:268.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando kosinārake malle kulaparivattaso kulaparivattaso "
"ṭhapetvā bhagavantaṃ vandāpesi:"
msgstr "And so that’s what he did."

msgctxt "dn16:268.9"
msgid ""
"“itthannāmo, bhante, mallo saputto sabhariyo sapariso sāmacco bhagavato pāde "
"sirasā vandatī”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:268.10"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando etena upāyena paṭhameneva yāmena kosinārake malle "
"bhagavantaṃ vandāpesi."
msgstr ""
"So by this means Ānanda got the Mallians to finish paying homage to the "
"Buddha in the first watch of the night."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:269.1"
msgid "34. Subhaddaparibbājakavatthu"
msgstr "On Subhadda the Wanderer"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="223"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.23"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.149"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:270.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena subhaddo nāma paribbājako kusinārāyaṃ paṭivasati."
msgstr "Now at that time a wanderer named Subhadda was residing near Kusinārā."

msgctxt "dn16:270.2"
msgid "Assosi kho subhaddo paribbājako:"
msgstr "He heard that"

msgctxt "dn16:270.3"
msgid ""
"“ajja kira rattiyā pacchime yāme samaṇassa gotamassa parinibbānaṃ "
"bhavissatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"that very day, in the last watch of the night, the ascetic Gotama would "
"become fully extinguished."

msgctxt "dn16:270.4"
msgid "Atha kho subhaddassa paribbājakassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "He thought:"

msgctxt "dn16:270.5"
msgid ""
"“sutaṃ kho pana metaṃ paribbājakānaṃ vuḍḍhānaṃ mahallakānaṃ "
"ācariyapācariyānaṃ bhāsamānānaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“I have heard that brahmins of the past who were elderly and senior, the "
"teachers of teachers, said:"

msgctxt "dn16:270.6"
msgid "‘kadāci karahaci tathāgatā loke uppajjanti arahanto sammāsambuddhā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Only rarely do Realized Ones arise in the world, perfected ones, fully "
"awakened Buddhas.’"

msgctxt "dn16:270.7"
msgid ""
"Ajjeva rattiyā pacchime yāme samaṇassa gotamassa parinibbānaṃ bhavissati."
msgstr ""
"And this very day, in the last watch of the night, the ascetic Gotama will "
"become fully extinguished."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:270.8"
msgid ""
"Atthi ca me ayaṃ kaṅkhādhammo uppanno, evaṃ pasanno ahaṃ samaṇe gotame, ‘"
"pahoti me samaṇo gotamo tathā dhammaṃ desetuṃ, yathāhaṃ imaṃ kaṅkhādhammaṃ "
"pajaheyyan’”ti."
msgstr ""
"This state of uncertainty has come up in me. I am quite confident that the "
"Buddha is capable of teaching me so that I can give up this state of "
"uncertainty.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="224"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.24"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.150"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:271.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho subhaddo paribbājako yena upavattanaṃ mallānaṃ sālavanaṃ, yenāyasmā "
"ānando tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"Then Subhadda went to the Mallian <i>sal</i> grove at Upavattana, approached "
"Ānanda,"

msgctxt "dn16:271.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

msgctxt "dn16:271.3"
msgid ""
"“sutaṃ metaṃ, bho ānanda, paribbājakānaṃ vuḍḍhānaṃ mahallakānaṃ "
"ācariyapācariyānaṃ bhāsamānānaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“Master Ānanda, I have heard that brahmins of the past who were elderly and "
"senior, the teachers of teachers, said:"

msgctxt "dn16:271.4"
msgid "‘kadāci karahaci tathāgatā loke uppajjanti arahanto sammāsambuddhā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Only rarely do Realized Ones arise in the world, perfected ones, fully "
"awakened Buddhas.’"

msgctxt "dn16:271.5"
msgid ""
"Ajjeva rattiyā pacchime yāme samaṇassa gotamassa parinibbānaṃ bhavissati."
msgstr ""
"And this very day, in the last watch of the night, the ascetic Gotama will "
"become fully extinguished."

msgctxt "dn16:271.6"
msgid "Atthi ca me ayaṃ kaṅkhādhammo uppanno—"
msgstr "This state of uncertainty has come up in me. "

msgctxt "dn16:271.7"
msgid ""
"evaṃ pasanno ahaṃ samaṇe gotame ‘pahoti me samaṇo gotamo tathā dhammaṃ "
"desetuṃ, yathāhaṃ imaṃ kaṅkhādhammaṃ pajaheyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"I am quite confident that the Buddha is capable of teaching me so that I can "
"give up this state of uncertainty."

msgctxt "dn16:271.8"
msgid "Sādhāhaṃ, bho ānanda, labheyyaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāyā”ti."
msgstr "Master Ānanda, please let me see the ascetic Gotama.”"

msgctxt "dn16:271.9"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando subhaddaṃ paribbājakaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, Ānanda said:"

msgctxt "dn16:271.10"
msgid "“alaṃ, āvuso subhadda, mā tathāgataṃ viheṭhesi, kilanto bhagavā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Enough, Reverend Subhadda, do not trouble the Realized One. He is tired.”"

msgctxt "dn16:271.11"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho subhaddo paribbājako …"
msgstr "For a second time,"

msgctxt "dn16:271.12"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:271.13"
msgid "tatiyampi kho subhaddo paribbājako āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"and a third time, Subhadda asked Ānanda, and a third time Ānanda refused."

msgctxt "dn16:271.14"
msgid ""
"“sutaṃ metaṃ, bho ānanda, paribbājakānaṃ vuḍḍhānaṃ mahallakānaṃ "
"ācariyapācariyānaṃ bhāsamānānaṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:271.15"
msgid "‘kadāci karahaci tathāgatā loke uppajjanti arahanto sammāsambuddhā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:271.16"
msgid ""
"Ajjeva rattiyā pacchime yāme samaṇassa gotamassa parinibbānaṃ bhavissati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:271.17"
msgid "Atthi ca me ayaṃ kaṅkhādhammo uppanno—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:271.18"
msgid ""
"evaṃ pasanno ahaṃ samaṇe gotame, ‘pahoti me samaṇo gotamo tathā dhammaṃ "
"desetuṃ, yathāhaṃ imaṃ kaṅkhādhammaṃ pajaheyyan’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:271.19"
msgid "Sādhāhaṃ, bho ānanda, labheyyaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāyā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:271.20"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āyasmā ānando subhaddaṃ paribbājakaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:271.21"
msgid "“alaṃ, āvuso subhadda, mā tathāgataṃ viheṭhesi, kilanto bhagavā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="225"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.25"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.151"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:272.1"
msgid ""
"Assosi kho bhagavā āyasmato ānandassa subhaddena paribbājakena saddhiṃ imaṃ "
"kathāsallāpaṃ."
msgstr "The Buddha heard that discussion between Ānanda and Subhadda."

msgctxt "dn16:272.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "He said to Ānanda: "

msgctxt "dn16:272.3"
msgid ""
"“alaṃ, ānanda, mā subhaddaṃ vāresi, labhataṃ, ānanda, subhaddo tathāgataṃ "
"dassanāya."
msgstr "“Enough, Ānanda, don’t obstruct Subhadda; let him see the Realized One."

msgctxt "dn16:272.4"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kiñci maṃ subhaddo pucchissati, sabbaṃ taṃ aññāpekkhova pucchissati, no "
"vihesāpekkho."
msgstr ""
"For whatever he asks me, he will only be looking for understanding, not "
"trouble."

msgctxt "dn16:272.5"
msgid "Yañcassāhaṃ puṭṭho byākarissāmi, taṃ khippameva ājānissatī”ti."
msgstr "And he will quickly understand any answer I give to his question.”"

msgctxt "dn16:272.6"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando subhaddaṃ paribbājakaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Ānanda said to the wanderer Subhadda:"

msgctxt "dn16:272.7"
msgid "“gacchāvuso subhadda, karoti te bhagavā okāsan”ti."
msgstr "“Go, Reverend Subhadda, the Buddha is taking the time for you.”"

#. <a class="wp" id="wp5.26"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:272.8"
msgid "Atha kho subhaddo paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then the wanderer Subhadda went up to the Buddha,"

msgctxt "dn16:272.9"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ "
"vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"and exchanged greetings with him. When the greetings and polite conversation "
"were over, he sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "dn16:272.10"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho subhaddo paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn16:272.11"
msgid ""
"“yeme, bho gotama, samaṇabrāhmaṇā saṅghino gaṇino gaṇācariyā ñātā yasassino "
"titthakarā sādhusammatā bahujanassa, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"“Master Gotama, there are those ascetics and brahmins who lead an order and "
"a community, and teach a community. They’re well known and famous religious "
"founders, regarded as holy by many people. That is:"

# See my note on the parallel at MN 30.
msgctxt "dn16:272.12"
msgid ""
"pūraṇo kassapo, makkhali gosālo, ajito kesakambalo, pakudho kaccāyano, "
"sañcayo belaṭṭhaputto, nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto, sabbete sakāya paṭiññāya "
"abbhaññiṃsu, sabbeva na abbhaññiṃsu, udāhu ekacce abbhaññiṃsu, ekacce na "
"abbhaññiṃsū”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Pūraṇa Kassapa, Makkhali Gosāla, Nigaṇṭha Nāṭaputta, Sañjaya Belaṭṭhiputta, "
"Pakudha Kaccāyana, and Ajita Kesakambala. According to their own claim, did "
"all of them have direct knowledge, or none of them, or only some?”"

msgctxt "dn16:272.13"
msgid "“Alaṃ, subhadda, tiṭṭhatetaṃ:"
msgstr "“Enough, Subhadda, let that be."

msgctxt "dn16:272.14"
msgid ""
"‘sabbete sakāya paṭiññāya abbhaññiṃsu, sabbeva na abbhaññiṃsu, udāhu ekacce "
"abbhaññiṃsu, ekacce na abbhaññiṃsū’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:272.15"
msgid "Dhammaṃ te, subhadda, desessāmi;"
msgstr "I shall teach you the Dhamma."

msgctxt "dn16:272.16"
msgid "taṃ suṇāhi sādhukaṃ manasikarohi, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "dn16:272.17"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho subhaddo paribbājako bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Subhadda replied. "

msgctxt "dn16:272.18"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="226"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.27"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:273.1"
msgid ""
"“Yasmiṃ kho, subhadda, dhammavinaye ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo na upalabbhati, "
"samaṇopi tattha na upalabbhati."
msgstr ""
"“Subhadda, in whatever teaching and training the noble eightfold path is not "
"found, there is no true ascetic found, no second ascetic, no third ascetic, "
"and no fourth ascetic."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:273.2"
msgid "Dutiyopi tattha samaṇo na upalabbhati."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn16:273.3"
msgid "Tatiyopi tattha samaṇo na upalabbhati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:273.4"
msgid "Catutthopi tattha samaṇo na upalabbhati."
msgstr ""

#. VAR: ca → idheva (mr)
msgctxt "dn16:273.5"
msgid ""
"Yasmiñca kho, subhadda, dhammavinaye ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo upalabbhati, "
"samaṇopi tattha upalabbhati, dutiyopi tattha samaṇo upalabbhati, tatiyopi "
"tattha samaṇo upalabbhati, catutthopi tattha samaṇo upalabbhati."
msgstr ""
"In whatever teaching and training the noble eightfold path is found, there "
"is a true ascetic found, a second ascetic, a third ascetic, and a fourth "
"ascetic."

#. VAR: aññehi → aññe (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:273.6"
msgid ""
"Imasmiṃ kho, subhadda, dhammavinaye ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo upalabbhati, "
"idheva, subhadda, samaṇo, idha dutiyo samaṇo, idha tatiyo samaṇo, idha "
"catuttho samaṇo, suññā parappavādā samaṇebhi aññehi."
msgstr ""
"In this teaching and training the noble eightfold path is found. Only here "
"is there a true ascetic, here a second ascetic, here a third ascetic, and "
"here a fourth ascetic. Other sects are empty of ascetics."

msgctxt "dn16:273.7"
msgid ""
"Ime ca, subhadda, bhikkhū sammā vihareyyuṃ, asuñño loko arahantehi assāti."
msgstr ""
"Were these mendicants to practice well, the world would not be empty of "
"perfected ones."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="227"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:274.1"
msgid "Ekūnatiṃso vayasā subhadda,"
msgstr "I was twenty years of age, Subaddha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:274.2"
msgid "Yaṃ pabbajiṃ kiṅkusalānuesī;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:274.3"
msgid "Vassāni paññāsa samādhikāni,"
msgstr "It’s been over fifty years"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:274.4"
msgid "Yato ahaṃ pabbajito subhadda;"
msgstr "since I went forth."

# Padesavattī is difficult. Anandajoti has "Existing in the realm of the right Teaching" evidently taking vatti in the sense of exist, be present, and padesa as a place. Walshe more poetically has "To roam the realm of wisdom’s law". Neither of these agree with comm, which has "Padesavattīti padese vipassanāmagge pavattanto". However the Sanskrit has āryasya dharmasya pradeśavaktā, where vaktā means "speaker" and pradeśa presumably has the sense "pointing out". Thus, "I have been the teacher who points out the noble teaching." While disagreeing in details, this agrees with the thrust of the comm, in that it is to do with teaching. BTW, note that the Skt text has complete verses here and is far more satisfactory. It looks like the Pali has suffered loss of a couple of padas.
#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:274.5"
msgid "Ñāyassa dhammassa padesavattī,"
msgstr "I am the one who points out the proper teaching:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:274.6"
msgid "Ito bahiddhā samaṇopi natthi."
msgstr "Outside of here there is no true ascetic."

#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="228"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.152"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:275.1"
msgid "Dutiyopi samaṇo natthi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:275.2"
msgid "Tatiyopi samaṇo natthi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:275.3"
msgid "Catutthopi samaṇo natthi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:275.4"
msgid "Suññā parappavādā samaṇebhi aññehi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:275.5"
msgid ""
"Ime ca, subhadda, bhikkhū sammā vihareyyuṃ, asuñño loko arahantehi assā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Were these mendicants to practice well, the world would not be empty of "
"perfected ones.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="229"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5.28"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:276.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, subhaddo paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Subhadda said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn16:276.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "“Excellent, sir! Excellent!"

msgctxt "dn16:276.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, "
"mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya:"
msgstr ""
"As if he was righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark  "

msgctxt "dn16:276.4"
msgid "‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti;"
msgstr "so people with good eyes can see what’s there,  "

msgctxt "dn16:276.5"
msgid "evamevaṃ bhagavatā anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr "so too the Buddha has made the teaching clear in many ways. "

msgctxt "dn16:276.6"
msgid ""
"Esāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the Dharma, and to the mendicant Saṅgha."

msgctxt "dn16:276.7"
msgid ""
"Labheyyāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyaṃ upasampadan”ti. <"
"a class=\"wp\" id=\"wp5.29\"></a>“"
msgstr ""
"Sir, may I receive the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence?”"

msgctxt "dn16:276.8"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, subhadda, aññatitthiyapubbo imasmiṃ dhammavinaye ākaṅkhati "
"pabbajjaṃ, ākaṅkhati upasampadaṃ, so cattāro māse parivasati."
msgstr ""
"“Subhadda, if someone formerly ordained in another sect wishes to take the "
"going forth, the ordination in this teaching and training, they must spend "
"four months on probation."

msgctxt "dn16:276.9"
msgid ""
"Catunnaṃ māsānaṃ accayena āraddhacittā bhikkhū pabbājenti upasampādenti "
"bhikkhubhāvāya."
msgstr ""
"When four months have passed, if the mendicants are satisfied, they’ll give "
"the going forth, the ordination into monkhood."

msgctxt "dn16:276.10"
msgid "Api ca mettha puggalavemattatā viditā”ti."
msgstr "However, I have recognized individual differences in this matter.”"

msgctxt "dn16:276.11"
msgid ""
"“Sace, bhante, aññatitthiyapubbā imasmiṃ dhammavinaye ākaṅkhantā pabbajjaṃ "
"ākaṅkhantā upasampadaṃ cattāro māse parivasanti, catunnaṃ māsānaṃ accayena "
"āraddhacittā bhikkhū pabbājenti upasampādenti bhikkhubhāvāya."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, if four months probation are required in such a case, I’ll spend four "
"years on probation. When four years have passed, if the mendicants are "
"satisfied, let them give me the going forth, the ordination into monkhood.”"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:276.12"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ cattāri vassāni parivasissāmi, catunnaṃ vassānaṃ accayena āraddhacittā "
"bhikkhū pabbājentu upasampādentu bhikkhubhāvāyā”ti."
msgstr " "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="230"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.153"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:277.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to Ānanda: "

msgctxt "dn16:277.2"
msgid "“tenahānanda, subhaddaṃ pabbājehī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, Ānanda, give Subhadda the going forth.”"

msgctxt "dn16:277.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp5.30"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:277.4"
msgid "Atha kho subhaddo paribbājako āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Subhadda said to Ānanda:"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:277.5"
msgid "“lābhā vo, āvuso ānanda;"
msgstr " "

#. VAR: satthu → satthārā (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:277.6"
msgid ""
"suladdhaṃ vo, āvuso ānanda, ye ettha satthu sammukhā antevāsikābhisekena "
"abhisittā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“You’re so fortunate, Reverand Ānanda, so very fortunate, to be anointed "
"here in the Teacher’s presence as his pupil!”"

msgctxt "dn16:277.7"
msgid ""
"Alattha kho subhaddo paribbājako bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, alattha "
"upasampadaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And the wanderer Subhadda received the going forth, the ordination in the "
"Buddha’s presence."

msgctxt "dn16:277.8"
msgid ""
"Acirūpasampanno kho panāyasmā subhaddo eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī "
"pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—"
msgstr ""
"Not long after his ordination, Venerable Subhadda, living alone, withdrawn, "
"diligent, keen, and determined, soon "

msgctxt "dn16:277.9"
msgid "yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti—"
msgstr ""
"realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. He lived "
"having achieved with his own insight the goal for which people from good "
"families rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.   "

msgctxt "dn16:277.10"
msgid ""
"tadanuttaraṃ brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:277.11"
msgid ""
"“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti "
"abbhaññāsi."
msgstr ""
"He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual life has been lived; what "
"had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.” "

msgctxt "dn16:277.12"
msgid "Aññataro kho panāyasmā subhaddo arahataṃ ahosi."
msgstr "And Venerable Subhadda became one of the perfected."

msgctxt "dn16:277.13"
msgid "So bhagavato pacchimo sakkhisāvako ahosīti."
msgstr "He was the last personal disciple of the Buddha."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn16:278.1"
msgid "Pañcamo bhāṇavāro."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:279.1"
msgid "35. Tathāgatapacchimavācā"
msgstr "The Buddha’s Last Words"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="231"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.1"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.154"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:280.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha addressed Venerable Ānanda: "

msgctxt "dn16:280.2"
msgid "“ siyā kho panānanda, tumhākaṃ evamassa:"
msgstr "“Now, Ānanda, some of you might think:"

msgctxt "dn16:280.3"
msgid "‘atītasatthukaṃ pāvacanaṃ, natthi no satthā’ti."
msgstr "‘The teacher’s dispensation has passed. Now we have no Teacher.’"

msgctxt "dn16:280.4"
msgid "Na kho panetaṃ, ānanda, evaṃ daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr "But you should not see it like this."

# It's tempting to read pannatta here as "laid down", as per Anandajoti, but see eg DN 9 "‘Sassato loko’ti kho, poṭṭhapāda, mayā anekaṃsiko dhammo desito paññatto;"
msgctxt "dn16:280.5"
msgid ""
"Yo vo, ānanda, mayā dhammo ca vinayo ca desito paññatto, so vo mamaccayena "
"satthā."
msgstr ""
"The teaching and training that I have taught and pointed out for you shall "
"be your Teacher after my passing."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp6.2"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:280.6"
msgid ""
"Yathā kho panānanda, etarahi bhikkhū aññamaññaṃ āvusovādena samudācaranti, "
"na kho mamaccayena evaṃ samudācaritabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"After my passing, mendicants ought not address each other as ‘reverend’, as "
"they do today."

msgctxt "dn16:280.7"
msgid ""
"Theratarena, ānanda, bhikkhunā navakataro bhikkhu nāmena vā gottena vā "
"āvusovādena vā samudācaritabbo."
msgstr ""
"A more senior mendicant ought to address a more junior mendicant by name or "
"clan, or by saying ‘reverend’."

msgctxt "dn16:280.8"
msgid ""
"Navakatarena bhikkhunā therataro bhikkhu ‘bhante’ti vā ‘āyasmā’ti vā "
"samudācaritabbo."
msgstr ""
"A more junior mendicant ought to address a more senior mendicant using ‘sir’ "
"or ‘venerable’."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp6.3"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:280.9"
msgid ""
"Ākaṅkhamāno, ānanda, saṃgho mamaccayena khuddānukhuddakāni sikkhāpadāni "
"samūhanatu."
msgstr ""
"If it wishes, after my passing the Saṅgha may abolish the lesser and minor "
"training rules."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp6.4"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:280.10"
msgid "Channassa, ānanda, bhikkhuno mamaccayena brahmadaṇḍo dātabbo”ti."
msgstr "After my passing, give the prime punishment to the mendicant Channa.”"

msgctxt "dn16:280.11"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante, brahmadaṇḍo”ti?"
msgstr "“But sir, what is the prime punishment?”"

msgctxt "dn16:280.12"
msgid "“Channo, ānanda, bhikkhu yaṃ iccheyya, taṃ vadeyya."
msgstr "“Channa may say what he likes,"

# the pair vattabba anusasitabba is found quite frequently, eg An 4.111, AN 10.18, MN 15, etc. These are all similar contexts. However, it seems that the more limited sense of vattabba  as "advise, correct, admonish" is applicable in such cases, for which especially see MN 15. It seems, therefore, unlikely that the brahmadanda involved actually refusing to speak to him. Normally I render ovada as "advice" or "instructions", which is also what I use for vattabba in this context, so I just have two terms in the translation.
msgctxt "dn16:280.13"
msgid "So bhikkhūhi neva vattabbo, na ovaditabbo, na anusāsitabbo”ti."
msgstr "but the mendicants should not advise or instruct him.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="232"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.5"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.155"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:281.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to the mendicants: "

msgctxt "dn16:281.2"
msgid ""
"“siyā kho pana, bhikkhave, ekabhikkhussāpi kaṅkhā vā vimati vā buddhe vā "
"dhamme vā saṅghe vā magge vā paṭipadāya vā, pucchatha, bhikkhave, mā pacchā "
"vippaṭisārino ahuvattha:"
msgstr ""
"“Perhaps even a single mendicant has doubt or uncertainty regarding the "
"Buddha, the Dharma, the Saṅgha, the path, or the practice. So ask, "
"mendicants! Don’t regret it later, thinking:"

msgctxt "dn16:281.3"
msgid ""
"‘sammukhībhūto no satthā ahosi, na mayaṃ sakkhimhā bhagavantaṃ sammukhā "
"paṭipucchitun’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘We were in the Teacher’s presence and we weren’t able to ask the Buddha a "
"question.’”"

msgctxt "dn16:281.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, te bhikkhū tuṇhī ahesuṃ."
msgstr "When this was said, the mendicants kept silent."

#. <a class="wp" id="wp6.6"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:281.5"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho bhagavā …"
msgstr "For a second time,"

msgctxt "dn16:281.6"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:281.7"
msgid "tatiyampi kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "and a third time the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "dn16:281.8"
msgid ""
"“siyā kho pana, bhikkhave, ekabhikkhussāpi kaṅkhā vā vimati vā buddhe vā "
"dhamme vā saṅghe vā magge vā paṭipadāya vā, pucchatha, bhikkhave, mā pacchā "
"vippaṭisārino ahuvattha:"
msgstr ""
"“Perhaps even a single mendicant has doubt or uncertainty regarding the "
"Buddha, the Dharma, the Saṅgha, the path, or the practice. So ask, "
"mendicants! Don’t regret it later, thinking:"

msgctxt "dn16:281.9"
msgid ""
"‘sammukhībhūto no satthā ahosi, na mayaṃ sakkhimhā bhagavantaṃ sammukhā "
"paṭipucchitun’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘We were in the Teacher’s presence and we weren’t able to ask the Buddha a "
"question.’”"

msgctxt "dn16:281.10"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho te bhikkhū tuṇhī ahesuṃ."
msgstr "For a third time, the mendicants kept silent."

msgctxt "dn16:281.11"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to the mendicants: "

msgctxt "dn16:281.12"
msgid "“siyā kho pana, bhikkhave, satthugāravenapi na puccheyyātha."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, perhaps you don’t ask out of respect for the Teacher. So let a "
"friend tell a friend.”"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:281.13"
msgid "Sahāyakopi, bhikkhave, sahāyakassa ārocetū”ti."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn16:281.14"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, te bhikkhū tuṇhī ahesuṃ."
msgstr "When this was said, the mendicants kept silent."

msgctxt "dn16:281.15"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn16:281.16"
msgid ""
"“acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante, evaṃ pasanno ahaṃ, bhante, imasmiṃ "
"bhikkhusaṅghe, ‘natthi ekabhikkhussāpi kaṅkhā vā vimati vā buddhe vā dhamme "
"vā saṅghe vā magge vā paṭipadāya vā’”ti."
msgstr ""
"“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing! I am quite confident that there’s not "
"even a single mendicant in this Saṅgha who has doubt or uncertainty "
"regarding the Buddha, the Dharma, the Saṅgha, the path, or the practice.”"

msgctxt "dn16:281.17"
msgid ""
"“Pasādā kho tvaṃ, ānanda, vadesi, ñāṇameva hettha, ānanda, tathāgatassa."
msgstr "“Ānanda, you speak from faith. But the Realized One knows that "

msgctxt "dn16:281.18"
msgid ""
"Natthi imasmiṃ bhikkhusaṅghe ekabhikkhussāpi kaṅkhā vā vimati vā buddhe vā "
"dhamme vā saṅghe vā magge vā paṭipadāya vā."
msgstr ""
"there’s not even a single mendicant in this Saṅgha who has doubt or "
"uncertainty regarding the Buddha, the Dharma, the Saṅgha, the path, or the "
"practice.”"

msgctxt "dn16:281.19"
msgid ""
"Imesañhi, ānanda, pañcannaṃ bhikkhusatānaṃ yo pacchimako bhikkhu, so "
"sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo”ti."
msgstr ""
"Even the last of these five hundred mendicants is a stream-enterer, not "
"liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="233"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.7"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.156"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:282.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to the mendicants: "

msgctxt "dn16:282.2"
msgid ""
"“handa dāni, bhikkhave, āmantayāmi vo, vayadhammā saṅkhārā appamādena "
"sampādethā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Come now, mendicants, I say to you all: Conditions fall apart. Persist with "
"diligence.”"

msgctxt "dn16:282.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ tathāgatassa pacchimā vācā."
msgstr "These were the Realized One’s last words."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:283.1"
msgid "36. Parinibbutakathā"
msgstr "The Full Extinguishment"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="234"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.8"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:284.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajji, paṭhamajjhānā vuṭṭhahitvā "
"dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajji, dutiyajjhānā vuṭṭhahitvā tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajji, "
"tatiyajjhānā vuṭṭhahitvā catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajji, catutthajjhānā "
"vuṭṭhahitvā ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samāpajji, ākāsānañcāyatanasamāpattiyā "
"vuṭṭhahitvā viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samāpajji, viññāṇañcāyatanasamāpattiyā "
"vuṭṭhahitvā ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samāpajji, ākiñcaññāyatanasamāpattiyā "
"vuṭṭhahitvā nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samāpajji, "
"nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhahitvā saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ "
"samāpajji."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha entered the first absorption. Emerging from that, he entered "
"the second absorption. Emerging from that, he successively entered into and "
"emerged from the third absorption, the fourth absorption, the dimension of "
"infinite space, the dimension of infinite consciousness, the dimension of "
"nothingness, and the dimension of neither perception nor nor perception. "
"Then he entered the cessation of perception and feeling."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="235"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:285.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda said to Venerable Anuruddha:"

# Following Anandajoti, who folows comm in seeing this as a question.
msgctxt "dn16:285.2"
msgid "“parinibbuto, bhante anuruddha, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable Anuruddha, has the Buddha become fully extinguished?”"

msgctxt "dn16:285.3"
msgid ""
"“Nāvuso ānanda, bhagavā parinibbuto, saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ samāpanno”ti."
msgstr ""
"“No, Reverend Ānanda. He has entered the cessation of perception and "
"feeling.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="236"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.9"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:286.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā saññāvedayitanirodhasamāpattiyā vuṭṭhahitvā "
"nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samāpajji, nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasamāpattiyā "
"vuṭṭhahitvā ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samāpajji, ākiñcaññāyatanasamāpattiyā "
"vuṭṭhahitvā viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samāpajji, viññāṇañcāyatanasamāpattiyā "
"vuṭṭhahitvā ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samāpajji, ākāsānañcāyatanasamāpattiyā "
"vuṭṭhahitvā catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajji, catutthajjhānā vuṭṭhahitvā tatiyaṃ "
"jhānaṃ samāpajji, tatiyajjhānā vuṭṭhahitvā dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajji, "
"dutiyajjhānā vuṭṭhahitvā paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajji, paṭhamajjhānā "
"vuṭṭhahitvā dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajji, dutiyajjhānā vuṭṭhahitvā tatiyaṃ "
"jhānaṃ samāpajji, tatiyajjhānā vuṭṭhahitvā catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajji, "
"catutthajjhānā vuṭṭhahitvā samanantarā bhagavā parinibbāyi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha emerged from the cessation of perception and feeling and "
"entered the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception. Emerging "
"from that, he successively entered into and emerged from the dimension of "
"nothingness, the dimension of infinite consciousness, the dimension of "
"infinite space, the fourth absorption, the third absorption, the second "
"absorption, and the first absorption. Emerging from that, he successively "
"entered into and emerged from the second absorption and the third "
"absorption. Then he entered the fourth absorption. Emerging from that the "
"Buddha immediately became fully extinguished."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="237"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.10"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.157"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:287.1"
msgid ""
"Parinibbute bhagavati saha parinibbānā mahābhūmicālo ahosi bhiṃsanako "
"salomahaṃso."
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha became fully extinguished, along with the full "
"extinguishment there was a great earthquake, awe-inspiring and hair-raising, "
"and thunder cracked the sky."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:287.2"
msgid "Devadundubhiyo ca phaliṃsu."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn16:287.3"
msgid ""
"Parinibbute bhagavati saha parinibbānā brahmāsahampati imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha became fully extinguished, Sakka the lord of gods recited "
"this verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="238"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:288.1"
msgid "“Sabbeva nikkhipissanti,"
msgstr "“All creatures in this world"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:288.2"
msgid "bhūtā loke samussayaṃ;"
msgstr "must lay their body down."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:288.3"
msgid "Yattha etādiso satthā,"
msgstr "For even a Teacher such as this,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:288.4"
msgid "loke appaṭipuggalo;"
msgstr "unrivaled in the world,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:288.5"
msgid "Tathāgato balappatto,"
msgstr "the Realized One, attained to power,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:288.6"
msgid "sambuddho parinibbuto”ti."
msgstr "the Buddha became finally extinguished.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="239"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:289.1"
msgid ""
"Parinibbute bhagavati saha parinibbānā sakko devānamindo imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha became fully extinguished, Sakka the lord of gods recited "
"this verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="240"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:290.1"
msgid "“Aniccā vata saṅkhārā,"
msgstr "“Oh! Conditions are impermanent,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:290.2"
msgid "uppādavayadhammino;"
msgstr "their nature’s to rise and fall;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:290.3"
msgid "Uppajjitvā nirujjhanti,"
msgstr "having arisen, they cease; "

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:290.4"
msgid "tesaṃ vūpasamo sukho”ti."
msgstr "their stilling is true bliss.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="241"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:291.1"
msgid ""
"Parinibbute bhagavati saha parinibbānā āyasmā anuruddho imā gāthāyo abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha became fully extinguished, Venerable Anuruddha recited this "
"verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="242"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:292.1"
msgid "“Nāhu assāsapassāso,"
msgstr "“There was no more breathing"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:292.2"
msgid "ṭhitacittassa tādino;"
msgstr "for the poised one of steady heart."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:292.3"
msgid "Anejo santimārabbha,"
msgstr "Imperturbable, committed to peace,"

# Of the two variants of this line, note that Skt attributes 'ackkhuma" to Sahampati, and kalamakari to Anuruddha.
#. <br>
#. VAR: yaṃ kālamakarī muni → cakkhumā parinibbuto (^sn6.15#1 [15.
#. Pari­nib­bā­na­sutta])
msgctxt "dn16:292.4"
msgid "yaṃ kālamakarī muni."
msgstr "the sage has done his time."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="243"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:293.1"
msgid "Asallīnena cittena,"
msgstr "He put up with painful feelings"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:293.2"
msgid "vedanaṃ ajjhavāsayi;"
msgstr "without flinching."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:293.3"
msgid "Pajjotasseva nibbānaṃ,"
msgstr "The liberation of his heart"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:293.4"
msgid "vimokkho cetaso ahū”ti."
msgstr "was like the extinguishing of a lamp.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="244"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:294.1"
msgid ""
"Parinibbute bhagavati saha parinibbānā āyasmā ānando imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha became fully extinguished, Venerable Ānanda recited this "
"verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="245"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:295.1"
msgid "“Tadāsi yaṃ bhiṃsanakaṃ,"
msgstr "“Then there was terror!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:295.2"
msgid "tadāsi lomahaṃsanaṃ;"
msgstr "Then they had goose-bumps!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:295.3"
msgid "Sabbākāravarūpete,"
msgstr "When the Buddha, endowed with all fine qualities,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:295.4"
msgid "sambuddhe parinibbute”ti."
msgstr "became fully extinguished.”"

# Note that here the text omits kese pakiriya, for obvious reasons. The Pali is almost always incredibly precise in such tiny details!
#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="246"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts2.158"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:296.1"
msgid ""
"Parinibbute bhagavati ye te tattha bhikkhū avītarāgā appekacce bāhā paggayha "
"kandanti, chinnapātaṃ papatanti, āvaṭṭanti vivaṭṭanti, “atikhippaṃ bhagavā "
"parinibbuto, atikhippaṃ sugato parinibbuto, atikhippaṃ cakkhuṃ loke "
"antarahito”ti."
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha became fully extinguished, some of the mendicants there, "
"with arms raised, falling down like their feet were chopped off, rolling "
"back and forth, lamented:"

msgctxt "dn16:296.2"
msgid "Ye pana te bhikkhū vītarāgā, te satā sampajānā adhivāsenti:"
msgstr ""
"But the mendicants who were free of desire endured, mindful and aware, "
"thinking:"

msgctxt "dn16:296.3"
msgid "“aniccā saṅkhārā, taṃ kutettha labbhā”ti."
msgstr "“Conditions are impermanent. How could it be otherwise?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="247"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.11"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:297.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā anuruddho bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then Anuruddha addressed the mendicants:  "

msgctxt "dn16:297.2"
msgid "“alaṃ, āvuso, mā socittha mā paridevittha."
msgstr "“Enough, reverends, do not grieve or lament."

msgctxt "dn16:297.3"
msgid "Nanu etaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā paṭikacceva akkhātaṃ:"
msgstr "Did the Buddha not prepare for this when he explained that"

msgctxt "dn16:297.4"
msgid "‘sabbeheva piyehi manāpehi nānābhāvo vinābhāvo aññathābhāvo’."
msgstr "we must be parted and separated from all we hold dear and beloved?"

msgctxt "dn16:297.5"
msgid "Taṃ kutettha, āvuso, labbhā."
msgstr "How could it we ever have it that"

msgctxt "dn16:297.6"
msgid ""
"‘Yaṃ taṃ jātaṃ bhūtaṃ saṅkhataṃ palokadhammaṃ, taṃ vata mā palujjī’ti, netaṃ "
"ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"what is born, created, conditioned, and liable to fall apart should not fall "
"apart?"

msgctxt "dn16:297.7"
msgid "Devatā, āvuso, ujjhāyantī”ti."
msgstr "The deities are complaining.”"

#. VAR: bhante, āyasmā anuruddho devatā manasi karotī”ti → bhante anuruddha
#. devatā manasi karoti (bj) | bhante anuruddha devatā manasika­ron­tīti (s1-3,
#. km, mr)
msgctxt "dn16:297.8"
msgid "“Kathaṃbhūtā pana, bhante, āyasmā anuruddho devatā manasi karotī”ti?"
msgstr "“But sir, what kind of deities are you thinking of?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="248"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:298.1"
msgid ""
"“Santāvuso ānanda, devatā ākāse pathavīsaññiniyo kese pakiriya kandanti, "
"bāhā paggayha kandanti, chinnapātaṃ papatanti, āvaṭṭanti, vivaṭṭanti:"
msgstr ""
"“There are, Ānanda, deities—both in the sky and on the earth—who are "
"percipient of the earth. With hair disheveled and arms raised, they fall "
"down like their feet were chopped off, rolling back and forth, lamenting:"

msgctxt "dn16:298.2"
msgid ""
"‘atikhippaṃ bhagavā parinibbuto, atikhippaṃ sugato parinibbuto, atikhippaṃ "
"cakkhuṃ loke antarahito’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Too soon the Blessed One has become fully extinguished! Too soon the Holy "
"One has become fully extinguished! Too soon the seer has vanished from the "
"world!’"

msgctxt "dn16:298.3"
msgid ""
"Santāvuso ānanda, devatā pathaviyā pathavīsaññiniyo kese pakiriya kandanti, "
"bāhā paggayha kandanti, chinnapātaṃ papatanti, āvaṭṭanti, vivaṭṭanti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:298.4"
msgid ""
"‘atikhippaṃ bhagavā parinibbuto, atikhippaṃ sugato parinibbuto, atikhippaṃ "
"cakkhuṃ loke antarahito’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:298.5"
msgid "Yā pana tā devatā vītarāgā, tā satā sampajānā adhivāsenti:"
msgstr ""
"But the deities who are free of desire endure, mindful and aware, thinking:"

msgctxt "dn16:298.6"
msgid "‘aniccā saṅkhārā, taṃ kutettha labbhā’”ti."
msgstr "‘Conditions are impermanent. How could it be otherwise?’”"

msgctxt "dn16:298.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ca anuruddho āyasmā ca ānando taṃ rattāvasesaṃ dhammiyā "
"kathāya vītināmesuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then Ānanda and Anuruddha spent the rest of the night talking about Dhamma."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="249"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.12"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.159"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:299.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā anuruddho āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then Anuruddha said to Ānanda:"

msgctxt "dn16:299.2"
msgid "“gacchāvuso ānanda, kusināraṃ pavisitvā kosinārakānaṃ mallānaṃ ārocehi:"
msgstr "“Go, Ānanda, into Kusinārā and inform the Mallians:"

msgctxt "dn16:299.3"
msgid "‘parinibbuto, vāseṭṭhā, bhagavā, yassadāni kālaṃ maññathā’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Vāseṭṭhas, the Buddha has become fully extinguished. Please come at your "
"convenience.’”"

msgctxt "dn16:299.4"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando āyasmato anuruddhassa paṭissutvā "
"pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya attadutiyo kusināraṃ pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"“Yes, sir,” replied Ānanda. Then, in the morning, he robed up and, taking "
"his bowl and robes, entered Kusinārā with a companion."

msgctxt "dn16:299.5"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena kosinārakā mallā sandhāgāre sannipatitā honti teneva "
"karaṇīyena."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the Mallians of Kusinārā were sitting together at the "
"meeting hall on some business."

msgctxt "dn16:299.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena kosinārakānaṃ mallānaṃ sandhāgāraṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Ānanda went up to them,"

msgctxt "dn16:299.7"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā kosinārakānaṃ mallānaṃ ārocesi:"
msgstr "and announced:"

msgctxt "dn16:299.8"
msgid "“parinibbuto, vāseṭṭhā, bhagavā, yassadāni kālaṃ maññathā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Vāseṭṭhas, the Buddha has become fully extinguished. Please come at your "
"convenience.”"

msgctxt "dn16:299.9"
msgid ""
"Idamāyasmato ānandassa vacanaṃ sutvā mallā ca mallaputtā ca mallasuṇisā ca "
"mallapajāpatiyo ca aghāvino dummanā cetodukkhasamappitā appekacce kese "
"pakiriya kandanti, bāhā paggayha kandanti, chinnapātaṃ papatanti, āvaṭṭanti, "
"vivaṭṭanti:"
msgstr ""
"When they heard what Ānanda had to say, the Mallians, their sons, daughters-"
"in-law, and wives became distraught, saddened, and grief-stricken. And some, "
"with hair disheveled and arms raised, falling down like their feet were "
"chopped off, rolling back and forth, lamented:"

msgctxt "dn16:299.10"
msgid ""
"“atikhippaṃ bhagavā parinibbuto, atikhippaṃ sugato parinibbuto, atikhippaṃ "
"cakkhuṃ loke antarahito”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Too soon the Blessed One has become fully extinguished! Too soon the Holy "
"One has become fully extinguished! Too soon the seer has vanished from the "
"world!”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:300.1"
msgid "37. Buddhasarīrapūjā"
msgstr "The Rites of Venerating the Buddha’s Corpse"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="250"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.13"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:301.1"
msgid "Atha kho kosinārakā mallā purise āṇāpesuṃ:"
msgstr "Then the Mallians ordered their men:"

msgctxt "dn16:301.2"
msgid ""
"“tena hi, bhaṇe, kusinārāyaṃ gandhamālañca sabbañca tāḷāvacaraṃ "
"sannipātethā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“So then, my men, collect fragrances and garlands, and all the musical "
"instruments in Kusinārā.”"

msgctxt "dn16:301.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho kosinārakā mallā gandhamālañca sabbañca tāḷāvacaraṃ pañca ca "
"dussayugasatāni ādāya yena upavattanaṃ mallānaṃ sālavanaṃ, yena bhagavato "
"sarīraṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr ""
"Then—taking those fragrances and garlands, all the musical instruments, and "
"five hundred pairs of garments—they went to the Mallian <i>sal</i> grove at "
"Upavattana and approached the Buddha’s corpse."

msgctxt "dn16:301.4"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato sarīraṃ naccehi gītehi vāditehi mālehi gandhehi "
"sakkarontā garuṃ karontā mānentā pūjentā celavitānāni karontā maṇḍalamāḷe "
"paṭiyādentā ekadivasaṃ vītināmesuṃ."
msgstr ""
"They spent the day honoring, respecting, revering, and venerating the Buddha’"
"s corpse with dance and song and music and garlands and fragrances, and "
"making awnings and setting up pavilions."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="251"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:302.1"
msgid "Atha kho kosinārakānaṃ mallānaṃ etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then they thought:"

msgctxt "dn16:302.2"
msgid ""
"“ativikālo kho ajja bhagavato sarīraṃ jhāpetuṃ, sve dāni mayaṃ bhagavato "
"sarīraṃ jhāpessāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“It’s too late to cremate the Buddha’s corpse today. Let’s do it tomorrow.”"

msgctxt "dn16:302.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho kosinārakā mallā bhagavato sarīraṃ naccehi gītehi vāditehi mālehi "
"gandhehi sakkarontā garuṃ karontā mānentā pūjentā celavitānāni karontā "
"maṇḍalamāḷe paṭiyādentā dutiyampi divasaṃ vītināmesuṃ, tatiyampi divasaṃ "
"vītināmesuṃ, catutthampi divasaṃ vītināmesuṃ, pañcamampi divasaṃ "
"vītināmesuṃ, chaṭṭhampi divasaṃ vītināmesuṃ."
msgstr ""
"But they spent the next day the same way, and so too the third, fourth, "
"fifth, and sixth days."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="252"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.14"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.160"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:303.1"
msgid "Atha kho sattamaṃ divasaṃ kosinārakānaṃ mallānaṃ etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then on the seventh day they thought:"

# Both MW and Anandajoti take it that this means to carry it out of the city to the south. But I can't see how this is justified either by context or syntax. They are already outside the town. 
msgctxt "dn16:303.2"
msgid ""
"“mayaṃ bhagavato sarīraṃ naccehi gītehi vāditehi mālehi gandhehi sakkarontā "
"garuṃ karontā mānentā pūjentā dakkhiṇena dakkhiṇaṃ nagarassa haritvā "
"bāhirena bāhiraṃ dakkhiṇato nagarassa bhagavato sarīraṃ jhāpessāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Honoring, respecting, revering, and venerating the Buddha’s corpse with "
"dance and song and music and garlands and fragrances, let us carry it to the "
"south of the town, and cremate it there outside the town.”"

# Note that this context confirms the sense of ahata and unworn. Elsewhere we have sīsaṃnhāto navaṃ khomayugaṃ nivattho 
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="253"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:304.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena aṭṭha mallapāmokkhā sīsaṃnhātā ahatāni vatthāni "
"nivatthā:"
msgstr ""
"Now at that time eight of the leading Mallians, having bathed their heads "
"and dressed in unworn clothes, said:"

msgctxt "dn16:304.2"
msgid "“mayaṃ bhagavato sarīraṃ uccāressāmā”ti na sakkonti uccāretuṃ."
msgstr "“We shall lift the Buddha’s corpse.” But they were unable to do so."

msgctxt "dn16:304.3"
msgid "Atha kho kosinārakā mallā āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "The Mallians said to Anuruddha:"

msgctxt "dn16:304.4"
msgid ""
"“ko nu kho, bhante anuruddha, hetu ko paccayo, yenime aṭṭha mallapāmokkhā "
"sīsaṃnhātā ahatāni vatthāni nivatthā:"
msgstr ""
"“What is the cause, Venerable Anuruddha, what is the reason why these eight "
"Mallian leaders are unable to lift the Buddha’s corpse?”"

msgctxt "dn16:304.5"
msgid "‘mayaṃ bhagavato sarīraṃ uccāressāmā’ti na sakkonti uccāretun”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:304.6"
msgid ""
"“Aññathā kho, vāseṭṭhā, tumhākaṃ adhippāyo, aññathā devatānaṃ adhippāyo”ti. <"
"a class=\"wp\" id=\"wp6.15\"></a>“"
msgstr "“Vāseṭṭhas, you have one plan, but the deities have a different one.”"

msgctxt "dn16:304.7"
msgid "Kathaṃ pana, bhante, devatānaṃ adhippāyo”ti?"
msgstr "“But sir, what is the deities’ plan?”"

msgctxt "dn16:304.8"
msgid "“Tumhākaṃ kho, vāseṭṭhā, adhippāyo:"
msgstr "“You plan to "

msgctxt "dn16:304.9"
msgid ""
"‘mayaṃ bhagavato sarīraṃ naccehi gītehi vāditehi mālehi gandhehi sakkarontā "
"garuṃ karontā mānentā pūjentā dakkhiṇena dakkhiṇaṃ nagarassa haritvā "
"bāhirena bāhiraṃ dakkhiṇato nagarassa bhagavato sarīraṃ jhāpessāmā’ti;"
msgstr ""
"carry the Buddha’s corpse to the south of the town while venerating it with "
"dance and song and music and garlands and fragrances, and cremate it there "
"outside the town."

msgctxt "dn16:304.10"
msgid "devatānaṃ kho, vāseṭṭhā, adhippāyo:"
msgstr "The deities plan to"

msgctxt "dn16:304.11"
msgid ""
"‘mayaṃ bhagavato sarīraṃ dibbehi naccehi gītehi vāditehi mālehi gandhehi "
"sakkarontā garuṃ karontā mānentā pūjentā uttarena uttaraṃ nagarassa haritvā "
"uttarena dvārena nagaraṃ pavesetvā majjhena majjhaṃ nagarassa haritvā "
"puratthimena dvārena nikkhamitvā puratthimato nagarassa makuṭabandhanaṃ nāma "
"mallānaṃ cetiyaṃ ettha bhagavato sarīraṃ jhāpessāmā’”ti."
msgstr ""
"carry the Buddha’s corpse to the north of the town while venerating it with "
"celestial dance and song and music and garlands and fragrances. Then they "
"plan to enter the town by the northern gate, carry it through the center of "
"the town, leave by the eastern gate, and cremate it there at the Mallian "
"shrine named Makuṭabandhana.”"

msgctxt "dn16:304.12"
msgid "“Yathā, bhante, devatānaṃ adhippāyo, tathā hotū”ti."
msgstr "“Sir, let it be as the deities plan.”"

# The sense of sandhi here is obscure. I think it means "covered without gaps".
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="254"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.16"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.161"></a>
#. VAR: santhatā → saṇṭhitā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn16:305.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena kusinārā yāva sandhisamalasaṅkaṭīrā jaṇṇumattena "
"odhinā mandāravapupphehi santhatā hoti."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the whole of Kusinārā was covered knee-deep with the "
"flowers of the Flame Tree, without gaps even on the filth and rubbish heaps."

msgctxt "dn16:305.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho devatā ca kosinārakā ca mallā bhagavato sarīraṃ dibbehi ca "
"mānusakehi ca naccehi gītehi vāditehi mālehi gandhehi sakkarontā garuṃ "
"karontā mānentā pūjentā uttarena uttaraṃ nagarassa haritvā uttarena dvārena "
"nagaraṃ pavesetvā majjhena majjhaṃ nagarassa haritvā puratthimena dvārena "
"nikkhamitvā puratthimato nagarassa makuṭabandhanaṃ nāma mallānaṃ cetiyaṃ "
"ettha ca bhagavato sarīraṃ nikkhipiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then the deities and the Mallians of Kusinārā carried the Buddha’s corpse to "
"the north of the town while venerating it with celestial and human dance and "
"song and music and garlands and fragrances. Then they entered the town by "
"the northern gate, carried it through the center of the town, left by the "
"eastern gate, and deposited the corpse there at the Mallian shrine named "
"Makuṭabandhana."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="255"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.17"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:306.1"
msgid "Atha kho kosinārakā mallā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "Then the Mallians said to Anuruddha:"

msgctxt "dn16:306.2"
msgid "“kathaṃ mayaṃ, bhante ānanda, tathāgatassa sarīre paṭipajjāmā”ti?"
msgstr "“Sir, how do we proceed when it comes to the Realized One’s corpse?”"

msgctxt "dn16:306.3"
msgid ""
"“Yathā kho, vāseṭṭhā, rañño cakkavattissa sarīre paṭipajjanti, evaṃ "
"tathāgatassa sarīre paṭipajjitabban”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Proceed in the same way as they do for the corpse of a wheel-turning "
"monarch.”"

msgctxt "dn16:306.4"
msgid ""
"“Kathaṃ pana, bhante ānanda, rañño cakkavattissa sarīre paṭipajjantī”ti?"
msgstr "“But how do they proceed with a wheel-turning monarch’s corpse?”"

msgctxt "dn16:306.5"
msgid ""
"“Rañño, vāseṭṭhā, cakkavattissa sarīraṃ ahatena vatthena veṭhenti, ahatena "
"vatthena veṭhetvā vihatena kappāsena veṭhenti, vihatena kappāsena veṭhetvā "
"ahatena vatthena veṭhenti."
msgstr ""
"“They wrap a wheel-turning monarch’s corpse with unworn cloth, then with "
"uncarded cotton, then again with unworn cloth."

msgctxt "dn16:306.6"
msgid ""
"Etena upāyena pañcahi yugasatehi rañño cakkavattissa sarīraṃ veṭhetvā "
"āyasāya teladoṇiyā pakkhipitvā aññissā āyasāya doṇiyā paṭikujjitvā "
"sabbagandhānaṃ citakaṃ karitvā rañño cakkavattissa sarīraṃ jhāpenti."
msgstr ""
"In this way they wrap the corpse with five hundred double-layers. Then they "
"place it in an iron case filled with oil and close it up with another case. "
"Then, having built a funeral pyre out of all kinds of fragrant substances, "
"they cremate the corpse."

msgctxt "dn16:306.7"
msgid "Cātumahāpathe rañño cakkavattissa thūpaṃ karonti."
msgstr "They build a monument for the wheel-turning monarch at the crossroads."

msgctxt "dn16:306.8"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, vāseṭṭhā, rañño cakkavattissa sarīre paṭipajjanti."
msgstr "That’s how they proceed with a wheel-turning monarch’s corpse."

msgctxt "dn16:306.9"
msgid ""
"Yathā kho, vāseṭṭhā, rañño cakkavattissa sarīre paṭipajjanti, evaṃ "
"tathāgatassa sarīre paṭipajjitabbaṃ."
msgstr "Proceed in the same way with the Realized One’s corpse."

msgctxt "dn16:306.10"
msgid "Cātumahāpathe tathāgatassa thūpo kātabbo."
msgstr "A monument for the Realized One is to be built at the crossroads."

msgctxt "dn16:306.11"
msgid ""
"Tattha ye mālaṃ vā gandhaṃ vā cuṇṇakaṃ vā āropessanti vā abhivādessanti vā "
"cittaṃ vā pasādessanti, tesaṃ taṃ bhavissati dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"When someone there lifts up garlands or fragrance or powder, or bows, or "
"inspires confidence in their heart, that will be for their lasting welfare "
"and happiness.”"

#. <a class="wp" id="wp6.18"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:306.12"
msgid "Atha kho kosinārakā mallā purise āṇāpesuṃ:"
msgstr "Then the Mallians ordered their men:"

msgctxt "dn16:306.13"
msgid "“tena hi, bhaṇe, mallānaṃ vihataṃ kappāsaṃ sannipātethā”ti."
msgstr "“So then, my men, collect uncarded cotton.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="256"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.162"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:307.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho kosinārakā mallā bhagavato sarīraṃ ahatena vatthena veṭhetvā "
"vihatena kappāsena veṭhesuṃ, vihatena kappāsena veṭhetvā ahatena vatthena "
"veṭhesuṃ."
msgstr "So the Mallians wrapped the Buddha’s corpse,"

msgctxt "dn16:307.2"
msgid ""
"Etena upāyena pañcahi yugasatehi bhagavato sarīraṃ veṭhetvā āyasāya "
"teladoṇiyā pakkhipitvā aññissā āyasāya doṇiyā paṭikujjitvā sabbagandhānaṃ "
"citakaṃ karitvā bhagavato sarīraṃ citakaṃ āropesuṃ."
msgstr ""
"and placed it in an iron case filled with oil. Then, having built a funeral "
"pyre out of all kinds of fragrant substances, they lifted the corpse on to "
"the pyre."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:308.1"
msgid "38. Mahākassapattheravatthu"
msgstr "Mahākassapa’s Arrival"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="257"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.19"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:309.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā mahākassapo pāvāya kusināraṃ "
"addhānamaggappaṭipanno hoti mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi "
"bhikkhusatehi."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Venerable Mahākassapa was travelling along the road from "
"Pāvā to Kusinārā together with a large Saṅgha of around five hundred "
"mendicants."

msgctxt "dn16:309.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo maggā okkamma aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle nisīdi."
msgstr "Then he left the road and sat at the root of a tree."

# This is probably the ultimate source for the Zen story about the Buddha, Mahakassapa, and a flower.
msgctxt "dn16:309.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena aññataro ājīvako kusinārāya mandāravapupphaṃ gahetvā "
"pāvaṃ addhānamaggappaṭipanno hoti."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time a certain <i>ājīvaka</i> ascetic had picked up a Flame Tree "
"flower in Kusinārā and was travelling along the road to Pāvā."

msgctxt "dn16:309.4"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho āyasmā mahākassapo taṃ ājīvakaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ, disvā taṃ "
"ājīvakaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Mahākassapa saw him coming off in the distance and said to him:"

msgctxt "dn16:309.5"
msgid "“apāvuso, amhākaṃ satthāraṃ jānāsī”ti?"
msgstr "“Reverend, might you know about our Teacher?”"

msgctxt "dn16:309.6"
msgid "“Āmāvuso, jānāmi, ajja sattāhaparinibbuto samaṇo gotamo."
msgstr ""
"“Yes, reverend. Seven days ago the ascetic Gotama became fully extinguished."

msgctxt "dn16:309.7"
msgid "Tato me idaṃ mandāravapupphaṃ gahitan”ti."
msgstr "From there I picked up this Flame Tree flower.”"

msgctxt "dn16:309.8"
msgid ""
"Tattha ye te bhikkhū avītarāgā appekacce bāhā paggayha kandanti, chinnapātaṃ "
"papatanti, āvaṭṭanti, vivaṭṭanti:"
msgstr ""
"Some of the mendicants there, with arms raised, falling down like their feet "
"were chopped off, rolling back and forth, lamented:"

msgctxt "dn16:309.9"
msgid ""
"“atikhippaṃ bhagavā parinibbuto, atikhippaṃ sugato parinibbuto, atikhippaṃ "
"cakkhuṃ loke antarahito”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Too soon the Blessed One has become fully extinguished! Too soon the Holy "
"One has become fully extinguished! Too soon the seer has vanished from the "
"world!”"

msgctxt "dn16:309.10"
msgid "Ye pana te bhikkhū vītarāgā, te satā sampajānā adhivāsenti:"
msgstr ""
"But the mendicants who were free of desire endured, mindful and aware, "
"thinking:"

msgctxt "dn16:309.11"
msgid "“aniccā saṅkhārā, taṃ kutettha labbhā”ti."
msgstr "“Conditions are impermanent. How could it be otherwise?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="258"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.20"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.163"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:310.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena subhaddo nāma vuddhapabbajito tassaṃ parisāyaṃ "
"nisinno hoti."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time a monk named Subhadda, who had gone forth when old, was "
"sitting in that assembly."

msgctxt "dn16:310.2"
msgid "Atha kho subhaddo vuddhapabbajito te bhikkhū etadavoca:"
msgstr "He said to those mendicants:"

# The syntax here is obscure to me. Confusingly, both the former and latter parts of the sentence normally take the instrumental: "sumuttāhaṃ buddhena"; but also "tena homi upadduto". The Sanskrit is much clearer: "muktāḥ smas tataḥ kaukṛtikān mahallāt || ya evam āha || idaṃ vo bhikṣavaḥ karaṇīyam idam akaraṇīyam"
msgctxt "dn16:310.3"
msgid ""
"“alaṃ, āvuso, mā socittha, mā paridevittha, sumuttā mayaṃ tena mahāsamaṇena."
msgstr ""
"“Enough, reverends, do not grieve or lament. We’re well rid of that Great "
"Ascetic harassing us:"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn16:310.4"
msgid "Upaddutā ca homa:"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn16:310.5"
msgid "‘idaṃ vo kappati, idaṃ vo na kappatī’ti."
msgstr "‘This is allowable for you; this is not allowable for you.’"

msgctxt "dn16:310.6"
msgid ""
"Idāni pana mayaṃ yaṃ icchissāma, taṃ karissāma, yaṃ na icchissāma, na taṃ "
"karissāmā”ti."
msgstr "Well, now we shall do what we want and not do what we don’t want.”"

msgctxt "dn16:310.7"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then Venerable Mahākassapa addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "dn16:310.8"
msgid "“alaṃ, āvuso, mā socittha, mā paridevittha."
msgstr "“Enough, reverends, do not grieve or lament."

msgctxt "dn16:310.9"
msgid "Nanu etaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā paṭikacceva akkhātaṃ:"
msgstr "Did the Buddha not prepare for this when he explained that"

msgctxt "dn16:310.10"
msgid "‘sabbeheva piyehi manāpehi nānābhāvo vinābhāvo aññathābhāvo’."
msgstr "we must be parted and separated from all we hold dear and beloved?"

msgctxt "dn16:310.11"
msgid "Taṃ kutettha, āvuso, labbhā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:310.12"
msgid ""
"‘Yaṃ taṃ jātaṃ bhūtaṃ saṅkhataṃ palokadhammaṃ, taṃ tathāgatassāpi sarīraṃ mā "
"palujjī’ti, netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"How could anyone make it so that what is born, created, conditioned, and "
"liable to fall apart should not fall apart, even the Realized One’s body?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="259"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.21"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:311.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena cattāro mallapāmokkhā sīsaṃnhātā ahatāni vatthāni "
"nivatthā:"
msgstr ""
"Now at that time four of the leading Mallians, having bathed their heads and "
"dressed in unworn clothes, said:"

msgctxt "dn16:311.2"
msgid "“mayaṃ bhagavato citakaṃ āḷimpessāmā”ti na sakkonti āḷimpetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"“We shall light the Buddha’s funeral pyre.” But they were unable to do so."

msgctxt "dn16:311.3"
msgid "Atha kho kosinārakā mallā āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "The Mallians said to Anuruddha:"

msgctxt "dn16:311.4"
msgid ""
"“ko nu kho, bhante anuruddha, hetu ko paccayo, yenime cattāro mallapāmokkhā "
"sīsaṃnhātā ahatāni vatthāni nivatthā:"
msgstr ""
"“What is the cause, Venerable Anuruddha, what is the reason why these four "
"Mallian leaders are unable to light the Buddha’s funeral pyre?”"

msgctxt "dn16:311.5"
msgid "‘mayaṃ bhagavato citakaṃ āḷimpessāmā’ti na sakkonti āḷimpetun”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn16:311.6"
msgid "“Aññathā kho, vāseṭṭhā, devatānaṃ adhippāyo”ti."
msgstr "“Vāseṭṭhas, the deities have a different plan.”"

msgctxt "dn16:311.7"
msgid "“Kathaṃ pana, bhante, devatānaṃ adhippāyo”ti?"
msgstr "“But sir, what is the deities’ plan?”"

msgctxt "dn16:311.8"
msgid "“Devatānaṃ kho, vāseṭṭhā, adhippāyo:"
msgstr "“The deities plan is this."

msgctxt "dn16:311.9"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ āyasmā mahākassapo pāvāya kusināraṃ addhānamaggappaṭipanno mahatā "
"bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi."
msgstr ""
"Venerable Mahākassapa is travelling along the road from Pāvā to Kusinārā "
"together with a large Saṅgha of around five hundred mendicants."

msgctxt "dn16:311.10"
msgid ""
"Na tāva bhagavato citako pajjalissati, yāvāyasmā mahākassapo bhagavato pāde "
"sirasā na vandissatī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"The Buddha’s funeral pyre shall not burn until he bows with his head at the "
"Buddha’s feet.”"

msgctxt "dn16:311.11"
msgid "“Yathā, bhante, devatānaṃ adhippāyo, tathā hotū”ti."
msgstr "“Sir, let it be as the deities plan.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="260"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.22"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.164"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:312.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo yena kusinārā makuṭabandhanaṃ nāma mallānaṃ "
"cetiyaṃ, yena bhagavato citako tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"The Venerable Mahākassapa came to the Mallian shrine named Makuṭabandhana at "
"Kusinārā and approached the Buddha’s funeral pyre."

msgctxt "dn16:312.2"
msgid ""
"upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ cīvaraṃ katvā añjaliṃ paṇāmetvā tikkhattuṃ citakaṃ "
"padakkhiṇaṃ katvā bhagavato pāde sirasā vandi."
msgstr ""
"Arranging his robe over one shoulder and raising his cupped palms, he "
"respectfully circled the Buddha three times, keeping him on his right, and "
"bowed with his head to the Buddha’s feet."

msgctxt "dn16:312.3"
msgid ""
"Tānipi kho pañcabhikkhusatāni ekaṃsaṃ cīvaraṃ katvā añjaliṃ paṇāmetvā "
"tikkhattuṃ citakaṃ padakkhiṇaṃ katvā bhagavato pāde sirasā vandiṃsu."
msgstr "And the five hundred mendicant did likewise."

msgctxt "dn16:312.4"
msgid ""
"Vandite ca panāyasmatā mahākassapena tehi ca pañcahi bhikkhusatehi sayameva "
"bhagavato citako pajjali."
msgstr ""
"And when Mahākassapa and the five hundred mendicants bowed the Buddha’s "
"funeral pyre burst into flames all by itself."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="261"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.23"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:313.1"
msgid ""
"Jhāyamānassa kho pana bhagavato sarīrassa yaṃ ahosi chavīti vā cammanti vā "
"maṃsanti vā nhārūti vā lasikāti vā, tassa neva chārikā paññāyittha, na masi;"
msgstr ""
"And when the Buddha’s corpse was cremated no ash or soot was found from "
"outer or inner skin, flesh, sinews, or synovial fluid."

# Anandajoti has "neither charcoal was evident, nor was ash of the body left over.", yielding a strikingly different sense. But the idiom as ountuated here is found in a number of places, including below. Further, sarīrāneva must be plural in accord with the use following: sarīrānaṃ. Previously, sarira (corpse) is singular only.
msgctxt "dn16:313.2"
msgid "sarīrāneva avasissiṃsu."
msgstr "Only the relics remained."

msgctxt "dn16:313.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma sappissa vā telassa vā jhāyamānassa neva chārikā paññāyati, "
"na masi;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like when ghee or oil blaze and burn, and neither ashes nor soot are "
"found."

msgctxt "dn16:313.4"
msgid ""
"evameva bhagavato sarīrassa jhāyamānassa yaṃ ahosi chavīti vā cammanti vā "
"maṃsanti vā nhārūti vā lasikāti vā, tassa neva chārikā paññāyittha, na masi;"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when the Buddha’s corpse was cremated no ash or soot was "
"found from outer or inner skin, flesh, sinews, or synovial fluid."

msgctxt "dn16:313.5"
msgid "sarīrāneva avasissiṃsu."
msgstr "Only the relics remained."

#. VAR: dveva dussāni na ḍayhiṃsu → dveva dussāni ḍayhiṃsu (si, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:313.6"
msgid ""
"Tesañca pañcannaṃ dussayugasatānaṃ dveva dussāni na ḍayhiṃsu yañca "
"sabbaabbhantarimaṃ yañca bāhiraṃ."
msgstr ""
"And of those five hundred pairs of garments only two were not burnt: the "
"innermost and the outermost."

msgctxt "dn16:313.7"
msgid ""
"Daḍḍhe ca kho pana bhagavato sarīre antalikkhā udakadhārā pātubhavitvā "
"bhagavato citakaṃ nibbāpesi."
msgstr ""
"But when the Buddha’s corpse was consumed the funeral pyre was extinguished "
"by a stream of water that appeared in the sky,"

#. VAR: Udakasālatopi → udakaṃ sālatopi (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn16:313.8"
msgid "Udakasālatopi abbhunnamitvā bhagavato citakaṃ nibbāpesi."
msgstr "by water dripping from the <i>sal</i> trees,"

msgctxt "dn16:313.9"
msgid "Kosinārakāpi mallā sabbagandhodakena bhagavato citakaṃ nibbāpesuṃ."
msgstr "and by the Mallians’ fragrant water."

msgctxt "dn16:313.10"
msgid ""
"Atha kho kosinārakā mallā bhagavato sarīrāni sattāhaṃ sandhāgāre "
"sattipañjaraṃ karitvā dhanupākāraṃ parikkhipāpetvā naccehi gītehi vāditehi "
"mālehi gandhehi sakkariṃsu garuṃ kariṃsu mānesuṃ pūjesuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then the Mallians made a cage of spears for the Buddha’s relics in the "
"meeting hall and surrounded it with a buttress of bows. For seven days they "
"honored, respected, revered, and venerated them with dance and song and "
"music and garlands and fragrances."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:314.1"
msgid "39. Sarīradhātuvibhajana"
msgstr "Distributing the Relics"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="262"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.24"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:315.1"
msgid "Assosi kho rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto:"
msgstr "King Ajātasattu of Magadha heard"

msgctxt "dn16:315.2"
msgid "“bhagavā kira kusinārāyaṃ parinibbuto”ti."
msgstr "that the Buddha had become fully extinguished at Kusinārā."

msgctxt "dn16:315.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto kosinārakānaṃ mallānaṃ dūtaṃ "
"pāhesi:"
msgstr "He sent an envoy to the Mallians of Kusinārā:"

msgctxt "dn16:315.4"
msgid ""
"“bhagavāpi khattiyo ahampi khattiyo, ahampi arahāmi bhagavato sarīrānaṃ "
"bhāgaṃ, ahampi bhagavato sarīrānaṃ thūpañca mahañca karissāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The Buddha was an aristocrat, and so am I. I too deserve a share of the "
"Buddha’s relics. I will build a large monument for them.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="263"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.165"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:316.1"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho vesālikā licchavī:"
msgstr "The Licchavis of Vesālī also heard that"

msgctxt "dn16:316.2"
msgid "“bhagavā kira kusinārāyaṃ parinibbuto”ti."
msgstr "that the Buddha had become fully extinguished at Kusinārā."

msgctxt "dn16:316.3"
msgid "Atha kho vesālikā licchavī kosinārakānaṃ mallānaṃ dūtaṃ pāhesuṃ:"
msgstr "They sent an envoy to the Mallians of Kusinārā:"

msgctxt "dn16:316.4"
msgid ""
"“bhagavāpi khattiyo mayampi khattiyā, mayampi arahāma bhagavato sarīrānaṃ "
"bhāgaṃ, mayampi bhagavato sarīrānaṃ thūpañca mahañca karissāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The Buddha was an aristocrat, and so are we. We too deserve a share of the "
"Buddha’s relics. We will build a large monument for them.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="264"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:317.1"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho kapilavatthuvāsī sakyā:"
msgstr "The Sakyans of Kapilavatthu also heard that"

msgctxt "dn16:317.2"
msgid "“bhagavā kira kusinārāyaṃ parinibbuto”ti."
msgstr "that the Buddha had become fully extinguished at Kusinārā."

msgctxt "dn16:317.3"
msgid "Atha kho kapilavatthuvāsī sakyā kosinārakānaṃ mallānaṃ dūtaṃ pāhesuṃ:"
msgstr "They sent an envoy to the Mallians of Kusinārā:"

msgctxt "dn16:317.4"
msgid ""
"“bhagavā amhākaṃ ñātiseṭṭho, mayampi arahāma bhagavato sarīrānaṃ bhāgaṃ, "
"mayampi bhagavato sarīrānaṃ thūpañca mahañca karissāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The Buddha was our foremost relative. We too deserve a share of the Buddha’"
"s relics. We will build a large monument for them.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="265"></a>
#. VAR: bulayo → thūlayo (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn16:318.1"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho allakappakā bulayo:"
msgstr "The Bulas of Allakappa also heard"

msgctxt "dn16:318.2"
msgid "“bhagavā kira kusinārāyaṃ parinibbuto”ti."
msgstr "that the Buddha had become fully extinguished at Kusinārā."

msgctxt "dn16:318.3"
msgid "Atha kho allakappakā bulayo kosinārakānaṃ mallānaṃ dūtaṃ pāhesuṃ:"
msgstr "They sent an envoy to the Mallians of Kusinārā:"

msgctxt "dn16:318.4"
msgid ""
"“bhagavāpi khattiyo mayampi khattiyā, mayampi arahāma bhagavato sarīrānaṃ "
"bhāgaṃ, mayampi bhagavato sarīrānaṃ thūpañca mahañca karissāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The Buddha was an aristocrat, and so are we. We too deserve a share of the "
"Buddha’s relics. We will build a large monument for them.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="266"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:319.1"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho rāmagāmakā koḷiyā:"
msgstr "The Koḷiyans of Rāmagāma also heard"

msgctxt "dn16:319.2"
msgid "“bhagavā kira kusinārāyaṃ parinibbuto”ti."
msgstr "that the Buddha had become fully extinguished at Kusinārā."

msgctxt "dn16:319.3"
msgid "Atha kho rāmagāmakā koḷiyā kosinārakānaṃ mallānaṃ dūtaṃ pāhesuṃ:"
msgstr "They sent an envoy to the Mallians of Kusinārā:"

msgctxt "dn16:319.4"
msgid ""
"“bhagavāpi khattiyo mayampi khattiyā, mayampi arahāma bhagavato sarīrānaṃ "
"bhāgaṃ, mayampi bhagavato sarīrānaṃ thūpañca mahañca karissāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The Buddha was an aristocrat, and so are we. We too deserve a share of the "
"Buddha’s relics. We will build a large monument for them.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="267"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:320.1"
msgid "Assosi kho veṭṭhadīpako brāhmaṇo:"
msgstr "The brahmin of Veṭhadīpa also heard"

msgctxt "dn16:320.2"
msgid "“bhagavā kira kusinārāyaṃ parinibbuto”ti."
msgstr "that the Buddha had become fully extinguished at Kusinārā."

msgctxt "dn16:320.3"
msgid "Atha kho veṭṭhadīpako brāhmaṇo kosinārakānaṃ mallānaṃ dūtaṃ pāhesi:"
msgstr "He sent an envoy to the Mallians of Kusinārā:"

msgctxt "dn16:320.4"
msgid ""
"“bhagavāpi khattiyo ahampismi brāhmaṇo, ahampi arahāmi bhagavato sarīrānaṃ "
"bhāgaṃ, ahampi bhagavato sarīrānaṃ thūpañca mahañca karissāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The Buddha was an aristocrat, and I am a brahmin. I too deserve a share of "
"the Buddha’s relics. I will build a large monument for them.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="268"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:321.1"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho pāveyyakā mallā:"
msgstr "The Mallians of Pāvā also heard"

msgctxt "dn16:321.2"
msgid "“bhagavā kira kusinārāyaṃ parinibbuto”ti."
msgstr "that the Buddha had become fully extinguished at Kusinārā."

msgctxt "dn16:321.3"
msgid "Atha kho pāveyyakā mallā kosinārakānaṃ mallānaṃ dūtaṃ pāhesuṃ:"
msgstr "They sent an envoy to the Mallians of Kusinārā:"

msgctxt "dn16:321.4"
msgid ""
"“bhagavāpi khattiyo mayampi khattiyā, mayampi arahāma bhagavato sarīrānaṃ "
"bhāgaṃ, mayampi bhagavato sarīrānaṃ thūpañca mahañca karissāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The Buddha was an aristocrat, and so are we. We too deserve a share of the "
"Buddha’s relics. We will build a large monument for them.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="269"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.25"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.166"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:322.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, kosinārakā mallā te saṅghe gaṇe etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"When they had spoken, the Mallians of Kusinārā said to those various groups:"

# Anandajoti's "we will not see a share" is incorrect. This is the future second plural of dadati.
msgctxt "dn16:322.2"
msgid ""
"“bhagavā amhākaṃ gāmakkhette parinibbuto, na mayaṃ dassāma bhagavato "
"sarīrānaṃ bhāgan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The Buddha became fully extinguished in our village district. We will not "
"give away a share of his relics.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="270"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:323.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, doṇo brāhmaṇo te saṅghe gaṇe etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Doṇa the brahmin said to those various groups:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="271"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:324.1"
msgid "“Suṇantu bhonto mama ekavācaṃ,"
msgstr "“Hear, sirs, a single word from me."

#. <br>
#. VAR: Amhāka → amhākaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:324.2"
msgid "Amhāka buddho ahu khantivādo;"
msgstr "Our Buddha’s teaching was acceptance."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:324.3"
msgid "Na hi sādhu yaṃ uttamapuggalassa,"
msgstr "It would not be good to fight over"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:324.4"
msgid "Sarīrabhāge siyā sampahāro."
msgstr "a share of the supreme person’s relics."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="272"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:325.1"
msgid "Sabbeva bhonto sahitā samaggā,"
msgstr "Let us make eight portions, good sirs,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:325.2"
msgid "Sammodamānā karomaṭṭhabhāge;"
msgstr "rejoicing in unity and harmony."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:325.3"
msgid "Vitthārikā hontu disāsu thūpā,"
msgstr "Let there be monuments far and wide,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:325.4"
msgid "Bahū janā cakkhumato pasannā”ti."
msgstr "so many folk may gain faith in the Seer!”"

#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="273"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:326.1"
msgid ""
"“Tena hi, brāhmaṇa, tvaññeva bhagavato sarīrāni aṭṭhadhā samaṃ savibhattaṃ "
"vibhajāhī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Well then, brahmin, you yourself should fairly divide the Buddha’s relics "
"in eight portions.”"

msgctxt "dn16:326.2"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho doṇo brāhmaṇo tesaṃ saṅghānaṃ gaṇānaṃ paṭissutvā bhagavato "
"sarīrāni aṭṭhadhā samaṃ suvibhattaṃ vibhajitvā te saṅghe gaṇe etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"“Yes, sirs,” replied Doṇa to those various groups. He divided the relics as "
"asked and said to them:"

msgctxt "dn16:326.3"
msgid ""
"“imaṃ me bhonto tumbaṃ dadantu ahampi tumbassa thūpañca mahañca karissāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sirs, please give me the urn, and I shall build a large monument for it.”"

msgctxt "dn16:326.4"
msgid "Adaṃsu kho te doṇassa brāhmaṇassa tumbaṃ."
msgstr "So they gave Doṇa the urn."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="274"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.26"></a>
#. VAR: pippalivaniyā → pipphalivaniyā (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn16:327.1"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho pippalivaniyā moriyā:"
msgstr "The Moras of Pippalivana heard"

msgctxt "dn16:327.2"
msgid "“bhagavā kira kusinārāyaṃ parinibbuto”ti."
msgstr "that the Buddha had become fully extinguished at Kusinārā."

msgctxt "dn16:327.3"
msgid "Atha kho pippalivaniyā moriyā kosinārakānaṃ mallānaṃ dūtaṃ pāhesuṃ:"
msgstr "They sent an envoy to the Mallians of Kusinārā:"

msgctxt "dn16:327.4"
msgid ""
"“bhagavāpi khattiyo mayampi khattiyā, mayampi arahāma bhagavato sarīrānaṃ "
"bhāgaṃ, mayampi bhagavato sarīrānaṃ thūpañca mahañca karissāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The Buddha was an aristocrat, and so are we. We too deserve a share of the "
"Buddha’s relics. We will build a large monument for them.”"

msgctxt "dn16:327.5"
msgid "“Natthi bhagavato sarīrānaṃ bhāgo, vibhattāni bhagavato sarīrāni."
msgstr ""
"“There are no portion of the Buddha’s relics left, they have already been "
"portioned out.”"

msgctxt "dn16:327.6"
msgid "Ito aṅgāraṃ harathā”ti."
msgstr "Here, take the embers.”"

#. VAR: hariṃsu → āhariṃsu (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "dn16:327.7"
msgid "Te tato aṅgāraṃ hariṃsu."
msgstr "So they took the embers."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn16:328.1"
msgid "40. Dhātuthūpapūjā"
msgstr "Venerating the Relics"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="275"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6.27"></a><a
#. class="pts" id="pts2.167"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:329.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto rājagahe bhagavato sarīrānaṃ "
"thūpañca mahañca akāsi."
msgstr "Then King Ajātasattu of Magadha,"

msgctxt "dn16:329.2"
msgid ""
"Vesālikāpi licchavī vesāliyaṃ bhagavato sarīrānaṃ thūpañca mahañca akaṃsu."
msgstr "the Licchavis of Vesālī,"

msgctxt "dn16:329.3"
msgid ""
"Kapilavatthuvāsīpi sakyā kapilavatthusmiṃ bhagavato sarīrānaṃ thūpañca "
"mahañca akaṃsu."
msgstr "the Sakyans of Kapilavatthu,"

msgctxt "dn16:329.4"
msgid ""
"Allakappakāpi bulayo allakappe bhagavato sarīrānaṃ thūpañca mahañca akaṃsu."
msgstr "the Bulas of Allakappa,"

msgctxt "dn16:329.5"
msgid ""
"Rāmagāmakāpi koḷiyā rāmagāme bhagavato sarīrānaṃ thūpañca mahañca akaṃsu."
msgstr "the Koḷiyans of Rāmagāma,"

msgctxt "dn16:329.6"
msgid ""
"Veṭṭhadīpakopi brāhmaṇo veṭṭhadīpe bhagavato sarīrānaṃ thūpañca mahañca "
"akāsi."
msgstr "the brahmin of Veṭhadīpa,"

msgctxt "dn16:329.7"
msgid "Pāveyyakāpi mallā pāvāyaṃ bhagavato sarīrānaṃ thūpañca mahañca akaṃsu."
msgstr "the Mallians of Pāvā,"

msgctxt "dn16:329.8"
msgid ""
"Kosinārakāpi mallā kusinārāyaṃ bhagavato sarīrānaṃ thūpañca mahañca akaṃsu."
msgstr "the Mallians of Kusinārā,"

msgctxt "dn16:329.9"
msgid "Doṇopi brāhmaṇo tumbassa thūpañca mahañca akāsi."
msgstr "the brahmin Doṇa,"

msgctxt "dn16:329.10"
msgid "Pippalivaniyāpi moriyā pippalivane aṅgārānaṃ thūpañca mahañca akaṃsu."
msgstr ""
"and the Moriyas of Pippalivana built large monuments for their portions and "
"held festivals in their honor."

msgctxt "dn16:329.11"
msgid "Iti aṭṭha sarīrathūpā navamo tumbathūpo dasamo aṅgārathūpo."
msgstr ""
"Thus there were eight monuments for the relics, a ninth for the urn, and a "
"tenth for the embers."

msgctxt "dn16:329.12"
msgid "Evametaṃ bhūtapubbanti."
msgstr "That is how it was in those days."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="276"></a><a class="wp"
#. id="wp6.28"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:330.1"
msgid "Aṭṭhadoṇaṃ cakkhumato sarīraṃ,"
msgstr "There were eight shares of the Seer’s relics."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:330.2"
msgid "Sattadoṇaṃ jambudīpe mahenti;"
msgstr "Seven were worshiped throughout India."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:330.3"
msgid "Ekañca doṇaṃ purisavaruttamassa,"
msgstr "But one share of the most excellent of men"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:330.4"
msgid "Rāmagāme nāgarājā maheti."
msgstr "was worshiped in Rāmagāma by a dragon king."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="277"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:331.1"
msgid "Ekāhi dāṭhā tidivehi pūjitā,"
msgstr "One tooth is venerated by the gods of Thirty-Three,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:331.2"
msgid "Ekā pana gandhārapure mahīyati;"
msgstr "and one is worshiped in the city of Gandhāra;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:331.3"
msgid "Kāliṅgarañño vijite punekaṃ,"
msgstr "another one in the realm of the Kaliṅga King,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:331.4"
msgid "Ekaṃ pana nāgarājā maheti."
msgstr "and one is worshiped by a dragon king."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="278"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:332.1"
msgid "Tasseva tejena ayaṃ vasundharā,"
msgstr "Through their glory this rich earth"

# Anandajoti's "like a most excellent hall" is incorrect. see CPD.
#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:332.2"
msgid "Āyāgaseṭṭhehi mahī alaṅkatā;"
msgstr "is adorned with the best of offerings."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:332.3"
msgid "Evaṃ imaṃ cakkhumato sarīraṃ,"
msgstr "Thus the Seer’s corpse"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:332.4"
msgid "Susakkataṃ sakkatasakkatehi."
msgstr "is well honored by the honorable."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="279"></a><a class="pts" id="pts2.168"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:333.1"
msgid "Devindanāgindanarindapūjito,"
msgstr "It’s venerated by lords of gods, dragons, and spirits;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:333.2"
msgid "Manussindaseṭṭhehi tatheva pūjito;"
msgstr "and likewise venerated by the finest lords of men."

#. <br>
#. VAR: Taṃ vandatha → taṃ taṃ vandatha (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn16:333.3"
msgid "Taṃ vandatha pañjalikā labhitvā,"
msgstr "Honor it with cupped hands when you get the chance,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:333.4"
msgid "Buddho have kappasatehi dullabhoti."
msgstr "for a Buddha is rare even in a hundred eons."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="280"></a>
msgctxt "dn16:334.1"
msgid "Cattālīsa samā dantā,"
msgstr "Altogether forty even teeth,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:334.2"
msgid "kesā lomā ca sabbaso;"
msgstr "and the body hair and head hair,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:334.3"
msgid "Devā hariṃsu ekekaṃ,"
msgstr "were carried off individually by gods"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn16:334.4"
msgid "cakkavāḷaparamparāti."
msgstr "across the universe."

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn16:335.1"
msgid "Mahāparinibbānasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
